antly intrigued. It took me until May to play it as I had a feeling I would be drawn in to the game too much for my own good. I was right.", "appid": "319630", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985926603", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1433160000.0} {"text": "This game got everything you need or want: Bloody butcher, nice weapons, fast and intense rounds and it takes a good teamplay. I'm just saying thumbs up and stay alive!!!", "appid": "232090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004793035", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511697600.0} {"text": "–ò–≥—Ä–∞ —Ö–∑ –∫–∞–∫–∞—è,—è –Ω–µ –∏–≥—Ä–∞–ª xD", "appid": "1089710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198314771590", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "–í –†–ë –æ—Å—Ç–∞–ª—Å—è –æ–¥–∏–Ω –ø—Ä–æ—Ç–∏–≤ –±–æ–±—Ä–∞, —É–≤–∏–¥–µ–ª —Ç–æ—á–∫—É, –∏ –Ω–∞—á–∞–ª –∑–∞ –Ω–µ–π –ª–µ—Ç–µ—Ç—å, –ª–µ—Ç–∞–ª 10 –º–∏–Ω—É—Ç, 20 –º–∏–Ω—É—Ç, 30 –º–∏–Ω—É—Ç, –∞ –ø–æ—Ç–æ–º –æ–∫–∞–∑–∞–ª–æ—Å—å —ç—Ç–æ –ø—è—Ç–Ω–æ –Ω–∞ —ç–∫—Ä–∞–Ω–µ", "appid": "236390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198247533806", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1483444800.0} {"text": "I like it. And I approve it. (type R18 to make it uncensored)", "appid": "927890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198138049619", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544875200.0} {"text": "UBERMOSH:OMEGA is already the eigth game in the series, where you take control of a character, with their specificities, and try to ascend to the OMEGA rank. It's a fast-paced retro arcade game, where you must survive the longer you can so that you can score enough KO (killing enemies) to reach that rank, in a limited arena full of enemies. The six characters introduced in the previous game are back but now, you don't need to level them up for more strength and powers. They retain nearly all their characteristics from Vol 7: * Aya is the polyvalent one, with all the powers (melter, shredder, manastrike, brainclap). She's the core of UBERMOSH series. She is one of the three characters that can use a blade. * Wook can now use brainclap and is still using Onslaught as special power. The Autogun feature (flying gun) is still present and he's quick to upgrade the single flying gun to four of them. * T7 is still the reminder of the former GUNNER mode: only keeping your finger on the left-click to fire without difficulty. He has the Double Strike feature (two weapons) and still has tentacles as special attack. He's still brainclapping. * Q is the only one that can't grab a gun, a reminder to the former KENSAI mode. However, her long blade (or a double blade) is useful to cut bullets more efficiently. She's still brainclapping and using the double/triple melter * Kore is autofiring his gun, uses the Triple Strike and spawns directly with the four flying guns and he's still brainclapping. * Reez is spawning with a gun and a double-edge blade and she's still brainclapping and equipped with manastrike. However, you can choose to customize them with two extra gameplays. All of them have different customizations, however, here are the possibilities: * Up to two extra respawns (as you spawn with four by default) - all * Celerity to move faster - all * Warmup shield for the first ten seconds of a round - Aya, Wook, Kore * Late shield for the last ten seconds of a round - Wook, T7, Q, Kore, Reez * Buckler, a shield deflecting bullets - All except Reez * Shredder - All except Aya who has it naturally * Boneblade, a long-range blade - Aya, Reez * Autogun, the flying gun - All except Wook and Kore who spawn with them - Q is the only one that can choose twice the feature * Warlock, where the character spawns with a Warlock rifle - All except Q who can't grab gun Also, there is a new enemy: a shielded warrior, with the Warlock rifle, able to send multiple shredders and appearing at the same time as the shielder warrior with the same gun. There are no new weapons if you except the Boneblade. Walter Machado, the developer, comes back to what we loved also from UBERMOSH: the possibility to customize the gameplay as we wish to reach the OMEGA Rank, which was kinda missing in Vol 7. The whole way to progress has also turned back to the root of the series, instead of how Vol 7 was working: unlocking feature or improving skills by reaching a specific number of KO. I'm still trying to reach 100% with Wook in the previous game, which is the character I had the harder time to play. The graphics are still the same, even if the characters changed a little from the previous game. It's still that retrogaming feels, with pixels. The soundtrack is still the same. I love UBERMOSH and the whole series, even if I can agree that some of the titles could have been DLC instead of games. Here, the difference between Vol 7 and OMEGA are enough to justify a new game. However, I'm quite curious to see if we're going to have a new game or not. Because OMEGA is the best UBERMOSH game that Walter provided and I feel that everything after could suffer from that excellency (for me anyway). True, I would consider UBERMOSH:OMEGA like the UBERMOSH game you must play. But playing the first title of the series would also give you a real glance at the evolution of the games. Fans of the series will be satisfied, newcomers will enjoy the game as there are enough options to try. Really, a giant applause for Walter, who really outdid themselves this time.", "appid": "1181000", "steamid": "profiles/76561197971532357", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581854400.0} {"text": "OK", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198250440730", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1471435200.0} {"text": "Really nice game<3", "appid": "211050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198971459140", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574942400.0} {"text": "9/10 gra zajebista grafika mega zdecydowanie nie jest latwa. grac mozna multi jak i single player. swiat wielki a budowanie bardzo rozwiniete. wada jest umieranie na multi bo resetuje ci inventory :( ale ogolnie zajefajna", "appid": "242760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198233631436", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1467028800.0} {"text": "You may write me down in history With your bitter, twisted lies, You may tread me in the very dirt But still, like dust, I'll rise. Does my sassiness upset you? Why are you beset with gloom? 'Cause I walk like I've got oil wells Pumping in my living room. Just like moons and like suns, With the certainty of tides, Just like hopes springing high, Still I'll rise. Did you want to see me broken? Bowed head and lowered eyes? Shoulders falling down like teardrops. Weakened by my soulful cries. Does my haughtiness offend you? Don't you take it awful hard 'Cause I laugh like I've got gold mines Diggin' in my own back yard. You may shoot me with your words, You may cut me with your eyes, You may kill me with your hatefulness, But still, like air, I'll rise. Does my sexiness upset you? Does it come as a surprise That I dance like I've got diamonds At the meeting of my thighs? Out of the huts of history's shame I rise Up from a past that's rooted in pain I rise I'm a black ocean, leaping and wide, Welling and swelling I bear in the tide. Leaving behind nights of terror and fear I rise Into a daybreak that's wondrously clear I rise Bringing the gifts that my ancestors gave, I am the dream and the hope of the slave. I rise I rise I rise.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198136268981", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 154