r algo o al menos interactuar de alguna forma, pues de eso se trata o deber√≠a tratarse un videojuego, pues pasa de esta obra de The Chinese Room, puesto que ac√° lo √∫nico que encontrar√°s es una historia corta en formato audiovisual. Como producto art√≠stico dir√© que Dear Esther hace m√©ritos, una narrativa de car√°cter casi po√©tico, un arte gr√°fico sobrecogedor que en lo personal me ha parecido notable, podr√≠as sacarte unos cuantos excelentes wallpapers para tu PC de ac√°, pero lastimosamente toda la \"jugabilidad\", si se le podr√≠a llamar de esa forma, consiste en ir de un punto inicial a un punto final, en un sendero lineal, donde de cuando en cuando te narran la historia motivo de esta obra digital. No podr√≠a decir que la experiencia me disgust√≥, es m√°s me encantar√≠a una versi√≥n VR de Dear Esther, pues disfrutar√≠a a lo grande pase√°ndome por esta isla en un modo con el grado de inmersi√≥n que proporciona la realidad virtual, pues la ambientaci√≥n no tiene desperdicio, esa sensaci√≥n de horror c√≥smico que caldea alrededor es fabulosa y es una l√°stima que no se haya aprovechado todo esto para hacer algo mucho m√°s memorable en el sentido estrictamente videojueguil, con algo m√°s de interacci√≥n, exploraci√≥n y resoluci√≥n de puzzles hubiese bastado, pero ac√° no hay nada de eso. En este punto me encuentro en la disyuntiva de recomendar o no esta obra y creo que la recomendar√© a quienes busquen pasar un rato agradable visionando una breve historia con un despliegue visual que estremece. Si buscas un juego de verdad, desafortunadamente deber√°s mirar hacia otro lado.", "appid": "203810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034558991", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594555200.0} {"text": "good practice for a real apocalypse", "appid": "368360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127694601", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561723200.0} {"text": "Bardzo fajna gra!! POLECAM WSZYSTKIM!! <3", "appid": "508900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198274142859", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1526558400.0} {"text": "It's ok. I don't really like the new expansion but meh.", "appid": "1085660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073982622", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "–ö–ª–∞—Å—Å–Ω–∞—è –∏–≥—Ä–∞, —Å –¥—Ä—É–∑—å—è–º–∏ —Ç–æ–ø –∏–≥—Ä–∞—Ç—å", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198859018503", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588680000.0} {"text": ":* ...", "appid": "207610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198289501526", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542888000.0} {"text": "The Game is very similar to the first Layers of Fear but it has some changes like the story is better and longer than in the first game, its less scarier than the first game (i was carefull about the jump scares because of the first one) about the grafix.....the game has better grafix than the first game but at one point of the game the wole szene is grey you have really no colours. but i really liked the game and stuff and how the wole game is on a ship and how the place is changeing when you play the game more and more and i like too how the game is based on to find the character or better him/her self, after i played the game i felt better in life, i was thinking about who i really am. its very worth to buy the game and its really fun. btw sorry for my bad english spelling (the first game ---on top there lol uwu)", "appid": "1029890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198349510654", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559390400.0} {"text": "√ßok g√ºzel oyunDU ya ben √ßok oynadƒ±ƒüƒ±mdan yada ba≈üka bi≈üeyden eski tadƒ± kalmadƒ± bu efsane oyunda yava≈ü yava≈ü yava≈ü √∂l√ºyo yeni bi cs oyunu beklemeye ge√ßtim ≈üahsen.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198277104836", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515931200.0} {"text": "My favourite anime characters move in the background. Do you have any questions? :P", "appid": "431960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198140403775", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "‚úÖ Great multiplayer system: Ping can be high but the gameplay and connection is always smooth and steady. ‚úÖ Great audio and visuals: The weapons sound very nice to fire and the game looks good but not so good that it‚Äôs unplayable. ‚úÖ Incredible amounts of content especially for a multiplayer game, different armies maps and customization options. ‚úÖ Good map atmosphere will make you feel like you‚Äôre in the conflict zone without overdoing detail or extensive color grading. ‚ùå if your network is slow or the drive on which you have this game is installed getting an in-game role or class you want is very challenging. ‚ùå Team balancing is virtually nonexistent and in almost every single scenario the winning team in one round will keep the upper hand. There are a lot of things that go into making a good multiplayer first-person shooter. It is important to make sure that not only the gameplay is entertaining but that networking isn't done poorly which will have your opponents teleporting all over the place. On top of that development team has to uphold the reputation of the previous installments in this series. Certainly a daunting challenge but in my opinion, it has been done exquisitely, only a few small problems exist that are not detrimental to the experience. RS2 is a multiplayer game, its core gameplay consists of a few game modes. While they are all different they revolve around the same premise: Capture point x until victory. This type of gameplay, while simple is a lot more engaging than simple deathmatch or free-for-all game-modes, it involves strategy and team coordination which is something that simplistic shooters cannot benefit from. To achieve these goals you work in a common way of organizing players in semi-realistic shooter games: Squads. All the players are divided into 6 man squads which then all answer to the game commander. An advantage this game has over others with similar structures is that, while it‚Äôs very useful, using your microphone to play is not required nor will anyone tell you to do so. A design step various games with similar core components take is to make sure you understand as little of what is going on as possible, this is done by not showing important or useful HUD (Heads-up-display) elements or by making them about as hard to use as Linux. RS2, however, doesn‚Äôt do this and gives you all the information you could want making the game not only useful to play but pretty when you need to, a lot of information can be hidden by a single button press. The visuals have gotten quite an upgrade since 2013 luckily however they have not overdone it like some other newer titles like ‚ÄúHell let Loose‚Äù or ‚ÄúPost Scriptum‚Äù have done where your PC needs to have quite decent specs to begin with to make it consistently playable. Instead, this game, while not as pretty as the aforementioned titles, plays very nicely and consistently. The visuals look good enough to not be bothersome and provide clarity to properly engage in gameplay. The sound design is exquisite, the weapons stay authentic to how the real-life version sounds but they feel as good to fire as a weapon from ‚ÄòCall of Duty‚Äô Firing the guns doesn‚Äôt get boring or repetitive which many other games suffer from, firing something that sounds like an auto-cannon takes a lot longer to get repetitive than a gun which sounds like a peashooter at best. I have caught myself picking certain guns more just because of the sound they make when fired, the combination with other sounds make the gunplay very enjoyable. A criticism I do have is that only your gun sounds like it packs a punch, even when standing next to an ally their gun still sounds like a box of paperclips being shaken around. Feeling the punch behind all of the guns would be better. When making a game in a historical period the history of the conflict you‚Äôre basing your game in is important. A good choice the developers made was to use history however to not be influenced by it. The maps, weapons, and vehicles follow the history but they are not limited by it. You can name quite a few historical inaccuracies for example that the Vietcong did not engage in open battle as much. However, this is not important since the focus is on producing a game that‚Äôs actually fun to play and properly works instead of one you can use to study for a history test. RS2 has 2 major problems, the first is that getting roles which only a few players can use on the team is quite difficult if you do not have it installed on a very fast hard drive or SSD. It‚Äôs a first come first serve system where the players that load the fastest can pick the roles they want before many of the other players have loaded forcing other users to take standard roles. While this works quite well for players with more higher-end PC's it ends up that with an average computer you will have to fight at the beginning of the round to get a role you want and just hope you are first, I find this to be flawed at best. The second issue is that team balancing is practically non-existent. If you join the losing team you‚Äôre going to lose the current and the next round as the teams are not auto balanced. I can understand this to an extent since you pick your team however nothing is done to give the losing team a hand so winning or losing depends on which team you pick upon joining a server which I think is relatively flawed but it‚Äôs not game-breaking. Surprisingly RS2 only costs 23 euros, that‚Äôs not a lot for such a large scale game when 30 euros would have also been an acceptable price. You‚Äôre essentially getting more bang for your buck then almost any other multiplayer shooter can offer you and the minimum requirements are quite low. So I would definitely recommend picking it up if you have the money to spend on it and well with a price this low most people do. RS2 has quite low system requirements so a vast majority of computers can run it and it will look comparable enough to higher-end systems. I was able to run on a mix of high to ultra on my computer : [GTX 1050TI OC, 16GB DDR4, I5-7600K] and I have noticed frame drops only once which was because of the server I was playing on. The multiplayer experience is great, even when your ping is high it‚Äôs hardly noticeable so only extremely high latency is a problem. Rising Storm 2 is a well-designed and well-executed game that not only provides you with a lot of playtime but with an enjoyable experience with great audio, functional visuals, and smooth multiplayer capabilities. All in all combined with a large amount of content, especially for a multiplayer game, it offers and the very low price for a game of this caliber I can do nothing but firmly recommend it. This game was provided for free by the developers.", "appid": "418460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198138290285", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "31", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1569672000.0} {"text": "Bardzo lubiƒô Hotline Miami, zar√≥wno jedynkƒô jak i dw√≥jkƒô. Fabu≈Ça i \"styl√≥wa\" na stare gry, jest jak najbardziej na plus. Co do tej ods≈Çony - oto kr√≥tka list plus√≥w i minus√≥w: +WpadajƒÖcy w ucho soundtrack, pasujƒÖcy do rozgrywki. Mog≈Çabym zaryzykowaƒá stwierdzenie, ≈ºe lepszy od tego z jedynki. +Sceneria (lokacje sƒÖ ciekawsze) -Postacie majƒÖ nowe umiejƒôtno≈õci i jest ich sporo, ale tylko niekt√≥re sƒÖ grywalne.", "appid": "274170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198255191086", "voted_up