, –¥–ª—è –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã—Ö –∏–≥—Ä—ã –Ω–µ –ø—Ä–æ—Å—Ç–æ –∏–Ω–¥—É—Å—Ç—Ä–∏—è —Ä–∞–∑–≤–ª–µ—á–µ–Ω–∏–π, –Ω–æ –∏ –µ—â—ë –≤–∏–¥ –∏—Å–∫—É—Å—Å—Ç–≤–∞.", "appid": "339190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198798152764", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520251200.0} {"text": "–ó–∞–ª–∏–ø–∞–µ—Ç", "appid": "233860", "steamid": "profiles/76561198070288531", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "Oyun tam bir Deh≈üet-√ºl vah≈üet simulasyonu...", "appid": "274170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356360171", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "XD", "appid": "227300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198442296788", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1548072000.0} {"text": "I am a fan of these types of card games and I know a great one when I see it! I am very pleased with the art, strategy, economy, and the way this game breaks the mold in an over saturated market!", "appid": "839910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044642052", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1577620800.0} {"text": "You know those time-stopping minutes as a plane nears the end of the runway, achieves lift, and then levels off? That millisecond when vertical acceleration stops and the heavier-than-air craft first attains the aspect of a weightless thing‚Ä¶ like a leaf on the wind‚Ä¶ in that moment the human heart feels the joy of the remarkable achievement that is flight. When I first entered the work world in the early eighties, the closest we could come to this experience was watching planes take off and land at the local airport during our coffee break through the office windows. Then Microsoft released Flight Sim 1.0. Much has changed since then, in the real world and in Microsoft, and in Microsoft Flight Simulator. Flight simulation has leveled up. This latest iteration of Microsoft Flight takes the game pilot from a flat earth limited map, to a full Earth globe. (Just in time, too for some of those 2020 conspiracy theorists.) Not only do you have the globe on your itinerary, but you have options for location-accurate weather, time, and traffic. With mp enabled, you can see friends who are in-game in the skies around you. You can visit real world landmarks like the Eiffel Tower, natural landforms like the Grand Canyon, and observe animal herds from bush planes. Circumnavigating the globe? Exploring Greenland or Antarctica‚Äôs Ice bases? Island hopping? Whether emulating Marco Polo or Ibn Battuta, you will likely have many ideas for world-class flights. Schiphol Amsterdam is one of my favorite airports IRL, so I have spent a bit of time arriving and departing there in game. I have also enjoyed journeys such as Charles-de-Gaulle to Gandhi International (Paris to Delhi,) New York to Patagonia, and Tokyo‚Äôs Haneda International to China‚Äôs Oriental Pearl Tower, as well as ‚ÄòSan Fran‚Äô to the ‚ÄòZahara‚Äô, and New York to Patagonia. My most recent flight was an oceanic cruise from Santiago, Chile to Queenstown, New Zealand. With the large selection of planes available at launch, the sky is no longer the limit. The in-game Earth, like its counterpart, is populated with airports where you can fully interact with ground services and control towers. (The sound is great as well.) The menu provides a hangar for viewing your planes. With a robust flight customization system and many options and settings, you can fly anywhere, to and from any airport or even the blank spaces in between. There are many options for arriving and departing airports. You have quite a bit of flexibility for choosing landing strips, or even in-air spawning. Overall, you will find yourself with a world of options. There is a full range of graphics output that you can expect, depending on your machine. Yesterday, I tried them all, just to get a good baseline, since I play the game on Ultra settings. Whether or not you will like the graphics quality is determined by which settings you use. The low-end settings are lousy tbh. While ultra is a good experience, you will not get that same quality on lower settings. So, while the game is accommodating for most players, not all will have the same experience. Processing power will still be an entrance barrier for some machines. But, the real joy is in This should be handled with care, as results will vary depending on your internet connection. I have a (crappy) rural connection that is only slightly better this year with a new provider in the area. To handle the streaming graphics option (along with Ultra settings of course) I hit live pause while in flight and go into the settings to turn on the streaming graphics. This allows the game to load it in a steady state, and the results are awesome when unpausing the game. This can then be untoggled at will. You must respect that versatility. The buttons and gauges on the control panel feel realistic. Whether using a HOTAS system or a simple gamepad, the experience is like being there yourself. The price of the game is a bit hefty, especially if adding the premium packages. So, I recommend using a throttle and stick with the game if that is an option for you. Just be aware that a simple cheap gamepad works fine too. But, if you are going to pay that much for the game, you will want to beg, borrow, or steal enough for the HOTAS too. That goes pretty much without saying. And, after over 150 hours in-game, I have to say that the realistic flight mechanics of Microsoft Flight Sim are worth every dollar or euro you will spend. : ‚Ä¢\tThe game is fully optimized for a triple-monitor setup, and looks jaw-dropping I might add. ‚Ä¢\tStable performance on my machine, great fps, no crashes ‚Ä¢\tSimulation of circumnavigation ‚Ä¢\tReal-world weather system ‚Ä¢\tRealistic stress damage to planes, and the ability to scale difficulty ‚Ä¢\tModern Smart cameras/ drone tools ‚Ä¢\tThe graphics are spectacular‚Ä¶ especially with the streaming option enabled. ‚Ä¢\tMultiple activities and scenarios simulate bush flights, landing, etc. ‚Ä¢\tThe Globe interactive mode (sandbox-like) allows for staging variety of ifr & vfr flights anywhere in the world. : ‚Ä¢\tHefty disk space usage 90+ GB. (I uninstalled games which this game made seem antiquated.) ‚Ä¢\tLoading screens are lengthy. (But, clicking the windows button gives you untemperamental access to other things on your pc while you wait.) ‚Ä¢\tFuel usage seems a bit off. ‚Ä¢\tThe AI needs some tweaking. Not sure if this is a user error, but while changing to auto pilot mid vfr flight, the AI will literally and unexplainably turn the plane around and head back to the departure point. (I guess you cannot get good help these days.) ‚Ä¢\tThe price is steep, and while community mods will be available from the game menu, expect some money to be spent there as well. ‚Ä¢\tThe save system appears problematic. While it does save, many options are lost when reopening, and save state is not quite accurate. I suspect saving also disables some achievements, or causes them to not be recognized. ‚Ä¢\tAt some point the weather change options will vanish from the menu bar. To retain the ability to change the weather throughout, I keep the options window open and do not save or exit game until flight finished. ‚Ä¢\tMore VFR mapping options are needed, such as the ability to add pins to the map. ‚Ä¢\tMore detail and zooming out in the map ‚Ä¢\tAI Improvements ‚Ä¢\tWhile some data is provided from log, more would be better. (Flights are only listed by month & year, for instance. Date not listed.) Alternatively, there are online options like Simbrief for planning and logging flights. It is pure simulation at its best, and with the full globe navigation possibilities, I feel like the world is truly under my plane, and the wind beneath my wings. I loved it so much at launch that I deleted all things flight from my wishlist and pc. This tops everything else with its state-of-the-art imagery and real-Earth data.", "appid": "1250410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198154425859", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "29", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598529600.0} {"text": "Thanks to this game i finally became a human. 10/10 would nuke Detroit again", "appid": "1222140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075555960", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592654400.0} {"text": "I will write a review after my survival mission", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066447273", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574769600.0} {"text": "Very nice game", "appid": "495890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198193077137", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1488196800.0} {"text": "Meh", "appid": "211500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198344634242", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561982400.0} {"text": "Noice", "appid": "656210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116284533", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600603200.0} {"text": "PRESENTACION DE VIDEO JUEGOS INTERACTIVA: Por jugadores para jugadores ! Realmente que puedo decir? es un evento interactivo, o sea un juego de un evento que presenta juegos o la cartilla de juegos que estan por venir. Podes mirar trailers ver los detalles y modelos de algunas cosas en los juegos, realmente me encuentro muy emocionado y se pueden hacer muchas cosas, hay muchos detalles y cosas que se pueden mirar e interactuar. No se trata de si el juego es bueno o malo, si no de que esto fue echo para nosotros ! Para hacernos vivir un evento de video juegos aunque no se pueda hacer por cuestiones de publico conocimiento o no podamos ir nosotros. RECOMIENDO POR QUE CREO QUE CADA UNO DEBERIA DE EXPLORARLO A SU MODO. Gente UN APLAUSO A ESTA EMPRESA LA VERDAD HACER UN EVENTO EN UN JUEGO ES ALGO INCREIBLE. Alerta de spoiler !!! 100/10 Les dejo un directo que hice sobre esta genialidad echa video juego !", "appid": "1283220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198239865012", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594555200.0} {"text": "(y) :)", "appid": "391720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198151965709", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529582400.0} {"text": "One of the best open world survival craft/horror games I've played. Enemy AI is super advanced with unpredictable behaviour, the story is intriguing and makes you eager to solve its mysteries, crafting/building is straightforward and accessible to new players; though beware, on certain terrain it can become a little glitchy. There's tons to discover and explore, and it's definitely one I'll be coming back to replay.", "appid": "242760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198089436728", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599998400.0} {"text": "Great game", "appid": "42670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198098168024", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591185600.0} {"text": "+ S√ºrekli indirim oluyor. + Grafikler iyi. + Optimizasyon sorunu yok. + P2W deƒüil. + Troll ve k√ºf√ºr eden insan sayƒ±sƒ± az (hi√ß g√∂rmedim). - Bazƒ± g√∂revler √ßok uzun s√ºr√ºyor ve sƒ±kmaya ba≈ülƒ±yor. - Bazƒ± e≈üyalarƒ± Craftlemek i√ßin gereken e≈üyalarƒ± bulmak zor. - Yapay zeka geli≈ütirilmeli.", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198292670314", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1504440000.0} {"text": "A Wonderful game! Unique world