"votes_up": "953", "votes_funny": "115", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1435492800.0} {"text": "this the game is amazing it combines great graphics with a storyline that puls u in once u start playing u just can not stop. I often find that when i start a game i cant finish because im easily board how ever this is one of those rare games that enthralls me until the end definitely worth playing over and over again.", "appid": "17460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198024354933", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1357128000.0} {"text": "A fun game with lots of replay value. You'll spend hours unlocking all the characters, traits, items, and super abilities. Then you can create custom characters made out of everything you unlocked. The game has you travel through a city eventually reaching the Mayor's location and then you have multiple ways to proceed. I just played through as the zombie character. I was supposed to kill and zombify everyone. Instead I was elected into the position of mayor by the voters I had won over when traveling through the city. This required saving up a lot of money from like selling bats and knives and using the money to remove traits that made my zombie unable to speak and one that made people either flee in terror or attack me when seeing me. So I was a friendly zombie. Though of course killing and zombifying everyone would have been the easier option. This game is a lot of fun. There's some grind but you do it just by playing the game. Unlocking traits and items require chicken nuggets which you get my leveling up as you travel through the levels. You just do a run through the city and you get several nuggets just by playing. I highly recommend this game.", "appid": "512900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008929643", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1562673600.0} {"text": "Its like CS:GO", "appid": "222880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056951289", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "11", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589025600.0} {"text": "Dear Sick Chicken Studios, I absolutely loved this love letter of a game. Please make more games, and give me review keys to sing your praises. Everyone, this is a short but extremely sweet game to those who are lovers of science fiction, fantasy, the 80's, the 90's, LucasArts, and Sierra. To get even more specific would be spoiling the fun. Let's get to the particulars. For a pixelated game, it's looks great. The game has a serious Sierra fantasy/sci-fi look. The cut scenes are those wonderful pixelated but cartoon cut scenes that reminded me of Saturday morning cartoons. The voice acting is very good. Considering a very small group of people did so many voices is an achievement. I enjoyed listening to all the background stories, even if they had nothing to do with the main plot. There were many laugh out loud moments, which hasn't happened in a while for me. The dialogue is great. I took so many screenshots not just because the game looked great but that the dialogue was so funny! The soundtrack is DLC for a reason. It is very good. It covers both genres of medieval fantasy and 80's-90's techno dark fantasy very well. I fully intend on purchasing the soundtrack. Now the puzzles. Unlike Sierra and LucasArts, you won't be banging your head in trying to figure them out. The emphasis is the story. There is also an ingame journal to keep track of what you are supposed to be doing, but it is there for comic effect more than anything else. Now, the story is a complete cliche. However, when you have got a great script, great music, and wonderful characters, it doesn't matter. It is paying homage to a beloved genre. This is a game I will be buying/gifting to give my monetary support and to spread the word about this great little indie title. Sick Chicken, I look forward to what you will be doing in the future!", "appid": "872750", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006176581", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "36", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1556971200.0} {"text": "Un muy buen juego.", "appid": "10", "steamid": "profiles/76561197966014126", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561118400.0} {"text": "Das Spiel ist meiner Meinung nach, besser geeignet zum lernen, f√ºr Personen unter 18, da es in der realen welt im umgang mit waffen zu unf√§llen kommen kann. Ich empfehle es jedem der von Waffen jeglicher Art begeistert sind und mehr dar√ºber erfahren wollen.", "appid": "262410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198154037132", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1411905600.0} {"text": "The game looks like it's from the 90's but it's a funny new puzzel game. You move the boats from point A to B using Wind and the Current of the Water to move them along. The Mechanics and physics of the game is very well done. You'll have reef/sandbar in the way that you'll need to move around. So controlling a few ships at a time helps. Now I can see how the early settlers felt like in the Ocean. Like the God's were F*cking with them. Would love to see some achievements for the game.", "appid": "416080", "steamid": "profiles/76561197977083756", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1446811200.0} {"text": "Uma dl√ß de jogo, mesmo sendo antigo continua divertido!", "appid": "223710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090917393", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1491307200.0} {"text": "top", "appid": "666220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198004148486", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542888000.0} {"text": "ƒê·∫¢M B·∫¢O......chi·∫øn tranh ch∆∞a k·∫øt th√∫c", "appid": "418460", "steamid": "profiles/76561197966140447", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562241600.0} {"text": "It's a nice game :) i love the way it plays yrs gameplay modes every thing is nice BUT! we cant BHOP xD", "appid": "550650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198418538512", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1546171200.0} {"text": "good game to play if you like matching tiles games.", "appid": "567140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198032162080", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565956800.0} {"text": "good gameeeeee", "appid": "397900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120266134", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "Has some potential. Its a standard builder like Ark, Empyrion, 7 Days to die, Osiris new dawn, Conan exiles etc. Farm materials, build a hut, Snap together walls etc, this unlocks constructors and auto-miners that make this process easier. It doesn't stray much from conventions and I would argue Empyrion is better in almost every way. A few things Nomads adds over Empyrion; -Better graphics in general. -Slightly less indoor rain. -Conveyors (basically tubes that connects Constructors to containers, this adds hours of fun and complexity). -Electrical connections, every device must be manually connected with wires to a power source. -Great physics engine that lets you do funny things like frame a tree then pick it up. -The ability to just dig a hole anywhere and find resources. -I also found it very accessible and easy to understand. But in almost every other respect, Empyrion is a much better builder, has enemies, weapons, quests, multiplayer (100 player servers), Poi‚Äôs, multiple planets, multiple systems, Blueprints, etc. I would also argue Conan Exiles has better graphics and lighting with similar building (just no airships or vehicles) The game is also crippled by lack of multiplayer. I personally find this the biggest issue But, the game kept me entertained for 50 hours. I enjoyed it more than some AAA (¬£39.99) titles so it gets a thumbs up at ¬£10.", "appid": "504050", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970685560", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "63", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1527854400.0} {"text": "A huge spinoff of your regular Hack'n'Loot genre, Book of Demons is a very fun, skill driven and funny game. The thing that Drives me playing this game the most is the way the game progresses with you, as you level up the lesser enemies become weaker, but at the same time it becomes more challenging with the introduction of new mechanics and enemies. The paper like graphics reminds me of Guild of Dungeooners, but unlike that game this is way more balanced and fun. I recommender this game any day of the week.", "appid": "449960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198045598071", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545220800.0} {"text": "Gra warta polecenia :X", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198281892726", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1517400000.0} {"text": "not bad", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198342563765", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "who else reviewed the game just for the achievement? lmao", "appid": "322170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198382782636", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530360000.0} {"text": "The definitive version to get for this trilogy of remakes. Looks and plays great. PC does what consoles don't.", "appid": "731490", "steamid": "profiles/76561197971158734", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": 