ally really spaghettified and still single threaded. Dont get me wrong, the depth of DF is great, and I still play it, this mornign in fact. But I like Dorf corp as well.", "appid": "252390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084416564", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550232000.0} {"text": "resident evil 3 remake is a good remake but not as well as resident evil 2 remake. i'm an old school fan of resident evil franchise , i played the original games and it's one of my favorite franchises of all time and i enjoyed these remakes but Capcom removed lots of content from them specially this game. don't get me wrong it's a good game but for new players that want to understand the story of the classic games these remakes are a little bit confusing but other than that gameplay is very smooth like the RE2 remake , the game optimization is awesome , story is not long like the classic one but not that short like some people say , overall playtime depends on how you play the game , if you know how to play a resident evil game your playtime will be over 7-8 hours for sure but if you don't like searching every corner for items and just want to complete the game your playtime will be under 5-4 hours. overall if you are an old fan of this franchise this is a hell of a ride for you and if you are the new member to the family it's gonna be a very fun experience but these are remakes and story is not exactly the same story from the original games , they added and removed lots of content so beware.", "appid": "952060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198278288461", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600689600.0} {"text": "This is an awesome game - i recommend it , awesome solo games , hard ones, and ITS FUN!", "appid": "10680", "steamid": "profiles/76561197999939426", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1324987200.0} 