access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554984000.0} {"text": "Just M O N I K A.", "appid": "698780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198237542568", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1519387200.0} {"text": "its gud", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198138841394", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "Í∞ì!Í≤ú!", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079240930", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1404302400.0} {"text": "Is this game a masterpiece? No, not yet, it is still in Early Access, but it will be one when it is finished. At least when they do not ruin anything anymore. The gameplay is already fanatstic. A hectic roguelite FPS experience in a beautiful (Ancient Egyptian inspired) Pyramid. Or Ziggurat? Crypt? Mausoleum? Whatever, you start already inside (whatever mission you choose) and have to defeat hordes of enemies intent on killing you. The rooms are not only elaborately decorated but also rather large and give you much room to maneuver, which helps avoiding all those projectiles hurled at you. So you can fight - until you die. Fans of the genre know what to expect - frantic FPS action. You take a few coins with you after death and can improve your unlocked heroes and their equipment. Before you start a run, you can select your hero, his equipment and one of the available quests. I played with m+kb (gamepad supported, but I am not sure if this is the best choice in a FPS) and had no problems on 3440x1440@100Hz. The devs plan to add more content to the game, updates are released regularly (at the time of writing). Candidate for the new roguelite FPS champion. Challenging, beautiful, smooth - as it should be.", "appid": "1159560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019466684", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "26", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_cre