 no entanto, foi a possibilidade de dirigir o batm√≥vel cm suas v√°rias armas no modo de combate e turbos de alta velocidade no modo de carro... e realmente focaram bastante nisso, durante toda a campanha e miss√µes secund√°rias o batm√≥vel vai sempre ter um papel crucial seja para resolver puzzles simples, seja para auxiliar no combate explodindo tanques inimigos e salvando a pele do Batman em emboscadas lotadas de soldados (tem at√© mesmo Bosses qe s√≥ podem ser derrotados usando o batm√≥vel). At√© certo ponto essa foi uma boa jogada, por√©m se vc√™ n√£o gostar mto de dirigir e sair atirando cm o ve√≠culo o jogo n√£o vai te agradar tanto, apesar de ter mtas partes em qe vc√™ controla o Batman normalmente, √© imposs√≠vel ficar sem usar o batm√≥vel prq√™ focaram bastante nessa nova mec√¢nica qe n√£o existia nos jogos anteriores e qe proporciona bastante liberdade para vc√™ dirigir pela cidade inteira atropelando tudo qnto √© bandido pelo caminho. Fora isso o qe surpreende mto nesse jogo s√£o os lindos gr√°ficos, super detalhados e cm uma atmosfera profunda, al√©m de conter um modo foto qe permite tirar lindas capturas de tela caso queira brincar de fot√≥grafo. J√° com rela√ß√£o a hist√≥ria, tenta ser mais complexa se comparado aos anteriores, mas ainda assim n√£o conseguiu prender tanto a aten√ß√£o, vc√™ se preocupa mais cm a jogabilidade e em se divertir derrotando os vil√µes do qe cm o enredo em si... faltou carisma nos personagens principais e a f√≥rmula de te fzer sentir dentro do jogo vista em Arkham Asylum e Arkham City.. sendo t√£o gen√©rico qnto o Arkham Origins nesse quesito, sem nada de muito marcante ou de tirar o f√¥lego. Ainda assim esse √© um √≥timo jogo para passar o tempo e mergulhar no mundo do Cavaleiro das Trevas, cm mta coisa pra fzer, mtos cen√°rios para explorar e mtos personagens famosos para rever (incluindo o Duas Caras, Espantalho, Pinguim, Gordon, Hera Venenosa, Robin, entre outros). Recomendo demais a franquia do Batman Arkham, vale mto a pena jogar todos, seguindo a ordem certa de lan√ßamento qe se inicia pelo ‚ÄúAsylum‚Äù para melhor experi√™ncia.", "appid": "208650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198375029180", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "82", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598961600.0} {"text": "nice game", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198816021224", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "This game's soundtrack is composed entirely of the percussion instrument the Wood Block. You're a woodblock dodging woodblock shaped Woodblocks. 10/10", "appid": "221640", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970418619", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1387540800.0} {"text": "Note: My hours have mostly been offline on this game. Decent, fun, fast side scroller that should appeal to fans of the genre. Not as deep a game like Jets n Guns Gold but few are. Not difficult either (bordering on easy) and easily played with KB and mouse (though I prefer this method of controls to any other). Great weapon effects, customization and mech designs keep the game interesting. 4 game modes adds to the fun as well as the replayability. Although I have not participated, I‚Äôm sure 4 player co-op is also blast. Some of the levels are simply gorgeous and you can tell the developers took a lot of time on them. Probably the strongest part of the game is the attention put to the upgrade path and skill tree. With several options and paths, you can customize your warrior to your liking. I agree with all the tags applied to this game except for bullet hell. This is NOT a bullet hell game by any stretch of the imagination. Enemy fire is sparse, slow and easy to dodge which leads me to one of the faults of the game is that it really is not hard enough. Enemies are plodding and predictable and your ship, even when not upgraded, is a bullet sponge. Characters are not funny with unnecessary presence and narration. If not included, they probably would not even be missed. You can tell there were attempts at humor which just don‚Äôt go over well. I would have liked to see some kind of heat management system. There are literally no consequences to holding down both mouse buttons throughout an entire level. Is it a good game? Yes. Is it a great game? No, not by any means. It is not without it‚Äôs flaws but overcomes these with a great fun factor, game modes, and replayability, which is very important to me as a person who puts a lot of hours into games that generally don't get a lot of hours from other people. Unfortunately, the biggest blemish against it is that it really looks like the developers spent more time on the visuals rather than focusing on the mechanics, gameplay, and story, except for the level progression, which is well done. I was a bit surprised when I used the windows key to exit the game and came back to find myself dead. I would have assumed the game would have paused but this isn‚Äôt that big of a deal, just a bit surprising. I recommend the game but with reservations. A strong candidate to pick up during sales‚Ä¶ 6/10 Fun Factor Fun powerups Good character (mech) design Weapons customization Well thought out upgrade path Sound Beautiful Scrolling landscapes/backgrounds Game Modes Too easy at times No heat management system Underwhelming enemy design Ineffective enemies Unnecessary, uninspiring, forgettable characters Predictable/repetitive level structure", "appid": "389650", "steamid": "profiles/76561197961395783", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561723200.0} {"text": "12/10 –ø—Ä–æ–ø–∞–¥–∞–Ω–∏–π –∫–æ—Ä–∞–±–ª—è –∑.—ã. –ü—Ä–æ–ø–∞–ª –∫–æ—Ä–∞–±–ª—å –Ω–∞—Ö—É–π,–≤–µ—Å—å –µ–≥–æ —ç–∫–∏–ø–∞–∂ –≤ –≤–æ–∑–¥—É—Ö–µ –ª–µ—Ç–∞–ª.", "appid": "242050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198154299239", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "19", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": fals