votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "Najlepsza czƒô≈õƒá i od groma DLC Polecam", "appid": "49520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198062368570", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "Jogo muito bom... Um estilo bem diferente para quem, como eu, curte jogos de FPS e guerra. Mas √© sensacional a busca pelo animal. Testa os sentidos da gente. Vale muito a pena jogar este jogo!!!!", "appid": "253710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198014225011", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588593600.0} {"text": "–ù–∞ —á–∞—Å–æ–≤ 15 –≤–ø–æ–ª–Ω–µ —Ö–≤–∞—Ç–∏—Ç", "appid": "555440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198117719597", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "haha heavy gun go brr", "appid": "440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198330917111", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585051200.0} {"text": "Amazing game! 9,5/10 A fresh and an essential take on the old good Tomb Raider franchise. This game definitely guarantees that you will have the best Tomb Raider experience up to now. The game has so many features and implementations that make you feel like: \"Wow, this feels so natural, why wasn't this implemented before anyway?\" Taking Tomb Raider out of her \"sexualized objectification\" and giving her character a meaning is something this game has accomplished very well. So, our new fresh main character, Lara Croft is no longer just an Indiana Jones-with boobs, and this is how everyone should see her. Whether you are an old Tomb Raider fan, who wants to see more of Lara Croft or just a newcomer who has finally decided to meet Lara Croft (actually that's even better) this game is just for you! Btw. I like how it is called just Tomb Raider, and it deserves that name because they have really re-created the Tomb Raider and Lara Croft! Thanks Square Enix and Crystal Dynamics for this amazing game! Ok here is my review of Tomb Raider: Graphics 10/10 This games graphics look amazing! I have played it on maxed settings with TressFx on and everything looks just beautiful. The details of the environment and the atmosphere are stunning and it is very immersive. When you are hiding from enemies in the forest you really feel like you are in a forest. There really isn't much to say. Also dynamic hair is evolutionary! Sound 8/10 The sound effects were nicely done and the music was wonderful, maybe the ambient sounds could be worked on as I thought that the atmosphere of being in a forest lacked a little bit but that is very personal. Also why didn't they put subtitles without hearing impaired captions? I prefer having subtitles but with this game I had to turn them off. Story 9/10 Normally I never felt like the story was good in Tomb Raider games but this time it is really good. At first I thought it was a cliche; ship crashes, enemies on the island try to kill you and your friends but the game has pulled it off very well and the story was interesting, logical and thrilling. Characters were good. But what I found lacking was the given information about the characters in the game. And also because you don't really spend much time with any of your friends, it's hard to connect with any of them emotionally. The same goes for the enemies as well. Although it might be seen as you know only the things you see/find about them during the game; for me at least it wasn't enough. Gameplay 10/10 Gameplay is really where this game shines. Everything is so smooth and fun to play with. Gunplay is great, jumping around looks and feels great, finding your way on the island right after you have escaped from your enemies is great, animations are amazing; in short everything is great! At this point I want to point out a few features I loved about the game: - Animations: Animations in the game look just amazing! Whether you are exploring the island or shooting your enemies in a fight, they look great! Also, going through little cracks or auto-crouching animation or the way Lara holds the torch, they are all beautifully executed. - Weapon Upgrade System: You no longer find your new weapons somewhere in your Mansion or hidden in the world waiting for you. You upgrade your own weapons by finding \"salvage parts\" through out the island either by finding crates or by looting enemies. You also have skills that you can progress after gaining skill points. Both systems are working very well and you never really feel like you have to grind for your next weapon. It just plays out very natural. - Books: Books or diaries you find in the game are giving a lot of information both about the story and the characters. They help you to have a connection to the story and the characters. The extra beauty of them is that you don't have to read them or even find them, they are just optional; though I really recommend reading them as they enhance the story and the lore. - Relics: Relics are well relics scattered around the island that you can find. You can then see information about them and you can find small hidden clues on the relics that helps Lara to figure out more information about the relic, that's really interesting and fun. I wish more relics had those hidden clues. Additionally the information about the relics do not feel like a wikipedia article, instead they are short and interesting and you feel like Lara has just found a relic. - Tombs: Ironically this game has one of the best implementations of tombs in a Tomb Raider game. They are hidden and awating for you to explore them. After solving little puzzles, you find treasures and earn experience points. They are good breaks from the action-pace of the game while giving you some puzzles to solve and calm down :) - Immersion: This game is the most immersive and lore-friendly game I have played ever! All the implementations, characters and the story stay true to that! - Continue playing after it ends: Yes, I hate it when an amazing game is over and it doesn't let you continue playing the game with your developed character. This game lets you do that! Furthermore most of the areas are also clear from enemies which let you explore the island freely without a worry! Also I highly recommend going back to those places to see how beautiful all the environments are. - Lara Croft: Yes, Lara Croft. The modelling, animations and the voice acting are superb! And the fact that she has 'a soul' so to speak makes it all amazing! Also smaller boobs make her look more normal, natural and more beautiful, - in my opinion they could be even smaller ;) What I wish there was but there wasn't: - More time with friendly characters: You just play most of the time alone. I understand that it was meant to be that way but I wish there were times when you could at least see Lara Croft playing with other characters. - More hunting: I just wish the game had an optional hardcore survival mode that made you drink water, hunt animals for food etc. Afterall this was a survival game, right? - Romance? Overall 9,5/10 The game is amazing, period.", "appid": "203160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044640686", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1386417600.0} {"text": "Najlepsza gra w historii", "appid": "639790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198354957664", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511870400.0} {"text": "fun", "appid": "945360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198346646702", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603800000.0} {"text": "–ù–∞–∏–≥—Ä–∞–ª —è –≤ —ç—Ç—É –∑–∞–º–µ—á–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—É—é –∏–≥—Ä—É —Å—á–∏—Ç–∞–π 100 —á–∞—Å–æ–≤. –ò–≥—Ä–∞ –∑–∞–º–µ—á–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–∞—è –Ω–æ –º–Ω–æ–≥–∏–µ –µ—ë –±–æ—è—Ç—Å—è —è–∫–æ–±—ã –∏–∑-–∑–∞ 