piece, introducing art into the Videogames' world. This game is stunning and it has wonderful graphics. This makes you addicted to the game, losing your mind somewhere in The Blind Forest. Besides, you're not only going to explore \"the ground\". You'll have adventures in the underground or even in the sky, finding different creatures and enjoying lovely landscapes. : The story is going to last a couple of hours, being full of secrets that can hardly be discovered. Finding all secrets can be a little challenging because On the other hand, this is a great way to get used with the game for a higher difficulty. As the story goes by, Ori will find new abilities allowing the player to access previously inaccessible areas. Ori and The Blind Forest have an autosave feature BUT you can save your game by simply creating Soul Links with Energy Cells. Ori can gain Ability Points to buy various upgrades, such as increasing the damage of the spirit flame. is literally making you curious of what is going to happen. Also, the story is based mostly on nature-elements which are going to bring The Blind Forest back to life. You're going to explore special \"worlds\" which are hidden (at the beginning) on the map. The accent doesn't stand only on saving the forest. Ori is determined to leave because of its \"mother's\" death, Naru. A great thing is that Ori has a little partener (Sein) which is going to be there for him all the time. Another important thing is the soundtrack. The music literally fits every part of the story, making it even more heart-touching and makes the player to be even more focused on the gameplay. :", "appid": "387290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198119475498", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498910400.0} {"text": ":]", "appid": "431960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198830257076", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595073600.0} {"text": "its okay