: false, "tstamp_created": 1585656000.0} {"text": "yes.", "appid": "782330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198152907574", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584705600.0} {"text": "TIMES'S TICKING!", "appid": "444090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198042234823", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1476100800.0} {"text": "Very Nice", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198827800043", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594468800.0} {"text": "tres bon jeux", "appid": "787860", "steamid": "profiles/76561198141800895", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1546430400.0} {"text": "This game is one of those games where you could sit in your chair all day and not get up up unless it's for food or the bathroom. It's a very entertaining game to keep you going and it can teach how to survive in a way. Not exactly, but bits and peices. Despite the fact that it is VERY laggy, it was worth playing even though it's free. I definetly recommend this game, if you don't mind the lag.", "appid": "346110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198166077508", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1469880000.0} {"text": "I can recommend OutDrive for what it is. An interactive 80s style music demo, featuring a very very easy never-ending driving theme. If you are looking for an actual driving game, this is not it. The music and visuals are awesome for as long as the soundtrack lasts. A good hour and a half. By that time you will have seen the 3 possible routs several times, and you probably want to stop playing. The driving is too easy to be challenging at any point, except fot the very first time, due to \"unexpected\" controller settings.. (which you need to setup every time you play). I don't think I'll play the game again, but for me, the 2 hours I spent driving in this \"Blood Dragon\" laser world with 80s electro-synth-pop in 2017 production quality, was well worth the 50c I paid on sale.", "appid": "441870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135792443", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "30", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1509364800.0} {"text": "To be completely honest, this game is really fun and enjoyable, involves mental strategy and manipulation, Requires tons of mental facts between minimal things provided to you, if you think about it, its like the board game Clue mixed with Guess who, but all the characters are real life people, making it that much harder and more challenging, Social Deduction at its finest", "appid": "334230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198267223519", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572696000.0} {"text": "um jogo parecido com o ark convencional mas so que com mais animais e recurcursos", "appid": "593600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198134979352", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1546776000.0} {"text": "Plus -Znovu-hratelnost -N√°hodnƒõ generovan√© -Nen√°roƒçn√© Minus -Z poƒç√°tku obt√≠≈æn√© (budete furt um√≠rat)", "appid": "250900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028369512", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479902400.0} {"text": "I like cats! My cat is called Sofus!", "appid": "219640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198040403959", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1387627200.0} {"text": "Outlast is a very cinematic game that definitely includes scares. Outlast does include innapropriate things, but it is all worth it. Outlast makes you think and has puzzles with enemies that you have to sneak by. You do have to sneak a lot as you cannot fight enemies. I loved this game and love playing it. So excited for Outlast 2~!", "appid": "238320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198129300687", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1480161600.0} {"text": "You can hug zombies with chainsaw", "appid": "550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198821043498", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "14", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601812800.0} {"text": "I am really enjoying Deadfall Adventures. First-person viewpoint games give me a headache, and this one does, too, but it's not a twitch-shooting FPS, so it's not that bad. For all the complaints you may read about Deadfall Adventures, I am really enjoying it. Ultimately, this is just a fun game that puts you in the shoes of an Indiana Jones or Lara Croft-like character, though more of an adventurer and less a knowledgeable archaeologist (like Indiana) and less of a bad-ass (like Lara) ... and now that I think about it, more like a Bard (from The Bard's Tale) in that he's a confident, sarcastic guy who just goes with the flow. Lots of exploration and different environments -- check the Guides section for the guide for Collectibles, and you'll see all the places you'll go just from the YouTube video headings. Puzzles are pretty easy (so far), so the focus is on fun and exploration and environment. Fighting is likewise pretty easy, at least on the Normal setting. You don't have to be spot on with your aim. This is good for me because I suck at aiming.", "appid": "231330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052935907", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574510400.0} {"text": "Ayo red actin kinda sus", "appid": "945360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198087614637", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602936000.0} {"text": "not bad", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198271696720", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access":