∏–∑ –≥–µ—Ä–æ–µ–≤ –∏–≥—Ä—ã, \"—Å–∞–º—ã–µ —Ç—Ä—É–¥–Ω—ã–µ —Å—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è —Ä–∞–∑–≤–æ—Ä–∞—á–∏–≤–∞—é—Ç—Å—è –Ω–µ –≤ —Ä–µ–∞–ª—å–Ω–æ–º –º–∏—Ä–µ, –∞ –≤ –Ω–µ–¥—Ä–∞—Ö —Ä–∞–∑—É–º–∞\".", "appid": "414340", "steamid": "profiles/76561197980940812", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "98", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1510228800.0} {"text": "10/10 buy all episodes", "appid": "319630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198119369630", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1553515200.0} {"text": "This game is really close to my heart. I absolutely loved NFS3 Hot Pursuit as a kid, and sank countless hours into it. Had high hopes for this game, and Criterion delivered an incredible experience. It's all about exotic cars, beautiful environments and police sirens. If you think a racing game should be about putting body kits and neon lights on your car, you're gonna be disappointed. This a pure old-school NFS experience, saluting the games from a time before all that nonsense became standard in racing games. There's no story, and the only customization is choosing the color of your car. At the time of writing this, the game is almost 7 years old, but still holds up visually. The game has a licensed soundtrack, with some tracks fitting for racing....some that don't. But pretty much everyone should find at least few tracks they like. It also has a composed soundtrack for pursuits, which seem to fit the tone, but they're not as good as the work Rom Di Prisco did on NFS3. The controls are tight, and the cars all handle the same (the only real difference being top speed and off-road capabilities). It's an arcade racer, so that's to be expected. There are two career modes: Racer and cop, each with its own progression and unlocks. If I had to describe the game with one world, it would be . There are no distractions, letting you focus on satisfying your need for speed. If you liked the classic NFS games, you have to get th