 The Boss fights are badass, the dialogues are funny and the gameplay on the xbox controller is great. But get ready to spend a lot of time on this game. This is the kind of game that sucks you in for hours and you look out your window and it's nightime already. Haha. It's also great to be able to get Kirito and Asuna together. Best couple ever! The only weird part is Leafa and Sinnon being in the game. The rest is just amazing.", "appid": "638650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028934604", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585656000.0} {"text": "Muito bom o Game!!! Geralmente n gosto muito de sthelf mais esse eu gostei de mais... boa a√ß√£o, bons gr√°ficos, jogabilidade e dublagem, embora a hist√≥ria seja meio despe√ßa e meio ruim no meu gosto ainda sim da para se divertir muito... √∫nico ponto ruim mesmo √© q tem pouca gente no coop e online por enquanto mais ainda acha... recomendo muito!!", "appid": "235600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127017914", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1420113600.0} {"text": "Guns don't kill people. 47 does.", "appid": "236870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198013579069", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603281600.0} {"text": "–≠—Ç–æ –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–æ —Ö–æ—Ä–æ—à–∞—è –∏–≥—Ä–∞, –Ω–æ —Ç–∞–∫–∏ –æ–Ω–∞ –¥–æ–≤–æ–ª—å–Ω–æ —Å–ª–æ–∂–Ω–∞—è.", "appid": "979160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198391057982", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563451200.0} {"text": "goood play", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198840123639", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529064000.0} {"text": "its fun to play even if your not a furry", "appid": "778700", "steamid": "profiles/76561199052215326", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "26", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590235200.0} {"text": "Before Mass Effect, there was KOTOR. Definitely a great purchase even by todays standards.", "appid": "32370", "steamid": "profiles/76561197960270969", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1342094400.0} {"text": "kesinlikle oynamanƒ±z gereken bir oyun 10/10", "appid": "620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198047800827", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1446120000.0} {"text": "I don't quite understand why this game gets so much hate; sure it's not a \"game\" in the traditional sense and there's not much actual \"gameplay\" involved, but have people forgotten the FMV games back in 90s? If anything, FMV adventures come as close as it gets to classic old-school games because the earliest adventure games actually used to be like this. So basically, the entire game consists of full-motion videos (a.k.a. movies) with real actors in them and you're given a few choices on how to advance the plot. Let me start by pointing out that most of the wrong choices are pure comedy gold. Sure, it's cringy and weird but it's one of those cases that \"it's so bad it's almost good\". I just couldn't stop laughing after watching some of the scenes play out after making the blatant wrong choice. There's also a commentary on every choice after the scene is over which actually does a pretty decent job of explaining what you did right or wrong. Sure, you can't just learn how to score dates in real life from playing a scripted video game but that's not the point. At least, that wasn't the point for me. If you go into this expecting to become a dating guru, you'd probably be disappointed but if you treat it as a comedy, you could have a great time laughing at the situations and dialog. Another criticism that I often see is that this game provides false information about dating, that is not true at all. I mean, there aren't any super secret mystical magic words that will instantly get you any girl in this game or any other game (because no such thing exists in the real world) but it does give you some basic understanding of how things work. For example, it does tell you that you should always treat women with respect even if they're rude to you. Again, expect comedy not a tutorial... - Cute girls - Some useful dating advice - Decent production quality - Hilarious dialog, very funny - Good environment and scene variety - The only gameplay element is dialog choices - Cringy presentation - Somewhat weak acting - Rather poor soundtrack - The scenes occasionally cut off abruptly - There's a small delay before you can skip a scene 6.75/10 - Decent Super Seducer is a genuinely hilarious work of comedy which does provide some very basic and trivial dating advice. It's a FMV adventure with the only gameplay element being dialog choices. Acting has room for improvement but some of the dialog is extremely funny. Overall, I'd recommend trying it out but expect a comedy movie (not an actual dating sim).", "appid": "695920", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963259080", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549972800.0} {"text": "Well after 145+ hours I guess it's time to write a review. I picked up this game on impulse for $7.99, thought it would be fun to mess around with a friend of mine in co-op. Somehow that turned into several months of addiction. The game has decent graphics for being an indi devoloped game (it runs on unreal engine 4), music is fitting and doesn't get annoying. One thing to note is the performance can be a bit jumpy, especially in online co-op, I can see 155 fps one second and 45 the next, but overall doesn't hurt playability in my opinion. The maps are procedurally generated each time you play and are random. The enemy spawns are dictated by your item pick ups which makes for some intense sitiuations. If you're low on ammo, do you grab that box of pistol ammo and risk some high level spawns or try to melee to save ammo? After each game you are awarded currency called \"karma\". You spend karm leveling up your gear, called \"trinkets\". The addiction comes from once you start being able to hunt for demon chests which have the random high level trinkets in them that make your character very powerful. It's a bit like Diablo in that regard. The game also has a small dedicated community that are awesome to play with and willing to help new players get into the game. After a while single player gets boring but co-op is where the fun is! Just be prepared to die a lot, the game is pretty unforgiving on the higher dfifficulties. The games creator, Blue actively reads the forums and continues to take suggestions on ways to improve the game with future updates. Overall, I highly recomend Unloved if you like fast paced FPS's. Special shout out to Zod, sobored3440, Moki, Linkowiezi, JIm, Godsdoomer, and tendersurrender. Playing with those guys is a blast, don't hesistate to jump into one of their games if you see them!", "appid": "321270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198175178995", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487246400.0} {"text": "–í —Å–∞–º–æ–ª–µ—Ç–µ –¥–∞—Ç—á–∏–∫–æ–≤ –º–µ–Ω—å—à–µ", "appid": "394360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198198525715", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582804800.0} {"text": "bom jogo", "appid": "113200", "steamid": "profiles/76561198332379920", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "ok", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198291650494", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "ÎßêÌï¥Î≠êÌï¥..", "appid": "333600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198361503004", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576929600.0} {"text": "Was REALLY surprised that they were giving this away for free. I would have been more than happy to pay full price for this, it still holds up even today.", "appid": "203160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198962505943", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586088000.0} {"text": "–ù–æ—Ä–º", "appid": "555440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198931641561", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "Paradox tired of its niche status and wants to be major publisher specializing in strategies. All kind of strategies. They started with the powerful collaboration and then continue with destroying region prices on their games, like most of the big boys do. Yeah, let's make it about politics. It‚Äôs not like bullying the way through their loyal community is the new tactic for Paradox. Crazy DLC politic is the great example. But what‚Äôs more important is what let them do anything they want and it‚Äôs their card of uniqueness. You won‚Äôt find any alternatives to paradox games. But you won‚Äôt find anything like Eugene‚Äôs game either, that‚Äôs why SD might be so important to paradox. Eugene delivered solid gameplay with an uncanny similarity to their Wargame Series. The main feature is the frontline which moves with the units. Neat idea on the surface turns out to be more of a gimmick. Even so, Eugene says that‚Äôs the main part of gameplay, in the end, it didn‚Äôt really change it, but make it more noob-friendly. And this is the main theme of SD. Wargame series are well known for its total unfriendliness toward new players, the game doesn‚Äôt have a proper tutorial, it got 2000+ units you better learn (how they perform and even looks). So they decide to cut the corners. Now we got 400 units, fewer stats for each unit, \"autodeckcreator\", we lost few tactics; like helicopter rush (no one would miss it, but still helicopters gave more tactical choices), we cannot get around and strike opponent to the back (because frontline shows there we got units, except recon infantry). Tactical choices reduced to constant push-build defense line-push/retreat. Maps became wider and units became sooo much slower, which is make sense but still might be frustrating. People who wished the infantry would be the kings of the Steal division (spoiler alert it doesn‚Äôt) would find themselves disappointed. Roles didn‚Äôt switch, dynamic didn‚Äôt change drastically, artillery became more powerful than ever. Even new stress system feels just like a light touch. Paradox is‚Ä¶ that game is still semi-realistic and really complex for the newcomers, while wargame veterans will get ‚Äúless of the same‚Äù. I think I appreciate the gentle approach, no one want‚Äôs to learn everything from the scratch, but at the same time, I can‚Äôt find anything that justifies the transfer from Red Dragon to Steel Division. Surprisingly enough SD doesn‚Äôt look as good as you might expect, models look shabbier than their brothers from Wargame DLCs. But animation became smoother; infantry doesn‚Äôt slide through the hills like they used to do. Anyway, I doubt you would notice it during the game, cause all you need to see is pictograms of your units on the whole wide map. The best new thing is the circle which allows you see how much vision each point on the map will give to you units, that‚Äôs what Red Dragon surely missed. Steal division doesn‚Äôt feel like a step back, more like ‚Äúconfident mudding-through‚Äù.", "appid": "572410", "steamid": "profiles/76561197974517652", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1495454400.0} {"text": "HYPERCHARGE: Unboxed, Digital Cybercherries ekibi tarafƒ±ndan geli≈ütiren eƒülenceli odaklƒ± bir FPS oyunu. Oyunda oyuncak olarak oynuyor, diƒüer oyuncaklara kar≈üƒ± m√ºcadele veriyoruz...", "appid": "52