files/76561198009245890", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1425816000.0} {"text": "wie beklommt man die neu map", "appid": "209650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009227547", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1429531200.0} {"text": "sanƒ±rsam t√ºr√ºn√ºn lideri", "appid": "227300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198118605115", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "36", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479902400.0} {"text": "gigjghjgjg", "appid": "9480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198352250985", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498132800.0} {"text": "They are definitely on the right track here. I like the new combat system althought it needs improving. HITBOXES? WHAT ARE THOSE?! It invokes the old one with it's simplicity to learn but hard to master nature. The blocking system requires the player to be active in combat and not just swing at the enemy and hope for the best. I say keep it. The graphics need more work. Why is everything so... \"shiny\"? Why the text on the interface is so flurry? I have nothing against the music. It fits the tone and brings back memories of the first Gothic ^_^ Just one thing... make it so the music changes into a dynamic theme when the actual combat starts. It shouldn't change just because my character has his sword pulled out. Now let's talk about the writing... It needs more work. Especially for the Nameless Hero. The guy shouldn't be so chatty outside of the actual dialogues. He should be a man of action not words. Unless it's some critical info don't make him \"talk to himself\" it's pointless and annoying. \"Worst prison ever\" was one of the cringiest things I've heard this year -_- Diego sounded forced and artificial in his speeches. Like a father that explains life to his kid. Was that the intent? I don't think a guy like Diego should tre