0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1395144000.0} {"text": "Dobre pomara≈Ñczowe!", "appid": "550900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198254158653", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "Meiner Meinung eins der besten GTA Teile √ºberhaupt. Man kann Stunden lang mit der super Drive-Engine herumfahren und die Welt erkunden, oder einfach Leute anfahren.. :D Einfach klasse!", "appid": "12210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198085453616", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1482408000.0} {"text": "–ë–ï–°–¢ –í–ï–†–°–ò–Ø –ª—É—á—à–µ —á–µ–º HD –∏ —Å—Ç–∞—Ä—ã–µ –≤–µ—Ä—Å–∏–∏, —Ä–µ–∫–æ–º–µ–Ω–¥—É—é –∫ –ø–æ–∫—É–ø–∫–µ —Ç–æ–ª—å–∫–æ –µ–µ.", "appid": "227780", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996849274", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1477310400.0} {"text": "I first played Assassin‚Äôs Creed Brotherhood when I was around 11 or 12, so coming into this game again in 2020 was a huge nostalgia trip for me. Exploring Rome sent me right back to my childhood. After finally finishing the game, I remember why I loved it so much. + The story is brilliant, on par with its predecessor, and the cast of characters, old and new, hold their own and enhance the quality of the narrative. Ezio is more the wiser in this entry and is without a doubt the best character in it. The antagonists are really good as well! + The outside animus story is really good as well. Being able to explore Monteriggioni in modern day as well as having conversations with the characters was one of my main childhood memories of this game. Still holds up. + The combat feels a lot more fast paced in comparison to previous entries. You can now chain executions after completing a successful execution. This can also be done with a successful counter. Whilst doing this you have to constantly be aware of your surroundings and be aware of interruptions. It‚Äôs quite entertaining, and it looks really cool. + The crossbow is a brilliant addition to the game. I normally despise crossbows in video games, but Brotherhood got it perfectly. It‚Äôs easy to use and it‚Äôs incredibly effective. + The ability to call in other assassins to support in combat is one of the best aspects of this game, and it‚Äôs what makes it stand out in the franchise. As you progress, the Brotherhood becomes more and more established as new recruits are added. You can also send them on missions across Europe which level them up and provide you with items and money. + The climbing hasn‚Äôt seen much changes, but there are a couple of minor changes and additions that have been made. It‚Äôs now easier to jump onto ledges that are parallel to you, and the lifts make it easier for vertical traversing. Other than that, it‚Äôs still good. + There is a very noticeable visual upgrade from the previous entry, especially in the character models. There‚Äôs much more detail and focus. The level design is fantastic as always. You spend the majority of the game in Rome, and it is a brilliant place to explore. + As well as the main story, there are other things you can do. AC: Brotherhood is the first entry in the series to have proper distinct side quests. They‚Äôre nothing major, but they‚Äôre unique. There are also other story lines to follow such as The Followers of Romulus and learning about Ezio‚Äôs ex-lover, all of which are very interesting. + Once again, the music for this game is fantastic. Iconic tracks from AC 2 have returned, along with some iconic new tracks that help immerse you into the world. Jesper Kyd is seriously fantastic. - The ending. Assassin‚Äôs Creed isn‚Äôt really known for having really good endings, and this game is no exception. My problem with it is that it didn‚Äôt make much sense to me. It felt way too abrupt. My opinion of this might change as I continue my playthrough of the franchise, but at the moment, I‚Äôm just confused. - The bugs. Oh, the wonderful bugs. There aren‚Äôt loads, but there are a few. Climbing can be a nightmare sometimes. You‚Äôll want to do one thing, but Ezio will want to do another, so there will be times where you‚Äôll have to find a compromise. There‚Äôs also a game breaking bug near the end where a crucial cutscene won‚Äôt play. Oddly enough, this was fixed by turning V-Sync on. Don‚Äôt ask how‚Ä¶ - The air tackle mechanic is stupid and pointless. There were so many times where I wanted to hang off a ledge, but instead Ezio would just jump on top of somebody, forcing me to climb again. It does more harm than good. Assassin‚Äôs Creed Brotherhood was the second game I played in the AC franchise, the first being Revelations. It is without a doubt, one of the best games the franchise has to offer. It is the definitive Assassin‚Äôs Creed experience in my opinion. Being able to establish and manage the brotherhood of assassins only reinforces it. I‚Äôve seen people call Brotherhood ‚Äúan expansion to AC2‚Äù or just simply ‚Äúa big DLC‚Äù, and I couldn‚Äôt disagree with this statement more. There is more content in Brotherhood, and the mechanics are more refined. I honestly think it‚Äôs slightly better than its predecessor. Only slightly. Although I was taken off guard by the abruptness of the ending, the past games so far have had abrupt endings, so I can‚Äôt say I was hugely annoyed by it. At the end of the day, questions usually get answered. Same thing goes for the bugs. They‚Äôre there, but they are manageable. At the moment, Brotherhood stands as my favourite in the franchise. This may change as I replay Revelations, but Brotherhood is something special. It‚Äôs less about a character‚Äôs journey, and more about something greater. The staple of the franchise. The Brotherhood itself.", "appid": "48190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091255120", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "66", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597579200.0} {"text": "A visually stunning, beautifully made short game that makes you feel cheerful, sad, and at some points even slightly spooked all within its short play time. Amazing writing with some of the best voice acting and dialogue I've ever heard in a game. Highly recommend if and when it's on sale.", "appid": "383870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198170707822", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593604800.0} {"text": "+ in my opinion, the best competitive FPS. Very great mechanics, no magic/colorful ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. I'd say one of the most tactical/strategic games on a higher skill level out there. - online community is overwhelmed with cheaters / can't play the game without a 3rd party league (e.G. faceit/esea) / \"OVERPATCHED\" -> its far away from the original CS:GO (2014-15), the way weapons work changed heavily as well as their importance ingame. The way to approach a fight kinda sucks these days (you just see patches of the shoulder and die) or people run and shoot, so its no longer as mechanicly as it used to which is very sad. The over-all performance of this game really degenerated, even with a high end pc. Hitboxes are not the same either, its so hard to hit somebody eventho you're perfectly on his skinmodel. Most of the essential attributes which made this game so awesome, are not the same any more which is very sad. Yet still has the potential of being one of the best games ever if valve gets their ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• together", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561197974674831", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588593600.0} {"text": "i love so much bout this software !", "appid": "301610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198154131980", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562068800.0} {"text": "Although I haven't played for very long I can say the game can be fun but not right now. There is still no full customization, no teams only 1v1 and no way to remap controls. Hit boxes are pretty random there is only 1 map at the moment and it's pretty dumb that you can see where your opponent is on the map (through wall and everything). Wait for the game to be released and have some more content. At this point just a 1 hour tryout.", "appid": "1008580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198080351654", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1574856000.0} {"text": "very immersing campaign offering a wide \"walkaround\" of the Huey, with different situations and tasks to accomplish, definitely replayable sometimes missions get stuck because missing a trigger point, yet it's not a campaign flaw, I guess, rather than DCS own structure", "appid": "1141980", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963584378", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603627200.0} {"text": "tut weh", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198040711495", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "This game is amazing, and it's definitely worth the play. It'll give you around 4-8 hours worth of entertainment, and for 5.19, it's well worth a buy. The only downside to this game is the lack of content in the form of English DLC's and expansions, and the lack of anything on the workshop to prolong the game. Regardless, get it, it's good fun, if only for a short time.", "appid": "942970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198031441235", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594468800.0} {"text": "Z ca≈ÇƒÖ pewno≈õciƒÖ polecam tƒÖ grƒô, jednak nie za pe≈ÇnƒÖ cenƒô. Zwyk≈Ça przygod√≥wka point & click z ciekawƒÖ fabu≈ÇƒÖ i tw√≥rcami pr√≥bujƒÖcymi w na szczƒô≈õcie udany spos√≥b prze≈Çamaƒá czwartƒÖ ≈õcianƒô. Szata graficzna od pierwszej czƒô≈õci bardzo siƒô poprawi≈Ça poprzez dodanie bardziej szczeg√≥≈Çowych lokacji itp. Spos√≥b gry jak i podr√≥≈ºowanie po ≈õwiecie trochƒô od poprzedniczki, a mianowicie dostajemy mapƒô z lokacjami do kt√≥rych mo≈ºemy siƒô teleportowaƒá. Zagadki nie sƒÖ wybitnie trudne ale niekt√≥re wymagajƒÖ od nas pog≈Ç√≥wkowania. Ocena ko≈Ñcowa 7,5/10", "appid": "769970", "steamid": "profiles/76561198856797076", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598529600.0} {"text": "Wowser! Awesome-possum! 0/10 game. Fire soundtrack and bright plot! By the way, what the hell devs? Step 1: Life is strange original: Makes me a BI Step 2: Life is strange before the storm: Makes me a Lesbi Step 3: Life is strange 2: Makes me a natural straight-girl Okay, Dontnod Entertainment 1-0 you score! UPD: tbh the sound and bright plot (chars like Finn etc) are only pros in this game, this one is propaganda game where americans are \"bad\" and mexicans are \"good\". In reality it's the other way around. I wish Deck Nine made this game.. DONTNOD Entertainment is typical sh11ty - left wing french company. LIS 1 & BTS > LIS 2! 4 out 10 my final score. LIS 1 4EVER!", "appid": "532210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198835107724", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "81", "votes_funny": "47", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557662400.0} {"text": "The classic Bioshock huh? Alright The game plays very smoothly, with responsive controls. The weapons feel very good to use, with the exception of the Chemical Thrower and grenade Launcher I'd say. Plasmids, which you can think of like \"magic\", works perfeclty and each one of them has an application to aid you in battle, my favourite being the \"Electro Bolt\" My olny problem with this category, I'd say it's the movement speed, feels like I'm walking when i'm running and feels like I'm crawling when walking. Spent 99% of the game in \"running\". The level design is one strong point here, with very beautiful landscape outside of the playable area that helps with the immersion for being in an Underwater city The maps make a good work in leading you the right way, but I got lost when exploring, even though it was pretty easy to find myself again. The story starts off kinda slow, but you do notice it will get more interesting right off the start The characters are all remarkable, from the ones you only hear in Recordings and the ones that talk directly to you. Everything goes together very well and the logs helps you get an understanding of what's going on in there and why is hell. In my opinion, the story feels like rushed in the final 2 levels or so, but the final boss battle was very good in exchange for it. There are two endings, I manage to get the good ending, what are you going for? Overall I'd say the game is still worth playing after all this time, it took me 15 hours to beat it, there isn't much to it aside from the story mode, I'd definetely recommend playing it, but wait a discount", "appid": "7670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198207017241", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579262400.0} {"text": "–í –¥–∞–ª–µ–∫–æ–º—É 2014 —è –±—É–≤ —Ä–∞–¥–∏–π –¥–∞–Ω—ñ–π –ø–æ–∫—É–ø—Ü—ñ. –î–∞–≤—à–∏ 30 (!) –±–∞–∫—Å—ñ–≤ –∑–∞ –∞–ª—å—Ñ—É –º–∞–≤ –Ω–∞–¥—ñ—é, —â–æ –æ—Å—å-–æ—Å—å —ó—ó –¥–æ–ø–∏–ª—è—é—Ç—å, –≤—ñ–¥—à–ª—ñ—Ñ—É—é—Ç—å. –ê–≥–∞ –∞–≥–∞. –ù–∞–∫–æ—Å–∏–ª–∏ –±–∞–±–ª–∞ –∑ –æ–±—ñ—Ü—è–Ω–æ–∫ —ñ –≤–¥–∞—é—Ç—å –±—É—Ä—Ö–ª–∏–≤—É —Ä–æ–±–æ—Ç—É –Ω–∞–¥ –Ω–µ—é. –û–¥–∏–Ω –±–∞–≥ –ø–æ—Ñ—ñ–∫—Å–∏–ª–∏, 2 –≤–∏–ª—ñ–∑–ª–æ, –∫–æ—Ä–æ—Ç—à–µ –∫–∞–∂—É—á–∏ - –Ω–∞—Å –∫–∏–Ω—É–ª–∏, —è–∫ –≤ —Ç—ñ–π –ø—ñ—Å–µ–Ω—Ü—ñ. –¢–∞–∫–µ –≤—ñ–¥—á—É—Ç—Ç—è, —â–æ —Ü—é –≥—Ä—É –ø–∏–ª—è–ª–∏ –Ω–∞—à—ñ –ø–æ–ª—ñ—Ç–∏–∫–∏ :D –ü—Ä–æ–π—à–ª–æ 4 —Ä–æ–∫–∏. –ë–∞–≥–∞—Ç–æ —Ö—Ç–æ –≤–∂–µ –æ–¥—Ä—É–∂–∏–≤—Å—è, —Ä–æ–∑–ª—É—á–∏–≤—Å—è —ñ –ø–æ–º–µ—Ä, –∞ —Ü—è –π–æ–±–∞–Ω–∞ —Ö—É–π–Ω—è —è–∫ –±—É–ª–∞ –≤ —Ä–∞–Ω–Ω—å–æ–º—É –¥–æ—Å—Ç—É–ø—ñ —Ç–∞–∫ —ñ –∑–∞–ª–∏—à–∏–ª–∞—Å—å. –ú—É–¥—Ä–∏–π –≤—á–∏—Ç—å—Å—è –Ω–∞ —á—É–∂–∏—Ö –ø–æ–º–∏–ª–∫–∞—Ö, –∞ –¥—É—Ä–µ–Ω—å –Ω–