", "steamid": "profiles/76561198040208340", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511438400.0} {"text": "Kane & Lynch 2: Dog Days is a sequel to the successful, though not perfect, shooter Kane & Lynch: Dead Men. She showed in full parade that there is no need to put a handsome positive in the lead role, because neither Kane nor Lynch are exactly handsome and not exemplary guys at all. You might think that after the first episode, our criminal duo Kane and Lynch will take a break from drug dealers, guns and criminals. Unfortunately, this did not happen and the very big crazy Lynch, around whom the whole story of the second part revolves, will go to Shanghai. We will soon find out that he did not come only on holiday when he plans a very risky event, in which, of course, there is money, drugs, weapons and local mobsters. Before the event, he had a good fight with his colleague Kan, but when he promises to help him a few million, from which he could sponsor his daughter, Kane nods and he is already flying to Shanghai too. However, Lynch is not exactly the type to think about, so his planned event has several large and small cracks, which will immediately manifest themselves. Thanks to this, our duo will become game not only for mobsters, but also for the local police. As you may already know, the main prime here will be the shootouts, which will take place in a total of ten levels. Unfortunately, this is not a large number, and believe me, the game took us about four hours of game time to complete the first game. This is a shame for the game like thunder. As for the gameplay itself, Kane & Lynch 2: Dog Days is a classic action shooter that takes inspiration from American action movies. Quite simply. You go through all 10 levels, but they are as linear as possible, with crowds of armed enemies. Your only task is to get through them at the end. At first, only similar bastards will keep you company, but later the police and in the second half of the game also special units that have bulletproof vests, but also better submachine guns. In order for you to succeed in the shootouts, the developers have added to the game even so popular today, which is really successful in the second part of Kane & Lynch. Your end is also very interesting. If you refuse to cover and you simply want to shoot the level, after a few hits, the character you control goes to the ground, while he has the opportunity to shoot everything from the ground, or quickly get up and run to safety. Anyway, if you don't get out of range of the bullets, you'll end up in a pool of blood soon. Thanks to the considerable linearity and constant skirmishes, the game has a really fast pace and you will really relax when you finish the game. Even thanks to the brutal pace, the game will definitely not let you go. Kane & Lynch 2: Dog Days is a hilarious action game that includes crazy shootouts full of violence and foul language. But in order to give a better mark, the game would have to be a bit longer, because less than four hours for the main campaign, that's a hell of a lot. Also, the game contains a fun Arcade mode and even the multiplayer is definitely not bad. But now the answer to the question of whether to buy or not. If you fell in love with the first part or you like purebred shooters, then definitely buy it. I personally rate the game 5/10 Positive + Literally a rough game + Cooperation mode + Multiplayer Negative - Extremely short campaign - Too stereotypical - A simple story", "appid": "28000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041153724", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601121600.0} {"text": "Press F and Let`s play", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198965902710", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1568203200.0} {"text": "N√£o vou mentir. O jogo √© bom. Pulei todo o hype e todos os \"first day review\" e joguei. Me diverti demais, ent√£o recomendo. Embora seja muito caro pelo que oferece", "appid": "314710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079289820", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591444800.0} {"text": "Jogo muito bom, recomendo!", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198133277825", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493208000.0} {"text": "Bu oyun √ßok g√ºzel ama ke≈üke valve bey bi √ß√∂z√ºm bulsa hilelere", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198860657124", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1542628800.0} {"text": "this is the excitement with the amazing graphics and battle people a snapshot of how i write multiplayer i can write that you don't miss a game like this there are a few sections that all of them, the arena is going in there, you can improve your own character by cutting down on the enemy, whatever it be armor or a sword is upgrade completely up to you this game is when you should get a discount are you seen rome war", "appid": "302510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198180670294", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1491825600.0} {"text": "Awesome Game. Buy it now if you can accept that things aren't going to be perfect. If not i suggest waiting until the full release.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198046418187", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1387281600.0} {"text": "<3 LOVE THIS GAME <3", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198313981983", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511006400.0} {"text": "When Metal Gear Survive was first revealed in 2016 I was left with mixed feelings. While I was never onboard the hate train I was not very excited either. Then once the first footage of gameplay was revealed the month after it was starting to look more appealing to me. At E3 2017 private showcasings were held for the upcoming spinoff and Konami invited me to attend the event. Once I was able to try out the game for myself I had a really good time with it and knew for sure I would be playing it at release. Much like The Phantom Pain Metal Gear Survive's main focus is on gameplay rather than story. The story content is a bit short and is heavily consisted towards the beginning and towards the end. The game begins with multiple cutscenes at the MSF motherbase where you also create your character between scenes. After creating your character it shows you how you end up getting sent through a wormhole to another dimension. You must use the resources you find on missions to survive in the harsh environment and find your way back home. Survive consists of many good plot twists while maintaining the Metal Gear feel. Building off of MGSV's core gameplay Metal Gear Survive adds many new mechanics and assets. Added assets include a variety of melee weapons, gear, apparel, and gadgets. In this game you must gather food and water to survive which can be tedious in the beginning of the game. However as you progress through the story it gets easier and easier as you build up your base. Eventually you will reach the point where you never have to hunt for food and water ever again. While the maps reuse assets such as textures and some buildings it still felt like a new environment to explore. On a final note stealth IS relevant in this game. If you sneak behind Detonators to kill them you get more materials and it prevents Bombers from blowing up and causing potential damage to nearby fortifications. I found microtransactions in Metal Gear Survive to be less intrusive than TPP's. The premium currency is called SV coins which are very similar to MB coins in TPP and can be acquired for free from the daily reward. You can use SV coins to buy temporary resource boosters, extra loadout slots, extra emotes, additional storehouse storage, and additional avatar slots. When you buy an avatar slot your resources such as weapons and materials are shared between your characters. If you were to delete your original character your resources would also still remain from your previous character which makes these avatar slots not truly save slots. In TPP you were locked out of the top equipment if you didn't buy extra FOBs with MB coins which is something Survive does NOT do. In Survive you can acquire all the top gear without using any SV coins at all. Metal Gear Survive is far from being the best Metal Gear game but I think it's the most enjoyable Metal Gear spinoff and offers more content than Metal Gear Rising ever did. I recommend this game to those who are craving for more Metal Gear content and looking to have a good time with friends. There is even still more to look forward to with a new CO-OP mode arriving in an update this month.", "appid": "543900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198057945441", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "113", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1520078400.0} {"text": "–ò–≥—Ä–∞–ª –≤ –ø–µ—Ä–≤—É—é —á–∞—Å—Ç—å,–ø–æ–Ω—Ä–∞–≤–∏–ª–æ—Å—å.–ü–æ –¥–µ–º–∫–µ –Ω–µ–ª—å–∑—è –º–Ω–æ–≥–æ–≥–æ —Å—É–¥–∏—Ç—å,–Ω–æ,—Å—É–¥—è –ø–æ –Ω–µ–π,–≤ –∏–≥—Ä–µ –µ—â–µ –±–æ–ª—å—à–µ –≤–∑–∞–∏–º–æ–¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏—è —Å –æ–∫—Ä—É–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ–º,—á–µ—Ä–Ω—ã–π —é–º–æ—Ä –Ω–∞ –µ—â–µ –±–æ–ª–µ–µ –≤—ã—Å–æ–∫–æ–º —É—Ä–æ–≤–Ω–µ) –°—Ç–µ–ª—Å –æ—Å—Ç–∞–ª—Å—è –Ω–∞ —Ç–æ–º –∂–µ –≤—ã—Å–æ–∫–æ–º —É—Ä–æ–≤–Ω–µ,–∫–∞–∫ –∏ –≤ –ø—Ä–æ—à–ª–æ–π —á–∞—Å—Ç–∏.–ò–ò –Ω–µ–º–Ω–æ–≥–æ —Ç—É–ø–æ–≤–∞—Ç—ã–µ,–º–æ–≥—É—Ç –≤–∞—Å –Ω–µ —É–≤–∏–¥–µ—Ç—å,–≤ –º–µ—Ç—Ä–µ –æ—Ç —Å–µ–±—è. –°–ø–æ–∫–æ–π–Ω–æ –ø–æ–π–¥–µ—Ç –Ω–∞ –∫–æ–º–ø–∞—Ö 5-–ª–µ—Ç–Ω–µ–π –¥–∞–≤–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏. –ò–∑ –º–∏–Ω—É—Å–æ–≤,—Ç–∞–∫ —ç—Ç–æ —Ü–µ–Ω–∞-2–∫ –ø–ª–∞—Ç–∏—Ç—å –º–Ω–æ–≥–æ–≤–∞-—Ç–æ,–±—Ä–∞—Ç—å –¢–û–õ–¨–ö–û –Ω–∞ —Ä–∞—Å–ø—Ä–æ–¥–∞–∂–∞—Ö,–∫ —Ç–æ–º—É –∂–µ,–∫–∞–∫ —Ä–∞–∑ —Å–µ–π—á–∞—Å —Å–∫–∏–¥–æ—á–∫–∞ 50 % .", "ap