D TOO MANY SYLLABLES! F*CK OFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF!!!", "appid": "1238820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198276871369", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "129", "votes_funny": "23", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599739200.0} {"text": "its good but not woth its price", "appid": "629760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198279349084", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573387200.0} {"text": "i only played this for 1.3hours to see if it would get to a good part and it never did and i heard it very bugged out its 90% off and and i still dont think i will keep it", "appid": "464340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198203238402", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605614400.0} {"text": "Whilst having an ambitious story, the uncoordinated art style and generally predictable characters in 'By Moonlight' tainted the experience. You're given the illusion of choice whilst going through a linear story line, with an unsatisfying ending. The story attempts to present endearing characters, though is unable to present them as anything other than two dimensional . The choice system implemented results in no real consequence, and the 'bad endings' often took an odd thematic turn, leaving an unpleasant taste. However, the game shines with clever dialogue and an exciting premise, albeit dissapointingly never fully developed. When dedicated, the game presents a playful and fun vibe, genuinely enjoyable, though this is diluted through a weak story line and somewhat lazy art style. Considerable care has been clearly invested, yet this ultimately fails to pay off as a worthwhile experience.", "appid": "1014880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198281011881", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1551614400.0} {"text": "meh", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198432024223", "voted_up": false, "votes_up":