amp_created": 1545480000.0} {"text": "–ñ–µ–ª–∞—é –≤–∞–º –≤—Å–µ–≥–æ –ø–ª–æ—Ö–æ–≥–æ ............/¬¥¬Ø/)..........................................(\\¬Ø`\\ .........../....//............................................\\\\...\\ ........../....//..............................................\\\\ ..\\ ...../¬¥¬Ø/..../¬¥¬Ø\\........................................./¬Ø`\\....\\¬Ø`\\ .././.. /..../..../. |_....DEEP SILVER.._.|..\\....\\....\\....\\.\\ (.(....(....(..../.) ..)....EPIC STORE...(...(.\\....).....)....).) .\\................\\/.../..............................\\...\\/.............../ ..\\.................../................................\\................../ ...\\.................(.................................)................", "appid": "287390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198257105042", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549972800.0} {"text": "Noooooo, I wanted to play God Simulator, not GOAT simulator :(", "appid": "265930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198017308898", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1488110400.0} {"text": "There are only a handful of maps. This is only just the locations you pick with their day and night cycles, but the actual tactical maps you‚Äôre on. It looks sort of detailed, but when you look past the first few layers of the tactical maps you‚Äôll see the green non-detailed background and other blocky items. I understand that is nit-picking, but if you‚Äôre going to add a few maps then that should‚Äôve never happened. The sounds were a bit off at times. Some of the guns sounded as if they were being fired out of a muzzled tin can and at times when you put the volume down the lightning would still be louder than rest of the game. Hey, I know its lightning and thunder, but shooting a gun near you ears also has that similar deafening sound. The progression of RPG elements is a nice touch, but every character lacks detail about who they are. I‚Äôm a police officer, or I‚Äôm a nurse. Okay? Were you the clerk, did you specialize in a certain field, were you the janitor? I mean, a lot of the characters lack a full fledge background, story, or more information about who they are. You try to see it based on the very limited dialogue, but compared to other RPGs, this is very concerning when you jump into a genre that is more story and knowledge than anything else. The survival aspect of the game was done well enough. You gather supplies by searching the same zones over and over and over again. You‚Äôll get anything from cloth, to food, to gun components. You‚Äôll take those back to your camp and make med-kits, guns, or clothing to help you further down the line. You‚Äôll also have access to a shop to sell some of your findings to make a killing in materials (currency). What I found the hardest of anything was the lack of tools and most of it was through the quests you‚Äôd get (you get some via exploration as well ‚Äì if RNG doesn‚Äôt hate you). The RPG attributes and skills were an iffy one with me. You‚Äôd get to choose between picking points into weapons/combat oriented or skills that benefit the camp. I found this to my dislike because it should have been separate. So everything I learned is either or? I see the point of it to prolong the ‚Äòsurvival‚Äô bit of it, but other survival games did fine as well keep it separate. Some of said skills help with guarding from raiders/zombies attacking in the night, hunting, or building items to be used. With the attributes none of it really added up either. I had someone who is level 3 Cunning and they still get hit like they‚Äôre a wet paper bag. So, if block is at 20 is that 20% to block, 20 less damage? I mean, a lot of the stats in here were not informative enough to know what is going on stat wise. There were no clear instructions on what or how it was used while in combat but did become more useful for jobs around the camp. I also didn‚Äôt like how far the gaps were between certain skills were to make a change. So what does selection 16, 18 (stat) do compared to selection 20 with a higher chance of block and level 3 guard selection? No idea, it was never explained. That‚Äôs a big issue when you add RPG elements into a game that one must detail what they do here, there, and up against enemies. Raises the chance of what? That is throughout a lot of this game. What chances is cunning at the third selection when guarding and with 6 block? No idea. Again, 6% chance of blocking, less damage, how does this affect the enemies in turn? This is where the combat becomes disappointing. Why is this particular zombie ineffective at everything! Melee, long range, traps. WHY is he ineffective? I look at the zombie and there is no stats, no buffs, no debuffs. Just in-effect-ive! Why did another zombie block all three of my party members attack with the same information? Is this vagrant a tank when he‚Äôs one of the first zombies you see? Is he even a tank? Do they have a random hidden stat that no one knows? And this is why stats are important in RPGs because so you can know how to counter things, but unfortunately there is so much RNG in here it wouldn‚Äôt make a difference. From blocking all your gunshots, to running low on AP. Even AP is odd at times. Wait for a round. The round you‚Äôre in against enemies, or when you start a new round? Does it restart if you go to the next zone? I mean, we‚Äôre missing out on a lot of the combat information and the descriptions are vague about it all. Now what pushed me over to deleting this game? When you fail you start completely over. Okay, I get that because it‚Äôs a survival game, but we‚Äôll help you cheat in the next round ‚Äì basically you‚Äôll get perks so your guy doesn‚Äôt suck so much next round. But now you do everything over again, with the same repetitiveness, storyline, dialogue, limited events, same pictures; that you‚Äôve seen all in the first few hours again ‚Äì No. Also, the lack of character customization is a drag too. Why do I have to play this Jack guy? Yes, I can rename him, but playing Jack is boring. What if I want to spice up my own character? What if a female wants to play a female character? Those options don‚Äôt exist and with RPGs, you have the option on how you want to look (even if limited) and this was rather forced. I guess there were also romance options too, but I didn‚Äôt see this in the game. Between the lack of details, to RNG heavy, to lack of information on stats, boring combat, and limited RPG elements; I found this game to be boring and extremely repetitive. Now, since it‚Äôs an Indie Dev and I support such small companies and teams, I‚Äôll say it‚Äôs a game worth its price, but I cannot continue on. If this game is something down your alley and want to try out a game knowing there are flaws, then I think you might enjoy this title.", "appid": "363930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003026615", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592222400.0} {"text": "The game is a good foundation but it still has a few major bugs and the interface needs improvment, for example I lost all troops in transit wich cost me ~5k reinforcment and a complete front didn't have any troops now. There is also a bug where you can't select anything. I wil come back to the game when the major bugs are patched out.", "appid": "603850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084595689", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543060800.0} {"text": "its literally just a worse nether... Its not worth the 9 dollars if you already own nether...", "appid": "1010270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198202196316", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557921600.0} {"text": "–°—ã–Ω —Å–æ–±–∞—á—å–µ–≥–æ –¥–µ—Ä—å–º–∞ —Å–æ–∑–¥–∞–ª —ç—Ç—É –∏–≥—Ä—É, –Ω–µ –≤–∏–¥–µ–ª —Ö—É–∂–µ –æ–ø—