en kann und wiederholt diese bis zum erbrechen. Die Ern√ºchterung, wenn man dann feststellt, dass man um alle Skills zu erreichen noch 100x iwelche Level rennen muss ist argh gro√ü. Zudem man erst am Ende fest stellt, dass man wenigstens 2 Errungenschaften nicht erreichen kann. Das Spiel k√∂nnte richtig gut sein, leider nur k√∂nnte.. - zu wenig Abwechslung in den Leveln - zu wenig Abwechslung bei den Gegner - ab Level 30 einfach nur noch sinnfreies gegrinde, Game wurde k√ºnstlich in die L√§nge gezogen - 100% nicht m√∂glich, den Entwickler st√∂rt es scheinbar nicht - Solo absolut einschl√§fernd auf Dauer - spielt man jede Mission genau 1x endet man ca. bei Level 30-35, falls √ºberhaupt ?! - diverse Bugs im Spiel, wie unsichtbare Gegner in den Verteidigungs Missionen - Base Ausbau ebenfalls sehr Grindlastig, wenn man √ºberleben m√∂chte - Schwierigkeit richtig sich nach eigenem Zeitaufwand, je mehr man grindet, desto einfacher ist es eben.. Schade.. denn der Ansatz ist nicht schlecht ;)", "appid": "360170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198303526516", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1517054400.0} {"text": "A very fun game if you enjoy ground, air and naval combat and have a lot of patience and interest for world war and post war vehicles. The game is very realistic with a ton of iconic vehicles to choose from. If you like a certain tank like a T-34 or a Tiger or even an Abrams you will have a fun time grinding and finally getting the vehicle you want. What I must stress though is that grinding is the biggest part of the game and getting the higher tier tanks or planes will definitely take years to get if you don't spend money within the game, even if you do it will still take about a year depending on what you buy. For example buying a premium tier IV tank is only good for researching tanks around that tier and once you get to tier VII you will struggle and will probably lose a lot of silver lions because of your stock tanks. The biggest problems I personally have are: - having to play against post war tanks that one shot you almost every game when you yourself are playing a late world war 2 era tank - this game has pay to win aspects such as bushes and camos that can only be bought with real money - Once you have the tanks or planes you wanted from the start you start to lose interest in the game and in the end you stop playing. Once a new vehicle comes out you get it and lose interest in the game once again, this cycle keeps on repeating. - camping is probably one of the best strategies in the game and if you don't have the patience to stand still and watch a point for 10 minutes then you should play arcade, which in itself is fun but makes grinding take quite a lot longer. - In the higher tiers there is always powercreep meaning that they will release a tank or plane for one nation with something far superior to the others which then makes that one nation extremely op UNTIL other nations finally get the equivalent some patches later, furthermore there will always be wallet warriors that will instantly get the OP vehicle on the first day and just keep killing you without you being able to do anything as your nation hasn't gotten an update yet. Conclusion: If you are one of those people that like a particular vehicle like the Challenger or a MiG then sure you can get this game, but if your vehicle isn't a top tier one than you will most likely get annihilated by vehicles that your tank or plane would have never met pretty often, also getting higher tier vehicles will take a LOT of time. If you are willing to spend some months to experience your favorite vehicle then sure get this game why not, but if you aren't ready to play a game where grinding is everything and the only way to make it faster is by spending money, then I dunno, go play other games where there is a ranked system and everyone is matched equally and skill is the main part of the game.", "appid": "236390",