É£„ÉÉ„Éà„Åø„Å¶„Åª„Åó„ÅÑÔºâ ÊúÄÂæå„Å´ÊÖ£„Çå„Å¶„Å™„ÅÑ„Åü„ÇÅ„Åß„ÅÇ„Çç„ÅÜ„ÄÅÊåáÂÆö„ÅÆ„Ç¢„Ç§„ÉÜ„É†„ÇíËªä„Å´‰πó„Åõ„Å¶Ëªä„ÅÆÂë®„Çä„Å´„ÅÑ„Çå„Å∞„ÇØ„É™„Ç¢„Éº„Å™„ÅÆ„Å´„ÄÅ„Å™„Åú„Å´„Ç¢„Ç§„ÉÜ„É†„ÅΩ„Éº„ÅÑ„Åó„Å¶„Çæ„É≥„Éì„Å®Êà¶„ÅÑ„Å†„Åó„Éº„ÅÆÂãùÊâã„Å´Ê≠ª„Å¨„Å®„Åã„Éª„Éª„Éª„Éª„Éª„Éª„ÄÇÔºà„ÅäÈ°ò„ÅÑ„Åß„Åô„ÄÅ„Åò„Å£„Å®„Åó„Å¶„Å¶„Åè„Å†„Åï„ÅÑÔºâ „Éï„É¨„É≥„Éâ„Å®„Éú„Ç§„ÉÅ„É£„Åó„Å™„Åå„Çâ„ÇÑ„Å£„Åü„Çä„Åô„Çã„ÅÆ„Åß„ÅÇ„Çå„Å∞Èù¢ÁôΩ„ÅÑ„Çà„Å≠ÔºÅÔºÅ„ÅÜ„Çì„ÅÜ„Çì „Å®„Å´„Åã„Åè„Åø„Çì„Å™ÊúÄ‰ΩéÈôê„ÅÆËã±Ë™û„ÅØÁêÜËß£„Åó„Çà„ÅÜÔºÅÔºÅ„Ç≤„Éº„É†„ÇØ„É™„Ç¢„Éº„Åß„Åç„Å™„Åè„Å™„Å£„Å°„ÇÉ„ÅÜ„Åã„Çâ„Å≠ÔºÅÔºÅ ÁßÅÁöÑ„Å´„ÅØÂ´å„ÅÑ„Å™„Ç≤„Éº„É†„Åß„ÅØ„Å™„ÅÑ„Åå„ÄÅ„Åç„Å£„Å®ÁßÅ‰ª•‰∏ä„Å´„Ç§„É©„Ç§„É©„Åô„Çã‰∫∫„ÇÇ„ÅÑ„Çã„Åã„ÇÇ„Åó„Çå„Å™„ÅÑ„ÄÇ „Å™„ÅÆ„ÅßÁßÅ„ÅØ„Åô„Åô„ÇÅ„ÅØ„Åô„Çã„Åë„Å©Âãß„ÇÅ„ÅØ„Åó„Å™„ÅÑ„ÄÇ „Åì„Çå„Åì„ÅùË≥õÂê¶‰∏°Ë´ñ„ÅÆ„É¨„Éì„É•„Éº„ÄÅÁöÜ„Åï„ÇìËâØ„ÅÑ„Çæ„É≥„Éì„É©„Ç§„Éï„Çí( *¬¥Ëâ∏ÔΩÄ)", "appid": "717690", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041776106", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1541592000.0} {"text": "rubberband u said?", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198182963266", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514030400.0} {"text": "Avoided this game since its' open beta. Then, a few days ago, i decided to take the risk and bought the game for multiplayer, since i didn't like the campaign when i tried the campaign on my friend's computer years ago. > Is multiplayer really dead? I think it is still alive-ish but it might be a regional thing. I'm living in Turkey and game matches me with Central and Eastern Europeans, Russians and sometimes Turks. While most of people aren't recognizable, some of them are regulars and i see them a lot (starting to memorize their names). Please note that nearly all of the game modes are dead. Like in most of the Call of Duty games, the player base shrunk to Team Deathmatch. > Is there a botmatch option? Can i play with bots? Yes, there is botmatch option. In multiplayer, choose custom game (right of the Nazi Zombies, out of the screen) and you're good to go. You can even play War with bots. > Are there cheaters? I think so. In the region i play, some players are suspicious but the situation is not gamebreaking. It's not like they run and hold left mouse button and kill everyone or they kill you from the other side of the map. > COD:WWII borrow some elements from WaW (gamemodes such as War; weapons such as Type 100, PTRS; dismemberment and gore etc.) while trying to modernize the game (and fails in my humble opinion). But in the end, playing CoD: WWII multiplayer feels like playing on a heavily modded, WWII themed custom CoD server. > It also borrow other things from other CoDs. > If you yearn for dark, gritty atmosphere of WaW, forget it. > If you like Pacific theater, forget it. Only thing you can find is some of the Japanese guns. > If you like to play a simple but fun shooter, you won't find it here too. It might be fun in some cases but it is not simple-fun for sure. > Gore isn't that good like in WaW. Most of time you can't even notice if someone lose their limbs. + Some design problems and old-school graphics here and there (which feels extremely cheap) but graphics are good enough. + If you want to play a mindless multiplayer shooter, it makes you play. + Carentan, if you miss the CoD 2 (on store page they say that you have to buy Season Pass to play on Carentan but i didn't buy Season Pass and, for an unknown reason, i can play on there). + You don't need to pay for microtransactions (COD Points). - Overpriced for what it offers. - Overcomplicated, nearly useless menu. - Some weapons are only unlockable with supply drops (loot boxes)(i.e. PTRS). - No dedicated servers. - Most of the guns are identical. Pistols are underpowered. Weird weapons such as Claymore (the sword one). - A lot of so-called features such as HQ (MMO-like hub area for players), weekly and daily challenges (and some of them are impracticable due to dead game modes such as Domination and War), contracts (time-limited challenges, i.e. kill 10 players with shovel in 20 minutes), social ranks (all of them can be gainable in HQ) and in-game currencies like armory credits (to unlock some avatars, player cards, weapons skins and get contracts) and COD Points (to buy suppy drops - it is not necessary though, you get supply drops while playing). These features somehow makes you play the game but they also drains your energy and desire to continue. Especially contracts are forcing you to play how they want you to play and sometimes it ruins the game not only for you but your teammates since -let's say- you try to melee players in a limited time. You can always pretend if they are not in game but common/rare supply drops or other rewards you get is always tempting. Even if you ignore them, someone else in your team might want to take their chances to complete contracts and ruin your game (i.e. they can kill less and die more in TDM). - I never expected a realistic atmosphere or pure 1940s while i decided to buy the game but the skins and emotes they added ruined the game atmosphere beyond my expectations. Vivid coloured weapon skins, a lot of weapon attachments, weird weapon charms, 90's style dances, ugly player cards and emblems... it feels like an alternative WWII scenario (or a third-party modification). - Uniforms aren't distinguishable. Is that guy an enemy or not? You can't be really sure about it. Furthermore, there are global skins which can be obtainable from supply drops (a.k.a. loot boxes) makes it impossible to say who is who (yes, you can still see color coded nicknames -red and green- but sometimes you can't see them at all or they don't matter). - Auto-balance system is non-existent. Good luck playing 5v2 if something happens. Even if you're in outnumbering side, you'll get bored while searching for enemies. If the game find some other players in background, joined players somewhat fixes the problem but still, teams generally ends up unbalanced. - A little bit grindy to level/rank up, unlock new weapons and perks (with double XP for Soldier, Division and Weapons and it is active since i bought the game -it seems like it is permanent) - TDM-only. \"But you played the game long enough and even found it fun, so why don't you recommend the game?\" you ask. Yes, i played the game for 20+ hours in 8 days and i found it kind of fun. But the multiplayer -especially in this condition- is mediocre at best. If i say otherwise, i would deceive you. I guess i found it fun because i feel tired due to pandemic and other factors and wanted to play a fairly casual multiplayer first person shooter which kind of reminds me older CoD games and end of 2000s and start of the 2010s. So, yes, i'm playing it but it doesn't mean that it is a well-crafted game. So, if you really want to try the multiplayer of the CoD: WWII but can't decide, i hope i could give you some ideas about the multiplayer mode of the game.", "appid": "476620", "steamid": "profiles/76561197981055338", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600084800.0} {"text": "I'd rather have buffalo diarrhea in my ear!!!!!!!!!!!!!", "appid": "111600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198286203843", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565265600.0} {"text": "HotLead is an unpolished game in every sense of the word. The game mechanics like jumping, cover system are out of whack and not even a mouse sensitivity option. You look like an erect robo-penis when you jump in this game. The graphics are quite nice though but the rest of the game like gameplay, sound and story is just pure garbage. Avoid at all cost. It's a freaking Doughnut as in Do Not Buy unless it's free ofcourse then by all means grab it for the trading cards and earn a few cents from it.", "appid": "416170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198296798593", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "27", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1463572800.0} {"text": "2 Years long lease expired so people cant play the game anymore. $60 game that stops being playable 2 years after its release... only 2k could pull out something like this :P", "appid": "385760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198102710877", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1551528000.0} {"text": "But THQ butchered this. Here are some points I noticed while playing: - Too many cutscenes! There were barely any in the original. - Character design: That's not nameless! - That is not Diego either; what happened to them both being thrown into prison and helping each other out? - It's so ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• bright! - It feels like everyone has suddenly turned talkative and happy. I remember in the original you were outcasts. - Nameless had an attitude in the original game, but not \"worst day ever\" - attitude. Fix it. - What the ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• is that combat system? The original one was superb. - I could jump and climb and bug my way through the Gothic world. What happened to that? - Please no invisible walls. Gothic was great because of that kind of freedom. - The saturation. Gothic was grey and dark, the atmosphere fit perfectly. Not bright & shiny like Fallout 4. - Too many skeletons and human-build stuff in the mines. They were empty and left for good in the original. - The dialouge system was perfect...why change it to garbage? - First 20 Minutes of the game: Cutscenes and WAY too long dialogues. What happened to the short / skippy dialouges? - Now to the stuff that I do like: + That fighting stance! Oh how I remember looking like a 5 year old who just picked up a stick. Nice touch bringing it back! + ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• finally a game that gets the shealth right. Swords don't float in midair. + I like the attempt to bring Gothic back for good. So much has changed and change is supposed to be good. But not in this case. If THQ continues to develop this remake the way they are aiming at now, it will fail horribly. I want Gothic. Pure Atmosphere, story, the freedom to go & do anything. Not Rise + Elex.", "appid": "950670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198069208364", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576238400.0} {"text": "Quantity > Quality = Bad game", "appid": "440730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198171836357", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1562846400.0} {"text": "Deluxe Edition gekauft, Kann die neuen Maps nicht spielen. Season Pass kaufen bringt auch nichts, Die Dlc's einzeln kaufen auch nicht. L√§cherlich sowas, bringt das in Ordnung. Zum Spiel: Alles gut bis das es keinen Multiplayer gibt, welcher \"Trottel\" hat das bitte gesagt das an keinen braucht. No Go.. Zum Zeitvertreib, aber mehr auch nicht.", "appid": "287330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198005043420", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1419940800.0} {"text": "Steuerung aus der H√∂lle. Bei diesen Dummen spiel ,solltet ihr eine hohe Frusttoleranz besitzen", "appid": "787400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054430192", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601208000.0} {"text": "Wow", "appid": "877200", "steamid": "profiles/76561198081792029", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1560859200.0} {"text": "bad", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198230548876", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584705600.0} {"text": "The game itself is 7.5/10 But uplay is -15/10 so it's -7.5/10", "appid": "220240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198167325342", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1535803200.0} {"text": "Tr√®s bon jeux de Fps", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561197999785900", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1511438400.0} {"text": "Completely inferior to the good old The clunky and unresponsive UI is absolutely garbage.", "appid": "268850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198016513479", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515585600.0} {"text": "I'm updating my review to accommodate for the changes that came with the cooperative update which, supposedly, is inspired by SWAT 3 & 4. I do have to disclaim that I was banned from the community forums for being \"toxic\" (despite my content being mostly criticisms and feedback about the game), but this is a review of the game itself and not a review of the developer's actions. To kick things off, we're gonna talk about the what the game is about. It's basically Rainbow Six: Siege, without the operator gadgets. It's really standard stuff. Instead of being a unit of elite operators taken from around the globe, you're part of a SWAT team. Keep this in mind later. Now how's the core gameplay? Well the intent of the developers is to provide a \"realistic\" gameplay experience. This \"realistic\" experience isn't really anything special, and is sometimes just laughable. The game features a 3D planning map before every round. This is mostly there to tell you where the hostage or bomb and tells you where you should spawn. It is rarely used for actual planning. This map is also completely negated if you have the map knowledge. The gunplay is horrid, the animations are a mess (this is supposed to be improved on next update, but they didn't actually create it in-house), and the sounds make my ears bleed. The movement in this game is clunky and sluggish. Speaking of movement, this game also comes with a stamina system to combat running and gunning. And they somehow screwed up the stamina system by making it to that shooting a gun takes a noticeable amount of stamina away. Terrific. Doors are an important part of mostly every tactical shooter. In order to open doors, you have to press F twice. One for slightly opening it and the other press for fully opening it. There are no faster ways to open a door. You also have to open both doors in a double door in order to get through. Now those were just some of the few problems this game has. Let's talk about the arsenal. Despite being a SWAT team, you're able to carry frag grenades. Grenades in this game are wack. It doesn't feel good throwing them, and the animation of you throwing your gun at them doesn't help. The other gadgets the SWAT team has are flashbangs, NODs, and C2 charges. The NODs don't have autogating so don't expect to be able to see anything but white. The SWAT team also gets access to 4 different weapons. The M4, SCAR, a shotgun, and a shield. The shield counts as a weapon since you one hit everyone with it. The terrorists get access to 2 weapons. A MAC-10 and an MP7. They have access to frags, door wedges, and door traps. The way you deal with door traps is that you shoot the wire, instead of cutting it with pliers like a normal person. Let's talk PvP, the mode that launched with the game initially. There are 3 modes. Hostage, bomb, and TDM. The planning map I mentioned earlier shows you the location of the bomb because you can apparently hear it beeping the next block over. The hostage will show on the map when he's moved because he has a motion activated GPS. You cannot kill the hostage. TDM is self-explanatory. The hitboxes are a mess. You can paint a guy and he won't go down, yet he'll pop your head in a single shot with a pistol. Now let's discuss PvE because that's a beast of its own. The PvE in this game is stated to be inspired by SWAT 3 & 4. This modes adds nothing that made SWAT 3 & 4 fun & immersive. The AI is a pile of hot garbage. Once they hear a noise, they'll all come running towards it like dinner's ready, basically making a funnel of enemies come towards your way. They don't have voices, making them extremely unpredictable and unfair. They'll either be top of the class Navy SEALs with their accuracy or don't even attempt to aim. There is no middle ground. They'll also sometimes do a 360 no scope when you get real close to them. The terrible AI makes it impossible to get past the first level. The map design makes no clear sense whatsoever. Whose idea was it for the terrorists to set traps on basically every door way and set door wedges outside of their place, locking themselves in? I'm beginning to think these guys are extremely suicidal. The PvE features an ROE that you have to strictly follow. It's very hard to strictly follow an ROE when its complete crap. You have the option of \"arresting\" suspects, but that's rarely encouraged, since you can only get a single flashbang and nothing else. Whether something is considered unauthorized or not is unclear. Sometimes I'll kill an oblivious man the next block over and it won't count. Other times, they'll surrender a split second after shooting me and it's counted as unauthorized force. It desperately needs non-lethal equipment, which SWAT 3 & 4 has. Even when someone surrenders, you can't zip tie them, basically making them free to run whenever they want (they choose not to). Overall, this game doesn't have a lot going for it. The last time I checked, the game's population was a measly 5-6 players. This was just some of the many problems this game has. I don't recommend it.", "appid": "1359090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198098423174", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1597233600.0} {"text": "CS:GO - 50 –æ—Ç—Ç–µ–Ω–∫–æ–≤ –±–æ–ª–∏. –ù–∞–∏–≥—Ä–∞–≤ –≤ —Å–∏ —ç—Å –≥–æ –±–æ–ª–µ–µ 900 —á–∞—Å–æ–≤, –º–æ–≥—É —Å–∫–∞–∑–∞—Ç—å, —á—Ç–æ –∏–≥—Ä–∞ –Ω–µ —Å—Ç–æ–∏—Ç –¥–∞–∂–µ —Å–≤–æ–∏—Ö 500 —Ä—É–±–ª–µ–π. –ù–∏–∫–æ–≥–¥–∞ –Ω–µ –ø–æ–∫—É–ø–∞–π—Ç–µ —ç—Ç–æ! –ü—É—Å—Ç–∞—è —Ç—Ä–∞—Ç–