: false, "tstamp_created": 1491393600.0} {"text": "Just buy Dead By Daylight, it's damned 2.0 baiscly.", "appid": "251170", "steamid": "profiles/76561197997082784", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1467979200.0} {"text": "A game that is bad and I wasted my time and money on it...", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198344545174", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525694400.0} {"text": "–•–æ—Ç—å –∏–≥—Ä–∞ –∏ –æ—Ç–≤–ª–µ–∫–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è –æ—Ç–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ –Ω–∞ –Ω–∞–∂–∞—Ç–∏ –∫–ª–∞–≤–∏—à—å, –Ω–æ —ç—Ç–æ –Ω–µ –∑–Ω–∞—á–∏—Ç, —á—Ç–æ –µ—ë —Å—Ç–æ–∏—Ç –ø–æ–∫—É–ø–∞—Ç—å... –ê—á–∏–≤–∫–∏ —Ç–æ–ª—å–∫–æ –¥–ª—è –∫–æ–ª–∏—á–µ—Å—Ç–≤–∞, –Ω–µ –±–æ–ª–µ–µ... –°–ø–∞—Å–∏–±–æ —Ö–æ—Ç—å –∫–∞—Ä—Ç–æ—á–∫–∏ –µ—Å—Ç—å))) –ö –ø–æ–∫—É–ø–∫–µ –Ω–µ —Ä–µ–∫–æ–º–µ–Ω–¥—É—é –æ–¥–Ω–æ–∑–Ω–∞—á–Ω–æ.", "appid": "581670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120235688", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530878400.0} {"text": "Do you remember that old pal you never really liked from back in the day? The one who always had to get the laser gun from the original game and yet kept complaining about how he disliked the smallest bubbles because he just didn't have the skills to do so? Of course, at least he did hit the platforms with it, wich drove him even more agitated as in the original you had to stay with your grapling hook to shoot them down. Wanna know what he does today? Well ... looks like he f*'n made this game, because he hates about everything from the original concept! Even the timeless piece of art that is the music tune playing throughout the levels got shoved out. There is just no reason at all to play this very reincarnation, apart from what looks like if you do so, you could unlock the original game as a bonus after completion of the overly stretched out tour mode. Avoid, if you love the original!", "appid": "415150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052707118", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590667200.0} {"text": "The screenshots and trailer no longer represent the game. MANY of the skins and some of the models have since been removed. The community is toxic now and anything other than complete and utter praise for this game and its devs will result in a horde of sycophantic fan boys descending on you. The devs are incredibly arrogant and insulting, frequently attacking or insulting their paying customers or their computer hardware. That being said... If I'd written this review a few months ago it would have been so different... Sadly, I can no longer recommend this game. I bought this game a few months back, from what I read and what I'd seen it seemed like a really cool game. There aren't many where you actually get to play as a dinosaur and that really appealed to me. On many occasions I would turn on The Isle and run around the sandbox like, open world servers. Sometimes I'd be a herbivore, a Stegosaurus or Ankylosaurus, and run around trying to ward off predators, find a herd and eat and drink my fill. Sometimes I'd be a carnivore, A T-Rex or an Allosaurus, and find a pack to hunt with, then hunt down some herbivores while trying to avoid being attacked myself. None of this is possible anymore... Not only have they implemented a \"progression system\" Where, each and every time you log in, die or the server crashes, you have to start out as the smallest dinosaur possible and wait a full 60 minutes to get enough points to be a slightly bigger dinosaur. This means that if you wanted to play one of the big carnivores or herbivores it would take , that is of course assuming you don't die and the server doesn't crash. If you are killed, die somehow, get stuck or the server crashes then you have to start It doesn't matter if you are 5 points into your first dinosaur or only need 5 more points to get the biggest, you go right back to the start. There is no \"save\" feature, no checkpoints, nothing. If, for whatever reason you die or are removed from the game your 3-4 hours of waiting around become meaningless. Some people may like this type of meaningless waiting around, this waiting to play the game. Personally I do not. The thing that annoys me is the fact that this is not the game I bought. I would not buy the game in its current state, not because it is early access, but because I don't like this type of game. I don't want to have to wait around for 3 hours in order to play it! If you haven't bought The Isle yet, I would strongly advise you to look at and decide whether you like the direction the game has gone in. If you do, then you can make an informed decision whether you would like to play it or not. For those of us that bought this game for what it was, we're basically screwed...", "appid": "376210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198042871443", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "191", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1470312000.0} {"text": "526 horas en mi otra cuenta y debo decir que no recomiendo el juego. Con la salida de Zexal mejor√≥ un poco, y la banlist hizo un buen trabajo pero hacia falta. El juego no ha mejorado lo suficiente como para atraer nuevos jugadores (nuevos en conocimiento de YGO), el meta sigue casi parecido, ahora es un poco m√°s sencillo subir pero no para decks F2P. Algunos decks cuestan much√≠simo, y que decir de un deck META. Toma el ejemplo de los nuevos SatellarKnight, son 5 a 6 monstruos UR de una misma caja, pero eso no es tan caro, lo caro es que si quieres jugar a casi cualquier deck necesitas Staples, en el deck mencionado se usa ballista (no siempre) es UR y necesitas 2 copias, es de otra caja, puedes reemplazarlo por enemy controller, pero no es lo mismo. Mi opini√≥n es: Si quieres jugar, debes tener 3 cosas a mano, las cuales son, tiempo, paciencia, y dinero; la √∫ltima pareciera broma pero es cierto. Creo que el juego debe mej