_______________#######__________ _________________________####___________ __________________________##____________ ________________________######__________ _______________________#######__________ _____________________#########__________ ____________________###_######__________ ___________________###__######__________ __________________###___######__________ _______________________######___________ _______________________#####____________ ________________________####______(_____ ________________________####_______)_____ ________________________####_____(##)____ ________________________####____(h1z1)___ _______________________#####___(######)__", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083283878", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "67", "votes_funny": "27", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514548800.0} {"text": "This game is complete garbage. The controls dont work with controllor or mouse and keyboard. DON\"T BUY!", "appid": "491280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198000366136", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1492948800.0} {"text": "O jogo √© excelente, suas mec√¢nicas funciona bem e s√£o excelentes, o jogo consegue ser complexo porem n√£o deixa de ser divertido pois um iniciante consegue jogar e zerar porem pra dominar suas mec√¢nicas √© preciso pratica ! Dai voc√™ pergunta, porra se o jogo √© tudo isso porqu√™ n√£o recomenda ? Resposta : Recomendaria sem problemas, √© um excelente jogo, o problema √© a maneira mesquinha a qual o jogo √© vendido, √© um modo controverso e injusto, se voc√™ deseja ter o jogo completo com todos os personagens e roupas ter√° que esta disposto a pagar mais de 3 mil reais, e por isso jamais poderia recomendar isso, jogo DOA desde o DOA2 que √© considerado um dos melhores games de luta de todos os tempos e ver o caminho que a franquia levou √© triste, tor√ßo para existir no futuro um DOA7, porem mais que existir que ele seja vendido de maneira seria e n√£o da mesma maneira mesquinha que o DOA6. Data da analise : 28/06/2020", "appid": "838380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198130029401", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593345600.0} {"text": "Very poorly optimised port, looks great but having massive strutter issues right from the beginning... Running it on 3900x 16gb and 2080 super and still have strutter problems on a 2k resolution. I'd recommend other people to wait for a couple of patches before buying this game, it's a shame really because the game itself looks beautiful.", "appid": "1151640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083591664", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596801600.0} {"text": "this game is trash", "appid": "359550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198306751114", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575633600.0} {"text": "phone one betteur", "appid": "322170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198146561308", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "This game will not challenge you, ever, even at the hardest difficulty. RotTR is extremely easy. Everywhere you have this white paint to signal where you can jump. Lara also has a peculiar \"sense\" where you click Q and all interactive objects in the area will be highlighted for you. She also has plenty weapons and ammos since the beginning. You can clear rooms with 5+ enemies in an instant, and without much challenge. And again, this is straight from the beginning, and at the hardest difficulty setting. Never seen a game underestimate players ability this much. The game is also as linear as they make them, with entire sections that are completely on rails. What really drove me to the point of feeling frustrated while playing is the fact that all areas are stuffed to nausea with these small interactive objects. They range from crafting ingredients to relics, but the only thing you can do is go near one and click the action button, and that's it. Hundreds of times per area (and these levels aren't that big either). Lara will mumble a random line, and your \"level completeness counter\" will go +1. That's it. There is also zero thought behind how these items are placed around, you will find pieces of maps, or boxes in the middle of a bush, or on top of a tree. There is no balance at all either, so after one or two areas Lara will be full on many of these crafting ingredients. The famous tombs from the franchise name are optional! They are irrelevant to the story and game, can be skipped, and even if you do them they will give basically nothing! I would like to give a trophy to that employee that thought a good idea to make tombs irrelevant in a tomb raider game. Cherry on top, this title has microtransactions. Seems like they are for multiplayer only, but you earn microtransaction related credits during the single player. And always during the single player campaign you will be prompted to go check the marketplace menu, and buy some pointless cards not meant for the single player. There was a beautiful game underneath all this manure, but they just killed it. To me is absolutely baffling how this game can have such a high rating.", "appid": "391220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082258384", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1536580800.0} {"text": "SPROOIT", "appid": "334210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198821220042", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531137600.0} {"text": "Jogo ruim, mas com caracter√≠sticas de jogo bom. Quase dois mil horas, em tr√™s anos jogando isso. Chegou a hora de avaliar este jogo. \"Dead by Daylight\" j√° me chamou a aten√ß√£o, primeiramente, em ter uma trilha sonora muito marcante e bem-produzida, o designer dos assassinos s√£o espetaculares, assim como as anima√ß√µes deles, que s√£o convincentes. O jogo, como todos j√° devem saber, trata-se de 4 jogadores contra 1, sendo este o assassino, doravante killer, que deve impedir os quatro sobreviventes de fugirem. Essa ideia funciona muito bem e faz com que tentemos de novo e de novo a fugir, mesmo morrendo o dia todo como sobrevivente. Esconder-se atr√°s de uma √°rvore e passar por pouco para ser descoberto traz uma grande adrenalina e satisfa√ß√£o que torna o jogo mais incr√≠vel. O melhor de tudo √© o sistema de upgrade, melhorar os personagens e assassinos para que se jogue melhor e em novos estilos. Eu mesmo j√° tentei v√°rios estilos: stealth, ati√ßador, reparador, salvador etc. No entanto, o jogo peca na qualidade de apresenta√ß√£o final, n√£o condizendo com o valor total do jogo, mesmo com tantos conte√∫dos. Primeiramente, porque esses conte√∫dos s√£o pagos e caros. As DLCs de personaliza√ß√£o de personagens s√£o muito caras sendo exclusivamente, algumas, compradas com dinheiro real. O jogo nunca se livrou de problemas constantes de glitches e bugs. S√£o tormentos que prejudicam sempre a experi√™ncia e progresso dos jogadores. O sistema de balanceamento nunca est√° perfeito. No in√≠cio, o jogo parecia bem mais balanceado do que atualmente, mesmo com as engrenagens que reparavam instantaneamente os geradores ou os ganchos serem para sempre destru√≠dos. Isso porque o jogo era mais din√¢mico e de m√∫ltiplos objetivos para todos fazerem algo para que o grupo se beneficie, enquanto o killer tinha que atuar mais estrategicamente, ser muito r√°pido. Hoje, entretanto; os sobreviventes, mesmo juntos, n√£o conseguem ter uma chance balanceada de fugir. Isso porque est√° muito f√°cil de ser killer. Quando eu jogo como tal, mato todos facilmente sem nenhuma estrat√©gia complexa, pois as perks dos killers t√™m sido melhoradas com o tempo, enquanto as dos sobreviventes rebaixadas (tome como exemplo as perks: corrida explosiva ou decisive strike). Para piorar, o kil