ways be people that mess up, which annoys other players. (Though this can be adjusted in this host's lobby settings, including the addition of desired restrictions) - PAYDAY 2 can end up lacking constant taste for some players, as the game seems repetitive with the same usual playable level and contents, and that the game doesn't look like it ever changes much, especially from some updates. It's pretty much going to make players feel like this is the same game over and over, as soon as they launch it. - The game's repetitiveness and minimum appeal to players will make PAYDAY 2 seem like a boring, dry, and worthless game in certain times, and not worth wasting time on. - Adding on to the previous con, you're basically going to end up playing the same heists and stuff over and over again everyday you hop on PAYDAY 2, for 80% of your playtime, without anything changing or seen as interesting. Overall, I know I may have bashed the game a bit too much, but it's my own personal thoughts about it. Like I said, PAYDAY 2 can be a love/hate product to players, depending on how everyone's taste over content is. If you enjoy the usual feel of the game, go for it. If you can't seem to be interested CONSTANTLY, because of how the game slowly dies and feels dry on you, then don't waste time hopping on.", "appid": "218620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198292069452", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "290", "votes_funny": "40", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1577016000.0} {"text": "Z1 map RIP", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198402498009", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1523188800.0} {"text": "Nicht mehr so Gut, wenn man den 3 Teil vorher gespielt hat ...", "appid": "20920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082799249", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498651200.0} {"text": "N√£o √© meu forte, mas o jogo √© bom.", "appid": "440", "steamid": "prof