1198223642436", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533902400.0} {"text": "Unfortunately it is not playable at its current state. It constantly disconnects and crashes, losing my progress. I will give it another chance a couple of weeks down the road, but for now steer clear.", "appid": "1030210", "steamid": "profiles/76561197982970251", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1592136000.0} {"text": "ÊàëÊÉ≥ËâπÂ•≥‰∏ªÔºå‰∏∫‰ªÄ‰πàËâπ‰∏çÂà∞", "appid": "771920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198385777636", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "539", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531396800.0} {"text": "Is this a joke!? If I hadn't gotten it for $0.09 I would have felt seriously ripped off. The game is nonsensical. Menu is non-existent. Talk about bare bones. No intro. No setting. No instruction. Gamepad support?? Forget it! It doesn't explain that your movement control is WSAD and left mouse to spin your character. Someone mentioned that this is a jukebox not a game. I admit the music is great for pumping you up, but it cuts off in the game. As to gameplay, there's not much to it. It's about setting you out to get killed and very fast too. There's no fairness, no rhyme, no reason. Why would anyone want to play this? Steam Cards. Its only somewhat redeeming quality. As the last reveiwer mentioned, start the game, walk away, and then come back later to find card drops.", "appid": "301480", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985100593", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1419681600.0} {"text": "It seemed a nice platformer, challenging bosses with beautiful pixel art and all, but I simply could not play, as the first scene, in the 'angel city', should be a friendly one, is just hell to get from a place to another with absolutely no enemies, as you need microtimed jumps, and that simply mak