∞–≥–æ–≤ –≤–æ–æ–±—â–µ —Ç–æ–º—É –∫—Ç–æ —ç—Ç–æ —Å–¥–µ–ª–∞–ª –Ω–∞–¥–æ –≥–æ—Ä–µ—Ç—å –≤ –∞–¥—É.", "appid": "1244950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006325591", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "105", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598011200.0} {"text": "Fallout 76 is a game with a lot of potential and good ideas, ruined by bad design choices and greed. It is certainly better than it was at its release, but it still suffers from a lot of problems it had at the start and you can't fix those by simply adding NPCs with Wastelanders update. Plus it has one of most predatory monetization systems with Atomic Shop and Fallout 1st shouldn't exist. Sometimes it feels like developers just took Fallout 4 and dumped it into an online world without making any adjustments to it, that you need to make if you are making an online game instead of classic one. Good things: 1. Amazing world, my personal favourite wasteland to explore 2. (Wastelanders) Dialogue system and writing is great, humour is back, you can build your character with dialogue choices, supporting cast is interesting, with their own motivation and personalities 3. (Wastelanders) Great quest design, there are some new ideas here I never saw in Fallout before 4. Weapon and enemy variety is decent, there is a lot to choose from and shoot 5. Weapon modification and card system are both good imo, but I know some people that prefer old ways of leveling up 6. Community is suprisingly nice, I never met any griefers and everyone was friendly, plus you can create vendor stalls to trade with other players, cool feature 7. CAMP building is fun, but a lot of good stuff is locked behind Atomic Shop paywall. Neutral - Main storyline - I personally like it (expect for Rose's story), but I know a lot of people that don't, but I think that with Wastelanders update it is a lot better, since now you don't just listen to hours of holotapes, but there are some actual NPCs at key locations. Bad things - oh boy, there is a lot 1. Level scaling system - Enemies level scales according to highest level player that passed through location, so good luck if you are just starting out and be prepared to be blasted by level 60+ enemies anywhere you go, unless you server hop 2. Weapons you find are usually locked behind level requirements, so even if you explore or kill high level enemies, you can't use anything you find, that ruins exploration for me, because what's the point? 3. Combat - to me it feels clunky, animations get bugged, enemies shoot through walls, they are braindead with no AI, most of them use melee attacks, so you just run around and try not to get hit, which gets boring quickly, it is basically a worse version of Fallout 4 combat 4. Survival mechanics - I don't understand what is their point, hunger and thirst meter only make your inventory full of food and water, but there is always enough of both, so you never feel like you are in danger and I personally think they should be removed or optional 5. Stash managment - In a game that tries to me an MMO and makes you pick everything up and rewards you with tons of weapons, you have a stash limit of 800, which can be easily filled in few hours and then you are stuck doing inventory managment for half your playtime. Why not decrease weight of items or make stash unlimited? I know that it is possible, because you offer it to Fallout 1st subscribers. 6. Side quests and lack of things to do - there are like 5 or 6 side quest and other than doing main quest, you are stuck with boring daily quests, so there is not that much to do here, but you need to level up if you want to explore high level locations, so you either grind low level mobs or try to push through main storyline and run away from stronger enemies, since there is no way to beat them and I don't think either of these two options is fun. 7. Bugs - Well there are still tons of bugs and synchronization issues, but it is better than it was at start. But it is still not perfect and I don't think it will ever be. 8. Fallout 1st and Atomic Shop - ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• both of these, a 15 dollars/month subscription service in a game that doesn't work, that basically fixes like half of its problems and offers features that should be in base game is a slap in the face of anyone who bought this game. Atomic Shop sucks aswell, skins are overpriced and anything pretty is locked behind its paywall. So overall I can't recommend Fallout 76 yet and unless developers fix its basic problems and publisher stop being greedy and gives us basic features that should be in game for free, instead of paying for them, then I don't think that Fallout 76 will ever get a redemption story like No Man's Sky. It has potential though. Anyway full review is here:", "appid": "1151340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044956970", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598702400.0} {"text": "–ß—Ç–æ-—Ç–æ –Ω–∞–≥–ª–æ –ø–æ–¥–∞–≤–∞—Ç—å —Ç–∞–∫–æ–µ –¥–æ–ø–æ–ª–Ω–µ–Ω–∏–µ –∑–∞ —Ü–µ–Ω—É –∏–Ω–¥–∏ –∏–≥—Ä—ã (–æ—Ç–ª–∏—á–Ω–æ–π –∏–Ω–¥–∏ –∏–≥—Ä—ã). –ï—Å–ª–∏ –≤–∑—è—Ç—å –∏ –≤—ã—Ä–µ–∑–∞—Ç—å 50 % –∫–æ–Ω—Ç–µ–Ω—Ç–∞ –∏–∑ –¥–æ–ø–æ–ª–Ω–µ–Ω–∏—è –ö—Ä–æ–≤—å –∏ –í–∏–Ω–æ (–í–µ–¥—å–º–∞ 3), —Ç–æ –ø—Ä–∏–º–µ—Ä–Ω–æ –±—É–¥–µ—Ç —ç—Ç–∞ —Å—É–º–º–∞, –¥–∞ –∏ –∫–æ–Ω—Ç–µ–Ω—Ç –ø–æ–¥—Ö–æ–¥—è—â–∏–π –ø–æ–¥ –Ω–µ–µ. –ñ–∞–¥–Ω–µ–Ω—å–∫–æ. –°–ø–æ—Ä—é –∫–æ–º–ø–µ–Ω—Å–∏—Ä—É—é—Ç –±–µ—Å–ø–ª–∞—Ç–Ω—ã–º –¥–æ–ø–æ–ª–Ω–µ–Ω–∏—è–º –¥–ª—è God Eater 3, –¥—É–º–∞—é —Ç–∞–∫ –∏ –µ—Å—Ç—å.", "appid": "774011", "steamid": "profiles/76561198052740874", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581336000.0} {"text": "A lot of people have said the same, but after over two 10 hours of play time the game just stops launching. It was fun until then, because now i can't refund the game and all the dlc i bought. 3/10", "appid": "863550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198950690419", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false,