ney. ALL of it. Hooray for recurrent consumer spending! Go screw yourself, 2K.", "appid": "577800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198037251340", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "173", "votes_funny": "66", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1526558400.0} {"text": "Huge waste of money. Terrible controls with a highly difficult and advantage-having AI. They'll spam you with explosives and cops will overwhelm you as you're attempting to fight them off while your mouse conflicts with ASWD. Not to mention they drain most of your health in two seconds. Don't waste five dollars on this sack of ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. All it is, is killing mostly innocent people anyway. Get Postal 2. The only good thing about Postal 1 is the soundtracks. Postal 2's way better than this trash.", "appid": "232770", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034908388", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1425124800.0} {"text": "DooM Eternal is a bit of a disappointment. Between a bit heavy handed gameplay, unreliable always online drm and a big collectathon i don't think this game is worth it's asking price. (Especially not with the dlc.) What i'm missing is the thing that made DooM 2016 good/fun. An arcade mode that skips the ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. The soundtrack is amazing and always fits very well to what is currently happening in game and i hope we will be able to buy it standalone soon. The graphics are very good and good looking albeit a bit generic knight/viking levels were added and the hell aesthetics aren't that gritty anymore. (compared to 2016) Gameplay feels more like a character action game (like dmc e.g.) in first person than a shooter. Movement got upgraded with dashes and a grappling hook on the ssg (yay :D) but this is needed since normal movement is pretty much only useful out of combat to get you to the next fight. In combat you jump, dash and monkey bar swing away from demons in enclosed arenas where you are expected to dispose every enemy according to it's assigned way. If you happen to not utilise the enemies gimmick/weakness they are very bullet spongey which you can't afford them to be because ammo is intentionally scarce and you have to rely on the fodder enemies as your resource (health/armor/ammo) batteries. I have a feeling they mistook action with being stressed and just added more mechanics (aka stuff to worry about) on top until the right level of stress was reached. The progression system is awful and annoying. Almost everything that makes combat a bit more fun is locked behind a progress bar or point system. The first hours of this game is work to get to the fun and strongly reminds me of game design that wants to push you to paying money to avoid the grind. I mean to improve a weapon you have to find a drone to unlock a specialisation first. Then get weapon points to improve it and unlock the mastery and then do a challenge to really unlock the mastery which you can skip by paying another kind of token. You have to do this twice for every weapon and a similar system is in place for the suit and health/armor/ammo upgrades. Did i mention the weapon you have to unlock by collecting keys through completing challenges and the batteries you have to collect to unlock skins or other unlock currency? But when you have worked through the annoying/awful things the game is quite fun. Alas not as fun as the hype bros want to make you believe. Edit: (I forgot to mention the issues with When you are starting the game or loading a level or just open the codex/arsenal ingame menu with tab the game wants to connect to . If the service is not reachable or slow you are forced to wait a long time through the connect attempt without the ability to abort.", "appid": "782330", "steamid": "profiles/76561197960710753", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585483200.0} {"text": "I know this game is still in BETA but I don't recommend buying this unless you have people u can play with regularly. Cause its boring when you play alone. Not to mention you need a really high end GPU to run it properly since its not optimized", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127466309", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1511870400.0} {"text": "Can't change my skin. I'm forced to play with a random generated, which i really don't like. Don't want to play like this. Don't buy.", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113610475", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1484740800.0} {"text": "I know I'll be against the majority with this review, and I knew beforehand this was going to be a short game before going in. But with barely 4 hours of total playtime Firewatch can hardly be considered a game. It's more of a (very) short interactive story with pleasant visuals. The story isn't that deep or interesting either, it's very linear until the end. In a few points there were nice hooks, that could have been developed into something interesting, but they were not taken advantage of, resulting in an overall flat and linear story that will leave you nothing after ending. TLDR: Visuals and voice over are quite good. But sadly there isn't much else. Total game length is barely 4 hours. So buy at a big discount, if you must, but it still might feel like overpaying.", "appid": "383870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082258384", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "51", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1534420800.0} {"text": "My only issue with this game is the terrible matchmaking, which is a big issue. My first few matches were fair, every single one after was me getting my ass kicked by people with fancy skins and exclusive mounts. Out of 5 hours I've only enjoyed my first 20 minutes.", "appid": "504370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072215182", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511438400.0} {"text": "Not an essential expansion and you don't get what is advertised. Just finished a campaign and a there are a few bugs. All in all, these bugs would have been easy to spot by a rookie QA team. Generally I am underwhelmed and disappointed. Lets take the text that was advertised and compare it to the product that was shipped - shall we? As Nakalim, you have a head start in tech and you'll actually keep it for a very long time, like 100+ turns on normal difficulties, probably some less on higher difficulties. But it does not feel like \"They ... are very poor at Science \". They are very good for most of the game at science thanks to the headstart and the relics. The use of relics for non-tech is meh. Maybe there is a niche use of relics with a production specc-ed hero on a production specc-ed system but is not obvious to me. To gain advantage of the temple you need a very narrow conjunction of circumstances. \"Their relationship with the Academy allows them to gain control over other systems through the Influence of their Temples,\" just means that there is another way to convert pacifically neighbouring systems that are low on influence. Consider that it will not happen on 80% of the playthrough and if it happens, will not tip the balance by much. So very niche, very gimmicky. Temples are not a core mechanism. Generally the way they play is like Venetians in other 4x games - very hard to colonize due to horrible desert start and no colonization ship at spawn. But thanks to turn 1 access to market to buy strategic resources and decent dust production, it makes it easy to have 1-2 very good mid game ships early flanked by half-a-dozen mercenary ships by turn 20. Mercenaries will cost you then 20-30 dust per ship upfront and 4 dusts per turn. You can then pass turn 20-50 to expand by attacking neighbours. So yes - these guys play like merchants paying for mercenaries and headhunters with a few own troops backed by strong tech. They do NOT feel at any moment like religious figures on a royal prophecy. That the relics make them so good at science is also very weird to me. I just don't buy that bits of bones and sacred clothes do generate blue science matter, sorry. The best part of the DLC is actually the changes to the academy. The mechanisms are quite well explained in the DLC description and add fun mechanism. That was unexpected but cool. Please note there is no way to interact with the academy by normal standard diplomatic means. You have to get summoned and interact only on their terms. Ok why not. I was more thumb down than thumb up after all this. But what really nailed it to thumb down for me is... that the main quest of this faction DLC cannot complete on chapter 4. There are two tech to unlock and once they unlock it does not move to next chapter. I am sure it will be fixed soon. but in 2019, the way DLCs are priced - not properly QA the main quest of a faction DLC? This is ... un-ac-cep-ta-ble. And yes it is also well reported on a few places including their official forums...", "appid": "1128540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198080099141", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "331", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1568376000.0} {"text": "Seguramente, una de las peores cosas que puedas comprar por 0.39‚Ç¨, que es lo que he pagado yo. Tan malo, que estoy incluso pensando en devolverlo, aunque me cueste m√°s \"tiempo-dinero\" hacerlo. Lo ten√≠a todo para triunfar: modelado sencillo, cricuitos molones y un nombre rid√≠culo con letras hechas en Word Art (tm). En una dimensi√≥n paralela, tampoco merece la pena comprarlo. Ideal para youtubers", "appid": "618140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198062456300", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593345600.0} {"text": "‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•, Pinball Arcade ist zwar kostenlos spielbar, aber auch wieder nicht. Man hat einen ganzen ewig verwendbaren Tisch, dann kann man noch alle anderen testen. Ja, man muss sich alle anderen Tische kaufen. Das alleine ist schon Grund genug das Spiel negativ zu bewerten. Es ist f√ºr mich ein No-Go, dass man einen kleinen Teil des Spiels kostenlos anbietet und man den Rest kaufen muss.", "appid": "238260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072615417", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1400673600.0} {"text": "---{Grafikler}--- ‚òêGer√ßek Hayattan Daha ƒ∞yi ‚òê G√ºzel ‚òê ƒ∞yi ‚òë Normal ‚òê K√∂t√º ‚òê Uzun S√ºre Bakma ‚òê Paint.exe ---{Oynanƒ±≈ü}--- ‚òê √áok ƒ∞yi ‚òê ƒ∞yi ‚òê Normal ‚òê Eh ƒ∞≈üte ‚òê Duvarlara Bakmak Daha Eƒülenceli ‚òë Sadece OYNAMA ---{Ses Kalitesi}--- ‚òê Efsane ‚òê √áok ƒ∞yi ‚òê ƒ∞yi ‚òê Eh ƒ∞≈üte ‚òë K√∂t√º ‚òê Earrape ---{Ya≈ü Kitlesi}--- ‚òê √áocuklar ‚òê Gen√ßler ‚òê Yeti≈ükinler ‚òê ƒ∞nsanlar ‚òë Kertenkeleler ---{Bilgisayar Gereksinimleri}--- ‚òê 10 Yƒ±llƒ±k PC ‚òë Patates ‚òê Normal ‚òê Hƒ±zlƒ± ‚òê Zengin PC‚Äôsi ‚òê NASA‚Äôdan Bilgisayar ƒ∞ste ---{Zorluk}--- ‚òë Sadece ‚Äúa‚Äù Tu≈üuna Bas ‚òê Kolay ‚òê Beyin ƒ∞ster ‚òê √ñƒürenmesi Kolay/Ustala≈ümasƒ± Zor ‚òê Zor ‚òê Dark Souls ---{Hikaye}--- ‚òë Hikaye ne demek? ‚òê Ses veya Metin ‚òê Eh ƒ∞≈üte ‚òê ƒ∞yi ‚òê Muhte≈üem ‚òê Hayatƒ±n Gibi ---{Oynanƒ±≈ü S√ºresi}--- ‚òê Kƒ±sa ‚òë Normal ‚òê Uzun ‚òê Sonsuzluk ve √ñtesine ---{Fiyat}--- ‚òê Bele≈ü! ‚òê Fiyatƒ±na Deƒüer ‚òê Paran Varsa ‚òë Paranƒ± Yaksan Daha ƒ∞yi ---{Hata}--- ‚òë Hi√ß Olmadƒ± ‚òê Minik ‚òê Sinir Bozucu ‚òê ARK: Survival Evolved ‚òê Oyunun Kendisi Hata", "appid": "818790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198812305269", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579435200.0} {"text": "Sound is broken and was reported issue with the demo. ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• audio was removed as well. Wouldn't know, no sound. Overpriced for underpolished product. Avoid until they fix it.", "appid": "650510", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985036092", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "59", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1536062400.0} {"text": "Yakƒ±nda insanlarƒ± da DLC ile satacaklar.", "appid": "255710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034533413", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "13", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1546344000.0} {"text": "‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030037538", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1431864000.0} {"text": "To jsem si tak chtel zahrat na prvni pohled roztomilou relaxacni hru s listickou v hl. roli...ze ktere se ejhle vyklubala nenapadna mormonska propaganda :) Ono to asi vetsine gameru vadit nebude, protoze to jsou bohuzel spise ateisti, ale mne jako katolikovi toto prozreni plesklo do oci jak cervenej hadr a cele snazeni autoru hodilo v zaveru na jiny level. Ale neni to JEN o tom, proc davam palec dolu. Hra je zaprve velmi kratounka (cca 2h), ale to je i na strance Storu uvedeno, takze to nebudu brat jako negativum. Horsi je spis gameplay jako takovy. Zakladem je jakysi \"pulnocni\" dialog Josepha a Rachel (easter egg - nejenze se zamerne jedna o zidovska jmena, ale zakladatel \"Cirkve Jezise Krista Svatych poslednich dnu\" a publisher \"Book of Mormon\" byl Joseph Smith Jr., 1805-1844). Vyklada hlavne o vztahu s jeho zesnulym otcem. Vztahu, ktery nebyl uplne idealni a zrejme jako i jini synove by byl rad, aby si s tatou mohl dulezite veci urovnat. K rozpominani se na minulost slouzi sen s onou listickou, ktera probiha lokacemi (zima, jaro, leto, podzim) a narazi na drobnosti z Josephova detstvi - tu hracka, tu detsky bunkr, rozbite veci apod. Do toho hraje opravdu pekny soundtrack, prevazne na piano, bez ktereho by hra spadla okamzite do podprumeru. Myslenka snoveho bloudeni neni spatna a \"umelecka\" grafika moc hezka, ale to zpracovani je nedotazene. Misty to pusobi jak amaterska ukazka Unity enginu. Hlavne skoky lisky jsou podivne \"plovouci\" a nepresne, takze do platformer zanru to ma dost daleko. Kdyz k nesikovnemu skakani prictete otravnou kameru, ktera se nedrzi za liskou, ale neustale ji musite rovnat, casto jsem opravdu skripal zuby. I samotny beh je pomerne otravny - napr. vubec nechapu, proc je tu pomale chozeni. Lokace jsou velke a spis bych uvital, kdyby liska bezela furt sama od sebe, aniz bych to musel neustale drzet analogem na gamepadu. Kdyz ale vemem v potaz, ze se jedna o indie hru a ze je fakt kratka, daji se nad jednoduchym modelem pohybu primhourit oci. Horsi je, pokud jste achievement hunter. Tohle je presne typ hry, kdy si budete asi trhat vlasy a nakonec sahnete po navodu. Na mapach jsou rozmisteny (nekdy docela sadisticky) bile hvezdicky, ktere sbirate a samozrejme pro achiev potrebujete vsechny. U nich me stvalo, ze se neda prilis odhadnout jejich poloha ve vzduchu a casto je minete. Navic zde neni zadny save a neda se pro ne ani vratit. Najednou se obraz ztmavi a hra vas posle do dalsiho levelu. Jako WTF? Dale je tu spousta drobnosti na zemi z Josephova detstvi, ktere musite opet najit vsechny. Nejsou tu zadne vyrazne zachytne vizualni body, mapa apod. Ba naopak vsude sama vegetace. Cili \"hledani jehly v kupce sena\" jak z ucebnice...no hruza. Do relaxacni filosoficke hry takto narocne (nebo spise vyjebavaci) achievementy podle me nepatri. Mely by jit udelat na jeden zatah a ne takhle. No a ten konec...pokud to nekomu nedoslo behem deje, kniha \"Book of Mormon\" na nocnim stolecku ve hre je jistota :) Filosofii toho, co ma liska a jeji mrtva mladata co do cineni se vztahem otce a syna, jsem nejak nepochopil. Kazdopadne cela tahle anabaze a cesta \"za prvnim stromem\" je vpodstate nenasilne ztvarneni mormonskeho proroka Lehie (resp. Josepha Smithe Sr.). Nerikam, ze je to spatne, ale hrac by to mel asi vedet. Podsouvat nekomu jiste myslenky podloudne...to ja nemam rad.", "appid": "555150", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968357064", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1552219200.0} {"text": "‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñÑ‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÄ‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñê‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñà‚ñê‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñà‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñà‚ñê‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñê‚ñë‚ñà‚ñÑ‚ñÑ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñÄ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñÑLEATHERFACE‚ñÑ‚ñÑ‚ñÑ‚ñÄ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë ‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë‚ñë", "appid": "700280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198157643661", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1506081600.0} {"text": "Ctrl Shift ESC End Task", "appid": "1239520", "steamid": "profiles/76561197971784544", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601640000.0} {"text": "Todos sabemos que el Far Cry PRIMAL fue el DEBACLE, pero este le sigue los pasos!!! MALO por TODOS lados, solo UNA cosa positiva por lo que tampoco lo hace valer. 1.Historia: MUUY POBRE, MAL PENSADA CON 22 MISIONES PRINCIPALES MUUY CORTAS 2.Armas: Como muchas 20 de la cual 15 son con CREDITOS....... ¬°¬°¬°¬°PAY TO WIN!!!! 3.Mundo: El MISMO que el 5, TODO IGUAL, solo flores rosadas por todos lados 4.IA: POBRE, los enemigos por momentos te dan la espalda...... MUY TRISTE 5.Gameplay: 0 cambio a los anteriores, agregaron SALTO DOBLE....... BUGS, COME ON IS UBISOFT!!!!! 6.Soundtrack: es lo UNICO BUENO!! lo mejor al entrar a las bases (Fatty Boom Boom . Die Antwoord) CONCLUSION FINAL : 0 ganas de crear un juego por donde