"221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198217919117", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544875200.0} {"text": "Can't finish the game, due to a bug in the final episode. (can't move my char in a certain boss fight) Not going to restart a whole episode, just to check out if it's bugged again at the same place. So far the game was OK until that point the game was bugged. By far not the best Resident Evil, but also no the worst... But I can't recommend a game that prevents me of finishing it...", "appid": "287290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008516562", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1464177600.0} {"text": "The game is extremely unoptimized. Game gets laggy when you expand prison because it only uses one CPU core. I can't recommend this game unless you can limit yourself to a very small prison.", "appid": "233450", "steamid": "profiles/76561198089075951", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574596800.0} {"text": "Back in 2014 despite its bugs This quickly became my most played game on steam. The random interactions with phyco players was great. though it was supposed to be a zombie survival game it was more or less the PUBG of times time. 2 years later and I'm sad to see they have literally changed more or less nothing. even the zombies are extremely buggy.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075410789", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1510315200.0} {"text": "This is a (just about )multi path branching choice based VN. The story is the fairly generic 'boy' moves to new area and goes to school and through some choices gets 'girls' out of his normal target range. + reasonable art good sound gothic lollies - Generic bland story no sense of connection with the characters Plot lines not utilised DS is a slice of life VN set on an island where no one is unhappy; the MC moves there after advice from his cousin and starts school, the problem is that its an incredibly dull slice. Nothing really happens and there is no real hook to get you invested in the characters nor the story. It lacks that little bit magic (no pun intended) that the DC series had. Parts of the story line are underutilised (e.g. the happy numbers) and others are just ropey (the MC suddenly remembering he lost his glasses after weeks of not using them) and everything plods mundanely through to the end leaving you wondering why anyone bothered writing it in the first place (maybe the producers needed a new porch extension or their drive repaved or something). Everything that happens is generic and predictable and even the 18+ patch fails to bring any real interest. If the game could be equated to a colour it would be dysentery beige If you want a dull plodding slice of life VN then go for it but I would suggest going for any of the DC stories instead", "appid": "638930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007850719", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "54", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1501243200.0} {"text": "I just want to know when you finish the Chinese translation.", "appid": "482730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198101977609", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1478347200.0} {"text": "Yeh so just beat the game. It had all the camera and inventory mechanics of the first game, but improved. The steath was wonky, and the game had no final answer or explanation. It could've had less nudity and less blood. Really, I wish this game was more of a horror, and less of a gross out. I do recommend the first game though.", "appid": "414700", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090521470", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529841600.0} {"text": "This game sucks more than Epic Games sucks