"early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1578052800.0} {"text": "Avalanche dropped development and moved on to make RAGE 2, i guess. Whatever scraps were done were packaged and sold as this piece of poop. Patched up and fitted with a DLC it's still somehow looks and plays worse than Just Cause 3.", "appid": "517630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003122895", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543924800.0} {"text": "Not recommended! After years of development it has barely the state of a prototype - and it gets worse the further they work on it. Don't expect to have a good gaming experience or much variety. From what I have seen, the developers don't care much to provide the players a good gaming experience. What started promising turns out to be an annoying game. Edit: And, you have 'missions' now. The scheme is, go there, kill this, get reward. No replayability for missions, cause you already have your reward. Nothing that extends the gameplay or is relevant for the ongoing game. Just short thrills and then back to boring. New game play experience depends now very much on releasing new missions - in a survival sandbox game..", "appid": "313120", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968428721", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "74", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1498651200.0} {"text": "(Review text hidden)", "appid": "587620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198074850966", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1518350400.0} {"text": "Clunky, buggy, bad performance, etc. etc., you've probably already read all of these things in the other reviews. As much as I love the Blair Witch franchise, this doesn't do it for me. Wait for the devs to patch the big issues, and preferably wait for it to go on sale. Would buy again and recommend if it wasn't a 30 dollar mess.", "appid": "1092660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048064777", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1567166400.0} {"text": "brought this game for zombies to play with my friends and then tried to setup a server so me and my friends could play but we could not join each other, we tried multiple fixes and they did not work i was very disapointed with this.", "appid": "10090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198226302388", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1472731200.0} {"text": "The game ran pretty poorly. Controls can't be changed (that I could find). Aiming with a controller felt like it was locked to a grid and not smooth like with a mouse. Killing certain enemies with autotargetting would cause the camera to freak out. The gameplay seemed fine but there were too many issues to enjoy it.", "appid": "384490", "steamid": "profiles/76561197986710049", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1480075200.0} {"text": "Don't buy this game... it's abandon by the developers and no new updates!", "appid": "352460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198201342783", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1446811200.0} {"text": "A creative, but nevertheless cloned Minecraft game. The game gets its updates, it is playable, but I can't get it out of my mind as another MC clone. Sorry guys...", "appid": "280790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018221890", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1477137600.0} {"text": "Hullad√©k.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198147806964", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1540641600.0} {"text": "the game sucks", "appid": "773240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127360339", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1528977600.0} {"text": "Muito mal opitimizado, tenho um pc considerado forte e roda o jogo em 50 fps. Precisa de mais suporte aos jogadores, e um sistema de anticheat mlr!", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198263642152", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1578398400.0} {"text": "‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•, digs for info, dont like it digging for a name....", "appid": "107410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008113369", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1528977600.0} {"text": "This is the MOST ARCADEY and MIND-NUMBING WW2 RTS I have ever played. Basically there's little strategy or even tactic involved. Most matches were just moving the deathball of troop toward the enemy. I didn't believe my eyes when I watched a youtuber Raptor moving his armor cars with his tank lagging behind and he still crushed the enemy. Gone was the feeling of accomplishment or even fulfillment you often get after a match on the old Blitzkrieg or Sudden Strike. I have no doubt that we will see a mobile port in a near future when this game tanks on PC. Campaign: Forgettable. I have no motivation to move on with the campaign b/c it's generic, trivial and felt just like an extra bullet point behind the gamebox. Gameplay: play just like a mobile game with fancy graphic. Make no mistake, if you think CoH was arcadey, this is even 10x times more. There's little flanking, manuvering or positioning of any kind. Like I said above, just make one single deathball of troop/tank and press Attack-Move. Rinse. Repeat. Graphic: very nice with flashy and over-the-top explosion. Audio: excellent voice over, each faction campaign has its own native speech with English subtitle for me. Lasting Appeal: - If you are a hardcore RTS gamer who look for the next gen WW2 RTS, look elsewhere. Spend time with Sudden Strike 4, Steel Division or Men of War Assault Squad 2. - If you are a casual RTS gamer, go play Clash of Clan. Y