tstamp_created": 1586865600.0} {"text": "I've somewhat always enjoyed a good session of TD. and by the looks of it. This game thoroughly looks and even feels like an oldschool topdown towerdefense with your regular gun, rocket, lightning, fire, slowing, concussion/aoe towers and so on with varying maps and difficulties. However, the problem with this game is that you can clearly see it's made and it's meant to be in the marketplaces with microtransactions such as microsoft store and mobile devices where you can buy coins (Didn't know this when i purchased the game). And even when the developer has lowered the difficulty (According to his own words), the difficulty spike shows, and the maps become absolute pain to complete, especially if you want to get the related achievements (Completing the maps without losing a single life.) When you have to actually struggle through what's the halfway of the game at the time of the review on easy difficulty, you can imagine how hard this games hard or nightmare difficulties are. Game lacks some serious optimization for it to be worth noted as a decent tower defense, but don't get me wrong, the gameplay itself is your generic towerdefense strategy which from time to time isn't bad, and didn't expect too much more for the admission of the game, however, i can't recommend the game to anyone until the serious optimization in difficulty/obtaining money to improve your towers are fixed. Especially when the levels themselves can take upwards of an hour even when sped up,. Oh and one final thing, completing the levels on harder difficulty won't attain you achievements for the lower difficulty levels, so you absolutely have to complete each level 4x in order to get the achievements.", "appid": "324520", "steamid": "profiles/76561197991757040", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592913600.0} {"text": "S√≥ compre esse jogo se tiver interessado nas conquista...pois √© muito ruim!", "appid": "422870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198090967709", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1484568000.0} {"text": "I dont have anything against this game itself, but the community is the real problem of this game. On every game at least 1 kid that is insulting others, becouse he thinks hes boss. Then Russians and Polish guys. Insulting you for not winning 1vs5 with 10 hp. For example: I played Inferno, 1 round killed 4 enemies, next round killed 3 and 4th killed me becouse I had 20 hp and he had 100, I lost the round. Russians voted to kick me. But there was 1 normal people thatt voted no. Then kids with knives are like: look at my knive, you dont have knife, you are noob. Probably moms bought them knives for Christmas or Birthday. I bought Operation Wildfire. If someone had mission to kill enemies with weapons of your teammates and he asked i dropped him, but when I had that mission, I asked and no one dropped. Only some kind players dropped, but there are few of them. And when no one dropped i needed to get weapon from dead teammate. And another thing that is bothering me, most people disagree with this, but its my opinion. This game is one of the most unrealistic FPS games out there. For example: grenade explode under someones legs, leave them 20 hp. Recoil is like: shooting with ak, controlling spray, aiming to ground, kill enemy. Then skin prices. Prices of skins are horrible. AWP Dragon Lore for 1,000 euro? Really? I will say ok, if this game would be Play for Free game. But 1,000 euro skin for full price game? Thats stealing money. Personaly my most expensive CS:GO item is very cheap Music Kit. Then Overwatch and VAC Bans. For example my friend was playing normaly without cheats and then he got VAC Banned for being cheater. Maybe some kids reported him for killing them and then other kid on Overwatch said: All reported players are cheaters. And send Overwatch report and then my friend got banned. And I almost forgot about hackers. Almost in every game is hacker. Mostly wallhackers or players with no flash. Thats another problem of this game. Thats the end of this review. I dont recommend this game. If you like Counter-Strike series buy it, if you dont disagree with me buy it. Personaly i have better games like Red Orchestra that are in my Steam Library or games that are waiting on for me to buy them on Steam Store.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082773936", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1459944000.0} {"text": "Bad game. Dont buy. This one not even was at gamescom.... Do yourself a favor, buy parkitect and planet coaster instead.... ## updated 2016/11/16 Game is now \"full\" released and it is SAME CRAP! Worst Dev's EVER! Even worst than No Mans Sky or Cities XXL!! They don't listen to gamers community They dont accept negative critics They ban for stating our opinion They ban for criticizing the game The release of RCTW is same thing as EA no improvements no nothing! Bad graphics, bad support, bad updates, bad marketing, bad trailers, bad release. Go and get Planet Coaster instead or Parkitect - even this one, is loads of times better than RCTW. ## UPDATED 2016/08/31 ## Tested latest pxp update, same crap. 1200 peeps and the game still becomes unplayable and then crash consuming almost all memory in the system. Also Pxp is the crappy copy of the one in Planet Coaster. They even added the same stores style as planet coaster to build the custom shops / building. Also they have reserved a slot on track station exactly the same (at least the faded screenshot) as Planet Coaster. Again, DO NOT BUY THIS!! ALSO THE GRAPHICS = AAARRRRGGGGHHHHH!!!!! MY PRECIOUS DISK SPACE! DELETED FROM COMPUTER ONCE AGAIN!! ## UPDATED 2016/08/27 ## Transcript of a comment i made on this review to @Scoot_in_FL:", "appid": "282560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198050122179", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "37", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1471867200.0} {"text": "The game has sadly become excedingly pay to win. Unique and well constructed robots pretty much no longer exist, almost every bot you will see will be a variation on whatever the current meta is. The game also penalizes your standing in the leagues and thus your chances of getting better items, which are required to play in higher leagues, by rating your performance entirely on whether you win or lose, get matched with crappy players over and over and you can drop entire ranks and theres nothing you can do about it. The loot system is one of the worst systems I've ever seen outside of iphone games where your forced to watch advertisements. Opening crates often taunts you with high powered items you cant have unless you pay for premium, and the only way to build a specific item is to sell your existing stuff for insignificant amounts of ingame currency. There is a massive lack of balance between the power and rarity of items. If a player refuses to pay money, they are forced into an endless pvp grind where their opponents will oftentimes have higher tier equipment that will win in nearly every fight.", "appid": "301520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198139595094", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1492430400.0} {"text": "NO! >:( Schon bei der Installation dieses \"Meisterwerks\" f√ºhlt man sich dumm, aber wenn man den Schrott erstmal spielt f√ºhlt man sich als h√§tte man einen IQ von -50000000000000. Die \"Story\" ist einfach nur M√ºll und kacke falls man es √ºberhaupt STORY nennen darf, dieses qualitativ hochwertige Produkt ist einfach nur D√úNNSCHISS, nachdem ich diesen Haufen M√ºll schmackhaft \"genossen\" habe musste ich nicht nur kotzen ich habe mich wie eine Bananenschale oder eine leere Kekspackung gef√ºhlt... nicht mal f√ºr 0‚Ç¨ w√ºrde ich es Spielen und die Errungenschaften sind h√§sslicher als das ganze Game.