 "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565524800.0} {"text": "used to love this game but now its all bots and hackers which makes it impossible to play", "appid": "274940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073952151", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1549972800.0} {"text": "I'm sorry to not recommend this game since the developer was kind enough to give me a review copy of it, but I just didn't enjoy it. The game is very much like Frozen Synapse, but with a soccer setting. The idea is pretty good and maybe could've worked if done differently. I'm not sure why but I find it boring to play, the graphics are just barely serviceable and the sounds seem taken from an old DOS game. Maybe it's because I hate soccer, but I had really no fun with it.", "appid": "453710", "steamid": "profiles/76561197997731390", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1517918400.0} {"text": "The game is great but here's why I am going to refund this game. Every time i get into open world there was always a slightest lag when I was running around doing some certain quest. I thought that was my graphic card issue but it was the online issue. I tried to do an offline mode but it's still connected to the internet by giving me the same problem. My next problem with this game is before i exit it was giving me a message saying i am unable to load a game. Bandai has not fixed this issue and never have. I tried to figure out why but it's simply telling me it can't? it wasn't suppose to show this message at first. They should have fixed it yet Bandai RUSHED the devs again and I am getting pissed off. Lastly, which is the most annoying thing when it comes on to exiting the game. My keyboard controls are messed up. Whenever i pressed certain buttons on the keyboards it keeps opening some other apps instead of typing a word on an address