ittle details on track and cars ( monitors around tracks, warning lights, tires wear?) Negatives - menu controls swaping in between the wheel buttons controls and keyboard button controls. No mouse :/ not a fan of that.( just as an example in ACC i can use my keyboard and mouse to control the menu and all options and then when i am on track i can also use wheel and keyboard in the same time widouth controls scheme swaping around) - BIG BIG Negative in this game are tracks. Some tracks have such weird look and weird corners that are nothing like IRL. For licenced game this is big no from me.. for a big company like Codemasters that they can not deliver laserscaned track is big dissapointment -FFB is horrible imho car and ffb feels weird driving on the wheel. I tried fiddling with the ffb settings improved it a bit but still feels weird. -Physics I just could not get it.. car starts loosing back you cant feel it on wheel. In the corner letting the car cruise feels like its getting artificialy slowed down turning in corners -watched graphics comparison videos from f1 2018 and 2019 only improvement was lighting and it looks good but all other textures in game are reduced quality. So with these couple of hours spent on the game over free weekend, doing some laps and as a huge fan of F1 i am glad i got to try this game out. But as a sim racer i would not buy it.", "appid": "928600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198063570798", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "26", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572782400.0} {"text": "The game is really fun and visually not that bad considering its from 2009, but can't really suggest getting it specially if you use a newer system constantly keeps crashing after I try to load a save file,did try to find solutions but cant really find anything helpful.", "appid": "10150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198379490128", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 15301008