they were on the right track with previous DLC which actually had a pretty decent story but it's one step forwards and two steps back with these devs. - Levels are pretty average, there are a couple with cool visual design but the rest are mediocre. - Boring loot, having completed all side-quests, I have all the unique loot and it's meh at best, the legendaries specific to DLC are also sub-par and I won't be using them in my builds. - Really boring side mission design, it's just more \"kill enemies in designated circle\" and \"fetch this\" crap, out of all side missions only stood out. - Extremely poor endgame content, previous DLC had a number of areas that can be farmed for specific drops, world drops and XP, there is very little of that here. The story bosses are all multi-stage crap design that can't be farmed efficiently and all chests I opened just had garbage in them, not a single legendary. - It is short and lacking in content compared to previous DLC and BL2 DLC. - Extremely annoying achievements that add nothing of value to the game.", "appid": "1232257", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006217347", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "34", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585310400.0} {"text": "Êõ¥Êñ∞‰∫ÜÈ©±Âä®Ëøò502ÔºåÂêÑÁßçÁé©‰∏ç‰∫Ü", "appid": "1097840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198100600500", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1569067200.0} {"text": "Probably most flawed of all quests designed by Tim Schaefer. Main story criplled by extremely shortiness, which leads to transformation of potentially great characters to unremarkable and blank sidekicks. The sole exception here is Ben Throttle, who had a lot of capacity to stand on par with Guybrush Threepwood and Manny Calavera, as another great hero of quest genre, but only affirms a fact, that such characters need a stong secondary support cast to uphold them. Aside from Ben, only garage rock music by The Gone Jackals (exceptionally fitting for blasting through apocalyptic road scenery) remains untouched by corrosion of time, and deserves listening on its own. Buy The Monkey Island or Grim Fandango instead.", "appid": "228360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198081897286", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1516536000.0} {"text": "Tek ruined the Game. Dino Survival with Transformers isnt fun. Game full of Dupers. Heavy Lag Issues since Alpha which will never be fixed. No DX12 Mode for Windows 10 for years.", "appid": "887380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066556018", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1541592000.0} {"text": "wuu", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198873418448", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545480000.0} {"text": "Sin dudas hoy en dia uno de los killers mas aburridos del juego, tanto como jugar con el o contra el. Yo se que la gran mayoria opina lo mismo", "appid": "971790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198217561141", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591358400.0} {"text": "Eine Warnung an alle Spieler. Dr√ºckt auf keinen Fall ESC. Ich habe mir das Intro gerade 10x angeschaut.", "appid": "234940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198042858126", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597060800.0} {"text": "car epic games", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198151278798", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557576000.0} {"text": "Probably The worst Total War game I have played out of them all, too basic and if you want more \"Gore\" They ask for money, what a joke", "appid": "779340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035548313", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "Pains me to give a bad review to the sequel of such a good game, but I don't enjoy Dishonored 2. The level design is too open, making it hard to stealth as I enjoyed in 1, leading to having to restart from checkpoint every few minutes. Also, its easy to get lost as it lacks linearity. Go get Dishonored 1 if you haven't already.", "appid": "403640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051039079", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498392000.0} {"text": "Don't make the same mistake I did, do not get this game on PC. Console is fine but this multiplayer is borderline unplayable and not fun at all. The story and zombies for PC is somewhat ok but multiplayer is difficult to even find anyone and its not fun at all.", "appid": "292730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091551521", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1478433600.0} {"text": "A hist√≥ria e os gr√°ficos s√£o pontos positivos, porem os bugs e todos os problemas que tiveram desde o lan√ßamento tiraram todo o brilho do que poderia ser o game do ano se a Ubisoft tivesse feito do jeito que deveria...", "appid": "289650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075109940", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1417521600.0} {"text": "Everything is good from combat to skins. The only ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• problem is the damn launcher !! For ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• sake fix that launcher, i can barely enter the game because the stupid launcher keeps closing itself and the play button keeps showing grey for hours,", "appid": "323370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198164556443", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1500120000.0} {"text": "Tja was soll ich sagen... CSGO halt Ich gab CSGO: -Liebe -Geld -Zeit CSGO gab mir: -hass gegen Russen, Polen, Franzosen und Russen -ein Kaputte Tast