 People are spamming noise, chats and links. So often disconnected from online session or getting errors.", "appid": "271590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079787805", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589025600.0} {"text": "Crash just deleted my save game twice, i lost around 2 hours progress. The fun fact is: This bug happened 3years ago and the dev didnt fix it", "appid": "409710", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076368396", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1587384000.0} {"text": "The unimpressive (by today's standards) graphics aside, it is the camera that ruined it for me. None of the angles seemed quite right, it responds slowly to player's movement and doesn't allow to rotate around at all. Maybe it would've benefited from some kind of \"spring mechanic\" where you change the angle with the joystick for a brief moment, then it returns to the default angle when you let go. Also the possibility to accurately choose the distance to the player model would've been nice.", "appid": "681280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060266670", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582891200.0} {"text": "Por lo general me gusta recomendar o no un juego al pasarme por lo menos su campa√±a principal pero hay veces en que un juego me resulta demasiado mon√≥tono y repetitivo, que termina por desesperarme y aburrirme demasiado que simplemente no puedo seguir jug√°ndolo y justamente eso consigue luego de un par de horas Tears of Avia. Siempre estoy pendiente de algunos rpg y juegos de estrategia que est√°n por salir, y este juego llamo mi atenci√≥n, obviamente no esperaba que me sorprendiera pero si algo decente al menos, pero por desgracia este titulo es realmente malo en varios aspectos sobre todo en el combate. Para empezar al comenzar el juego podremos elegir el personaje con el cual comenzar la aventura y luego tendremos un roster con otros 5 personajes para un total de 6 , aunque solo podremos llevar 5 a cada misi√≥n pero cada uno cada uno con un gran √°rbol de habilidades para desbloquear, y aqu√≠ es donde empiezan los problemas ya que tendremos 5 habilidades activas de nuestros personajes y otras 3 que nos proporciona el arma que se reducen a ataques, pero las habilidades b√°sicas de un juego por turnos como ser el overwatch o la postura defensiva no las tendremos, una decisi√≥n de dise√±o que en lo personal no me gusta para nada. Siguiendo con la parte del combate para resumirla en una palabra seria tosco, esto debido a unas pobres animaciones en todos los personajes en los movimientos y las habilidades especiales, y que por desgracia solo las animaciones de las habilidades permite saltar, adem√°s sum√°ndole que la mayor√≠a de los personajes tienen poca movilidad por el mapa en cada turno y con unos controles igual de malos sumado a su c√°mara que es demasiado lenta. Tambi√©n que el dise√±o de los escenarios en las bases creo que esta bien pero esto cambia mucho en los combate ya que se empiezan a repetir mucho, as√≠ como los enemigos que en un principio son bastante malos, para que luego el juego comience a amontonar muchos enemigos en el mapa para as√≠ tener algo de desaf√≠o, y para sumar al combo esta su banda sonora que en cada combate nos pone una melod√≠a lenta y nunca alguno que nos haga sentir una emoci√≥n en el combate. Otra cosa que pienso que esta muy mal planteado es el tema de la dificultad en el cual solo tendremos 2, una que es la est√°ndar y otra la hardcore, la primera sinceramente es completamente aburrida sin nada de desaf√≠o y que con que se avanza r√°pido en la historia, pero la segunda tambi√©n esta muy mal planteada ya que los enemigos obviamente aumentaran sus stats pero tambi√©n el escenario nos har√° un da√±o progresivo en cada turno a todos los personajes y que al final es ese da√±o es el que plantea el desaf√≠o porque los enemigos son igual de malos que en la normal. Sumando otra cosa mas a los malos dise√±os que tiene son los men√∫s que tiene, sobre todo el del inventario y las habilidades, muy mal organizados los 2 a la hora de ir cambiando los √≠tems no muestra de forma correcta las estad√≠sticas, el de las habilidades es muy poco intuitiva y no da una opci√≥n para organizar de manera r√°pida las mismas. Para terminar de describir este p√©simo juego tenemos su historia que la verdad no es la gran cosa y con unos personajes que resultan un poco carism√°ticos, pero el problema es que para avanzar algo hay que realizar muchas misiones consecutivas y cuando por fin aparece algo, esta se desarrolla demasiado r√°pido y que nos har√° perder el inter√©s demasiado r√°pido. Aunque a simple vista Tears of Avia puede resultar interesante, la realidad es que es un juego que corri√≥ con muchas decisiones de dise√±o que terminan por convertirlo en un juego bastante mediocre, sobre todo en el combate y que termina por parecer un early acces a medio hacer. Un juego de estrategia muy malo y no se lo recomiendo a nadie.", "appid": "461510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198129076118", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602849600.0} {"text": "muy malo, no tiene cloud, no hay ranking, se cuelga, no te deja abrirlo generalmente, no te reconoces los saves guardados, y no sacan una triste update casi nunca. sigan en el clicker heroes 1.", "appid": "629910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198062865770", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1554897600.0} {"text": "Good game but full of cheater..", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198884140890", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563710400.0} {"text": "M I C R O T R A N S A C T I O N S", "appid": "841370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033100962", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "51", "votes_funny": "17", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1550318400.0} {"text": "To be honest, it's a good game... only if you cut-out the \"Assassin's Creed\" part from it. Because this is sure as hell ain't an Assassin's Creed game. You want to make an open-world RPG with fantasy stuff on it? Great, go ahead and do it but for the love of all that is holy, A lot of stuff doesn't add up. Spoilers ahead, skip to Pros / Cons for a basic review. The Animus show you different stories / endings - it's just impossible. And there's a simulation inside a simulation which can also show you different stories based on your choices, you just can't do that with the Animus. Ubisoft should've just made a separate RPG game & kept the \"Assassin's Creed\" title far from it but let's poop on that logic, it's gonna generate money! Abstergo is already selling Animus to everyone - so any idiot with a little brain can discover whatever they want, all you need is the DNA of someone. New Animuses / Animi can use the DNA of anyone and is no longer limited to the user's DNA only. So, why the rest of the World doesn't know about The Hidden Ones / Assassins and Templars / Order of the Ancients / Cult of Kosmos / ? That broken spear of Leonidas only contained two blood samples? Pretty sure I've killed thousands of enemies with that spear. The protagonist only cuts herself / himself once, there's no way that blood is still on that spear after all this time. From the previous games, we know how powerful and resourceful the modern-day Templars are. Yet once they knew all about freaking they only sent 3 common soldiers without guns to investigate? Otso Berg killed Layla's best friend in the previous game. Layla has killed several people in the previous game, 3 soldiers in this game and her doctor as well. Yet she let Otso Berg live? Are you serious? He's one of the biggest leaders of the Templar order. And why did he came to Layla alone is beyond me, why is he fighting with a sword? Why not just shoot her and be done with it? Layla's last hit to Otso Berg looks extremely fatal, how on earth did he survive that? Mythical creatures, revisiting realms of afterlife at will, Isu machines speaking in English, enemies performing godly moves and you have godly abilities. Remember when Assassin's Creed used to be historically accurate? The goals of the modern day Assassins and Templars made sense? That franchise died with Desmond Miles. Since when and why are we calling \"Those who came before\" by the name \"Isu\"? The World was saved by Desmond's sacrifice, what's the point of using the Animus now? They're clearly not searching for any artifacts of Eden. The protagonist in the Animus confirms that their power can drain over time, so no point in going through all that trouble with the Animus to find some ancient piece of Eden that may or may not work. The reason why I'm focused more on the modern-day story is because you have to have a good enough reason to be in the Animus in the first place and I don't see any good reason to do that. The modern-day story is a complete mess and it's not going anywhere. Absolutely nothing happens when we finish the main story of the protagonist inside the Animus. We don't discover any artifacts that would help the Assassin in the ongoing battle against the Templars. It has become clear that Ubisoft has no idea what to do with the modern-day story-line and they don't seem to care enough to tie up loose ends. Instead, they're adding more characters to the story that we know nothing about and honestly I don't care about them. I didn't feel anything when Layla's best friend died in the previous game and her doctor's death in this game and one injured character - that's because I don't know much about them to care. Yet when Rebecca was shot a few titles back, I was desperate to see what happens next. I'm interested in finding out what happened to the previous characters such as Rebecca Crane, Shaun Hastings and William Miles. Those characters seemed to have been abandoned. Apart from the stinky poop that is the new modern-day and Isu stuff, the world of Greece is massive and beautiful, though most of the assets are from the previous game. But bigger doesn't always mean better. Maybe some people will like it, maybe some won't have the time to 100% everything. It took me a lot of time to finish up everything in the game but I encountered a bug with an engraving challenge, so I didn't get that satisfying feeling of completing everything because even though all quests, locations have been completed, there's one engraving challenge that's now impossible to complete. Maybe some completionists would know how annoying this can be. I pre-ordered the Ultimate Edition but I was shocked to see the number of premium content that are available for purchase using more money. Micro transactions in a single-player game is awful. I feel like I'm missing out. What's the point of purchasing the most expensive edition if I still have to buy more stuff to get everything the game has to offer? There is a way to get premium items for free but the process is worse than loot-boxes. + Gorgeous graphics and good soundtrack which fits various atmospheres. + Greece is really huge, there's a lot of things you can find that might surprise you. + Land adventures on foot or horse or even mythical creatures (act as cosmetics). + Sea and underwater adventure with customizable ship, its lieutenants and crew. + Tons of customization are available for your character and your preferred play-style. + Very realistic facial expressions, conversations feel natural. + So many quests! So many choices! So many outcomes! So many save slots! + You can bang quite a lot of NPCs without getting any ancient STDs. ! Requires a lot of time to complete everything, then there's the New Game+. ! Assassin's Creed game(?). ! Radiant quests for a never-ending adventure. ! Mythical mounts, ship items, crew can be obtained (they are cosmetics). ! Requires a lot of grinding before moving on to the next story related mission. - Poor modern-day story from the very beginning to the very end. - Uses about half of the game's assets from the previous game. - Isu story-line doesn't make much sense. - So many repetitive quests, even the dialogues of some quests are the same. - Very limited number of sea shanties compared to the previous titles which gets boring. - Mythical armor sets and ship lieutenants that can be purchased are not just cosmetics. - Lacks logic in most situations and basic common sense in some situations. - Micro-transactions in a single-player game. Question: How many Assassin's Creed games will you release before ending the series? Ubisoft: You have to visit Ubisoft's game booth at every gaming event and play all the games there. What's that? You live in the other side of the World? Well then.. no rewards for you! You have to participate in their Closed Alpha Tests, Open Alpha Tests, Closed Beta Tests, Open Beta Tests of their games. What's that? You weren't selected by them to be a tester? Well then... no rewards for you! You have to own several other Ubisoft games on the same account. What's that? You don't have the money and not interested in those other games? Well then... no rewards for you!", "appid": "812140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198063115240", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "60", "votes_funny": "37", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538740800.0} {"text": "This game is bad.", "appid": "204300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198524398906", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515758400.0} {"text": "I love point and click adventure games but what the heck did I just play? I admit I read some of the reviews and thought people were just making up everything that was said but nope now I understand. - Very short game over in like 10 minutes if that - Naked lizard people - Human kissing and tickling naked lizard woman and her child, yes AND her c