alse, "tstamp_created": 1466510400.0} {"text": "no, no, no AND AGAIN NO, this game is actually dead, first of all you can't play on official servers, MAYBE AT 4 AM, when there is nobody online because all the official servers are full, YEAH OF COURSE, and they made it free weekend, LIKE WTF, ok, ok, i was thinking that the modded servers will save it, OK, i watched some tutorials on youtube on how to install the mods, blah, blah, and i ended up installing all the mods, took me like 2 hours, 100 mods, some of them even 4-6 gb i opened the game... AND GUESS WHAT, AN ERROR, THAT I HAD MISSING FILE, i said ok, ok, i'll give it more chances... AFTER 250 MODS INSTALLED, GUESS WHAT? the modded servers are full had to wait in a queue of 100 people, i waited... same error. ok, so how do i start this, okay, i got into a good server, good ping, enough players and an official one, OK , no loot, like i'm for real, NOTHING, i'll say it again, NOTHING, and i get killed by an fully kitted guy, i said, OKAY,NEVER GIVE UP, so i try again, and finally i FIND SOME GOOD STUFF, like a shotgun and a decent backpack, a zombie comes near me so i attack him i hit him 2 time, BOOM FREEZE, couldn't do ANYTHING, I LOCKED MY PC THE PICTURE OF THE GAME WAS STILL THERE FROZEN, so i said, ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• IT... I UNINSTALLED THE GAME, ALL THE MODS, and now i'm writing this review, not for other people to see, BUT FOR ME TO NEVER BUY THIS TRASH GAME THAT HAS BEEN IN ALPHA FOR 7 YEARS, DAMN IT.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198327508005", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581681600.0} {"text": "Âà´ÁöÑËøòÂèØ‰ª•ÔºåÂ∞±ÊòØÊ∏∏ÊàèÁîªË¥®Â§™Ê®°Á≥ä‰∫ÜÔºÅÔºÅ", "appid": "1195460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198373068149", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581940800.0} {"text": "Nicht ohne Grund schlechter als BATTLEGROUNDS :D , was macht das Spiel nur Ausgeglichen? Alles was BATTLEGROUNDS besser macht ^^ , sch√§tze das dadurch dieses Spiel nie den Early Access Status verl√§sst und kann daher nur abraten dieses Spiel zu kaufen. 30 Euro sind zwar derzeit VIEL zu viel f√ºr BATTLEGROUNDS aber lieber dort ein bisschen warten bis es mal im Sale ist (oder fertig ... ^^) als wie sich jetzt noch dieses Spiel zu holen was ja eh bereits abgel√∂st wurde (siehe zb. Twitsch und co.) Wer dieses Spiel jedoch bereits besitzt soll es ruhig solang spielen eh der Sale f√ºr die bessere Version eingetroffen ist , zum Zeitvertreib ;) Aber wie gesagt da es sich JETZT nicht mehr lohnt zu kaufen ein negatives Review von mir.", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021004053", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1492171200.0} {"text": "I have mixed feelings about this game. The game can be an enjoyable WWII FPS experience. However, there are several major items that cause the my friends and I to play other games in lieu of HLL on many occasions. 1) Most notably is the requirement that you stay the whole match to get any experience. When you start a match, you're committed to the whole ride. I don't know about your schedules, but I don't have 1+ hours stretches to commit. After playing for a bit, getting 30 kills, knocking out a few garrisons and ops... it really leaves a foul taste your mouth knowing you'll have to get off and have none of it count toward your character progression. Oh, and If you're unlucky and it's your turn to crash, which happens often enough, say \"goodbye\" to your progression. A lot of players, myself included would really like the developers to change this. 2) The server browser is lackluster to put it mildly. Why can't we have filters where we can set an upper limit on ping, upper and lower limits on player count, select gamemode type, and have a list displayed of those servers? 3) Server Queuing. What is the deal with this? When the server list shows 85/100 players with 6/6 players in the queue... put them in the server already? Why isn't the queue when the server is full? Today, I waited in the queue several minutes to get into a server, when presented with the team selection screen, I find myself presented with player count on each time something like 42v42. Why the hell did I sit here and wait for 5 minutes to get in? There were 16 player spots available on the server. This is just irritating, especially when gaming time is a luxury. If the developers could change those things, it would certainly alleviate my annoyance with the game. I have a good enough time playing the game. The performance isn't too bad, graphics look pretty good, the game play pacing is good, the map size is just right, and finally the map development is pretty good with the environment feeling believable and conductive to good firefights. If you're cash strapped and wondering if you should get the game right now, I say... No, wait to see if the developers fix the above items. If you have plenty of time, cash, and WWII games are your thing, I say... maybe. Overall rating - 6.5/10 Rating if they fix issues noted above - 8.5/10", "appid": "686810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019696269", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1596974400.0} {"text": "It would be a nice game if more people would be playing it and better optimization But overall it's garbage", "appid": "701830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198393486038", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1506081600.0} {"text": "The game fails miserably at shocking you with its god-awful dialogue and bland gameplay. The shooting is weightless and unresponsive, and the game loses any kind of steam after around 5 minutes of playing. At least ramming cars into buildings is pretty fun.", "appid": "341940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113066921", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_ac