1198257191105", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599048000.0} {"text": "As a concept, the game is good... Now lets just actually discuss the game shall we? Softlocks the game is a first person Horror game with a plot that is somewhat so-so (Its understandable, but predictable), letting you explore a forest full of collision problems. If you buy this game, follow the paths, don't try to explore, weird right? you'd like trying to explore would help you find some hidden secrets? Or... Risk long sections of gameplay you've done just to get stuck on that Rock, Log, Small slope that looks traverseable and having to force a reset of the game, LOSING that progress (where most of my hours come from) Now, length, don't expect a long time if you avoided the dastardly hazards which are softlocks, because this game can span (In a long play session) roughly 3.5 - 4.0 hours, so if you think ¬£24.99 (or whatever currency you use) is worth 4 hours of gameplay? then this would be the game for you. As of writing this i'm currently trying to get a refund, knowing my luck they will say \"No, you should have known this game was incomplete when buying\".", "appid": "1092660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198048533035", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1567252800.0} {"text": "–∫–∞–ª", "appid": "113400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198314112846", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "many hack", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198192823363", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530014400.0} {"text": "Its the funniest game of my life i have ever seen .The game was awful .", "appid": "844870", "steamid": "profiles/76561199022409765", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1580558400.0} {"text": "bad poopy game", "appid": "242760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198168192711", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525521600.0} {"text": "If this Store Page was honest! Primal: $extinction is a class-based online roleplay featuring humans & dinosaurs A class-based online multiplayer shooter unlike any other, oh yeah we're so focused on other things besides that, we forgot it was suppose to be a shooter to begin with. We'll get on to the other things in a bit, but let's talk about the near non-existant PVP. Primal: $extinction features awkward paced aimless movie bad guys versus over-sized chickens moving around with their heads cut off, combat! <- yes, we and our fans consider this \"Fun & Balanced\" combat! Will you hunt down human prey as a variety of legendary prehistoric creatures? yes, because trying to play the humans is the equivalent of trying to shoot a cheetah while your drunk & dizzy while riding a pogo stick. Yet our Dinosaur features aren't much better. Unleash your inner rage as you try to take control of dinosaurs stiffer than a guy who worked out at the gym for 3 hours yesterday when he hasn't exercised in months. Choose from 10 unique dinosaur classes, only to end up playing 3 (Nova/Dilo/Ovi) cause the other 7 can't do jack s**t. Survive the island as one of the 5 distinct human classes, each with thier own special abilities to help the te- sorry we couldn't keep a straight face there. Take on your scaley foes with an aresenal of devastating wea- okay we're done here. *A Wasteland filled with trolls & horny kids/teens that have almost taken over the whole game, Roleplay. *A Broken Dino v. Dino mode that's more duable than our Human v. Dino PVP. *A Survival that isn't needed right now and makes Orion look good. *And everyones favorite, Search & Find! scroll through a bottomless list of servers where you desperately try to find a populated TDM or GTTC server with fair ping! Honestly, we tried adding more maps, but everyone wants Docks & Contingency. Aw yes, the real gem of our game, since Early Access we put most of our time & effort into an economy that people still whine about to this day. This is how we often forget about the shooting elements as we still continue to improve the economy and flesh it out with content that isn't really needed right now, but our fans still love it, heck even they forget the shooting elements as well! We have big plans for how to evolve Primal: $extinction, except areas which we were suppose to improve upon from the original since Early Access, but we've since then dropped that goal and wish to please our current fans. To see our roadmap of upcoming content and progress of fixing and adding bugs, check out our Trello organization! don't forget to buy those skins, it's really whats keeping our game alive right now rather than actual game sales and gameplay appeal. Wait wasn't this suppose to be called Primal Carnage: Extinction? oh right, cause we put so little focus on improving what made the original game so good, there's barely any Carnage to enjoy!! we might not be too far off from extinction though ...", "appid": "321360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198037249537", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "133", "votes_funny": "102", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1436875200.0} {"text": "(Review text hidden)", "appid": "1034200", "steamid": "profiles/76561198161000134", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1553342400.0} {"text": "deƒümez", "appid": "577800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198284345893", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533211200.0} {"text": "#IWantMyGems", "appid": "601510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198215428207", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531742400.0} {"text": "This game is fully of bugs!!!