alse, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1501761600.0} {"text": "pushed off bridge", "appid": "629760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076235662", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0} {"text": "–ë—ã—Å—Ç—Ä–æ –Ω–∞–¥–æ–µ–¥–∞–µ—Ç. –ë–∞–ª–∞–Ω—Å –ø–ª–∞—Ö–æ–π –≤—Å–µ–≤—Ä–µ–º—è –æ–¥–Ω–∏ –∏ —Ç–µ–∂–µ –¥–µ–π—Å—Ç–≤–∏—è.....–∑–∞–¥—Ä–æ—Ç–Ω–æ.", "appid": "645630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198285798547", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572868800.0} {"text": "I've been playing this game since the day it came out. It was supposed to be a remaster of Contract Wars, Absolutsoft's browser fps. And it was just that, for a while -- A balanced and fun shooter with a less arcadey feel than most other fps games that I've played. However, the game was super buggy, and it died quickly since it was a paid game, while Contract Wars was f2p. Fast forward 3 years, and the game has been \"\"remade\"\" several times, each straying further and further from what made Contract Wars so great. Now, we have a generic, buggy, and unbalanced game that is now arcadey in all the wrong places, while still retaining features that shouldn't be in an arcade fps. This game might be fun for a dozen hours, but as a veteran who only has access to high level servers, the game is overriden by people who abuse OP weapons and attachments, and know exactly where to camp on every level, so that the conquest game mode is unwinnable for one of the teams. If you live in North America, have fun playing on 200 ping servers as you get sniped from behind walls. 4/10. ps, they've been ignoring the feedback from non russians, such as myself, although me and a few other people have put in 300+ hours and know what this game needs more than most of the other players.", "appid": "374280", "steamid": "profiles/76561198326898712", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1",