alse, "tstamp_created": 1463659200.0} {"text": "Alright, I've been playing a fair bit (Level 11) and so far I can say this is not worth $40, it's a fun game in any case though especially with friends but the amount of waiting time to find a 400 MS game is ridiculous, by the looks of it there are no Australian servers so it just matches you with global players. Now this would be fine if it didn't take 10 minutes to find a game. For a $40 game you'd expect quality but it looks like they rushed out to finish this game without putting any hard work in. The facial expressions are absolute rubbish along with interaction with items (DOORS). Notice how in the intro's rather than create a variety of player models to get killed it's always that one guy for any level. Like I said this game is fun but it doesn't have a lot of replayability and it does not have the servers. This review would be different if the game was say $20 but I've had meals at McDonalds more satisfying than this game for $40 Edit: People are pointing out that the server issue has been resolved but even then my other points still stand. Thanks and God bless", "appid": "438740", "steamid": "profiles/76561197993464221", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "209", "votes_funny": "16", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1495800000.0} {"text": "I literally just stopped mid game to say that this game is actual hot garbage. The theory is orbit around a black hole as many times as you can while avoiding incoming obstacles. Decent idea with trash implementation. Once you get up around 50ish orbits all of a sudden RNG kicks in and instantly reverses your direction directly into the cloud of objects you just avoided ending the round. Then lets say you actually do well on the reversal ... then they throw in double reversals ... either way you're ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• by RNG. Game is good for nothing but farming achievements.", "appid": "615610", "steamid": "profiles/76561197967473096", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1523016000.0} {"text": "Ficou p√©ssimo.", "appid": "252950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198111074255", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605787200.0} {"text": "Loads came crashes :D 69/666", "appid": "311210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198119421902", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1446811200.0} {"text": "writing this for a badge", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198096242806", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1479902400.0} {"text": "Das Schlechteste race game was ich je gesehen habe", "appid": "310560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198154762971", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1495281600.0} {"text": "fix it on win 10", "appid": "413150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198123316139", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561550400.0} {"text": "I remember playing this game and having a great amount of fun. Then I got some other games and stopped playing this game for probably a year. I just downloaded the game again and they have ruined it. It is not as good as it used to be. I recommend if you are a old player and want to start playing this game again, Don't do it! It is not worth the time.", "appid": "209870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061702323", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1448539200.0} {"text": "Hayatta kalma oyunu seven insanlara tavsiye edeceƒüim ilk oyunlarƒ±n ba≈üƒ±nda gelir, oyun genel olarak g√ºzel fakat bir s√ºre oynadƒ±ƒüƒ±nƒ±z zaman sizi sƒ±kabiliyor a√ßƒ±k√ßasƒ± bu t√ºr√ºn pek hayranƒ± sayƒ±lmam. Grafikler g√ºzel, detaylara fazla takƒ±lmazsanƒ±z oyunu rahatlƒ±kla oynayabilirsiniz. Oyunda deƒüinmek istediƒüim bir diƒüer konu ise \"BUG\" olacaktƒ±r, oyunda √ßok fazla sayƒ±da bug ile kar≈üƒ±la≈üƒ±yorsunuz hatta s√∂yle s√∂yleyeyim kar≈üƒ±la≈ümama ihtimaliniz yok o derece, bu detaylar dƒ±≈üƒ±nda oyun akƒ±cƒ± fakat yazƒ±mƒ±n ba≈üƒ±nda da belirttiƒüim gibi oyun √ßok sƒ±kƒ±yor. Oyunu arkada≈ülarƒ±nƒ±zla oynamanƒ±zƒ± √∂neririm eƒüer tek ki≈üi oynarsanƒ±z oyun sizi √ßok bayacak ve direk bƒ±rakacaksƒ±nƒ±z, incelemeyi bitirirken son bir not daha eklemek istiyorum. Ben bu t√ºr√ºn pek hayranƒ± deƒüilim, bu t√ºrdeki diƒüer oyunlarƒ± da oynadƒ±m fakat benlik deƒüil, o y√ºzden oyunu olumsuz olarak i≈üaretliyorum ≈üayet siz bu t√ºr√º severseniz tam sizlik oyun diyebilirim.", "appid": "242760", "steamid": "profiles/76561198353790299", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1585224000.0} {"text": "Dead game", "appid": "686600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198055125568", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1549886400.0} {"text": "I rarely don't finish a story-driven single player game. I actually can't even remember when the last time was, because I usually find something to enjoy no matter the amount of drawbacks. That is not the case with Deus Ex: Mankind Divided. This steaming heap of boredom is probably one of the most forgettable experiences I've ever found myself trying to enjoy. That says something, because I've read \"To Kill A Mockingbird\" AND \"Catcher in The Rye\". Deus Ex: Mankind Divided isn't a bad game. The mechanics are rather enjoyable, the views are sometimes amazing, the prologue reminded me a great deal of Spec Ops: The line's main setting in Dubai, and it was very beautiful. There were a lot of throwbacks to earlier DX-games, and everything feels like it should make for a very enjoyable experience. However! This is where I try to explain why I find this game so horrible. First of all: Every person the player meets feels like they've been written by an 8 year old with a bog-standard character creation sheet from a D&D-session. It just feels like every reply is formulated, every line is taken out of some sort of matrix of the most stereotypical replies to pressure, taunting, niceties, etc. It's just boring. Bland. Annoying in the end. I never felt like I was in the story for any other reason than its own progression, and that does not a satisfied player make. At least not this player. The locations were (until my early out-bowing) very well-made, although they did feel slightly down-scaled. I found myself constantly trying to sneak around like I always do, but it didn't feel as rewarding as it did in Human Revolution. Again, I just couldn't shake the feeling of me only being around for the story to progress. I didn't sit around thinking \"‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• yeah, I'm gonna save the world here\", there was no feeling of imminence or importance. Just a feeling of \"meh\". To sum it all up. I didn't enjoy the game. I didn't wake up Saturday morning thinking only about playing on and seeing where the story took me. I just felt like replaying a good game instead. Sad. TL;DR: Don't buy this game if you expect good writing.", "appid": "337000", "steamid": "profiles/76561198014713184", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1518350400.0} {"text": "Such a lack of content...", "appid": "868380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198847762623", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589716800.0} {"text": "Repleto de gente toxica...", "appid": "550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198310568367", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525348800.0} {"text": "–ö–∞–∂–¥—É—é –∏–≥—Ä—É –¥–æ—Å—Ç–∞—é—Ç—Å—è –æ—Ä–∫–∏...", "appid": "1416260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084128932", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604491200.0} {"text": "–ü–æ —Ç—