cht Spa√ü f√ºr ein paar Stunden doch bittet auf dauer keine Langzeit Motivation und ist sehr unfair. Positiv: -Es gibt viele Waffen -Man kann Autos tunnen -Gro√üe Welt - Man kann seine eigenen Klamotten designen Negativ: -Zu viele Hacker -Unfaires Ballance in der Spielwelt -Ohne Premium schafft man so gut wie gar nichts - Das Spiel ben√∂tigt viel zu starke Hardware um √ºberhaupt fl√ºssig zu laufen. Fazit: Es bittet f√ºr ein paar Stunden eine nette Unterhaltung besonders wenn man es mit freunden spielt doch die Hacker die unfaire Ballance und die ben√∂tigte Hardware rauben einem doch sehr denn Spielspa√ü.", "appid": "113400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135849745", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1464523200.0} {"text": "1 haftaya sƒ±kƒ±lƒ±rsƒ±nƒ±z", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198274698450", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586174400.0} {"text": "‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• game! i unlock cards and uninstall this ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•", "appid": "4920", "steamid": "profiles/76561197967886318", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1386244800.0} {"text": "Not so fun", "appid": "703080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198097101173", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576152000.0} {"text": "–ù–µ—Ç. –°–ø–∞—Å–∏–±–æ alienware arena –∑–∞ –±–µ—Å–ø–ª–∞—Ç–Ω—ã–π –∫–ª—é—á.", "appid": "375230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198273342892", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1489492800.0} {"text": "Immortal Realms: Vampire Wars, the RANT review: Having played the beta for over 20 hours (i had to push myself tbh) it already was clear that this game would fall short. The concept is nice tho, i won't deny it, but the execution is very poorly done to say the least! (they basically left the beta running for over 6 months while changing little to nothing, how or why one does that goes beyond my comprehension?) This game tries so hard but delivers little, making it look, act and feel underqualified & unpolished in pretty much all aspects. (confirmed: missing card mechanics, disappearing units, corrupted save/load files, etc..) It has choppy/glitchy motion & user interfaces, little to no real strategic values, bland and boring maps, not to mention the severe lack of diversity for 'terrain & cover systems' and whatnot (which does practically nothing for archer/ranged types). Unit types that are not offering much, except some basic stats like buffs & boons even on highest tier and leveling them up should also have been made more transparent. Terrible story, bad acting, uninspiring voices (grunting and moaning basically) low quality FMV, mindless plot,.. Boring!! (Ooh, i would almost forget to mention about the awkward camera movement or functionality.. It's as if you're always mistaking left from right by the simplest of actions!) The battle maps pretty much all look the same really, they're way too small, feel overly cramped, are full of stupid choke points to get bogged into, and offer practically zero contribution to the trategic value of the game (in other words, potential wasted).. It's also worth mentioning that whenever an enemy lord plays a card, you need to focus in quickly or miss it, leaving you wondering what he/she actually played?! The soundtrack (strong point) and overall visuals aren't bad, i'll give them that. But as the game stands now, there's plenty of patching and polishing up to do in order to make things look, feel and behave like it should because my impression is that at some time during the development they ran out of steam (or didn't even care to read our comments) and decided to just leave it at that. This concludes my rant for now but no doubt i'll be back after delving longer into this abyss of boredom and bugginess.. Personal verdict: 6'5/10 (generously overrated) Not recommended for the current asking price!! Ps: Launch day was horrible (missing dlcs etc)!!", "appid": "1024480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198029242857", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598788800.0} {"text": "–ø–æ–∫–∞ –∑–∞–π–¥–µ—à—å –≤ –∏–≥—Ä—É —É–º—Ä–µ—à—å –æ—Ç —Å—Ç–∞—Ä–æ—Å—Ç–∏ —É –º–µ–Ω—è gtx 1050 ti –∏ –ø—Ä–æ—Ü I5 8300 2.3 –≥—Ä—Ü 8 –æ–ø–µ—Ä–∞—Ç–∏–≤—ã . –∑–∞—Ö–æ–∂—É –≤ –∏–≥—Ä—É 15 –º–∏–Ω –Ω–∞ —Å–µ—Ä–≤–µ—Ä 30 –º–∏–Ω . –ö—Ä—É—Ç–∞—è –∏–≥—Ä–∞", "appid": "252490", "steamid": "profiles/76561198813045982", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563796800.0} {"text": "+ Ze zaƒç√°tku docela z√°bavn√° hra, memes pobav√≠ + Sbƒõratelsk√© kartiƒçky, 15 achievement≈Ø - Velmi lacin√Ω \"p≈ô√≠bƒõh\", jeho 30 levl≈Ø jsem dohr√°l za 2 hodiny - Cel√Ω proces se zaƒçnƒõ opakovat a je to dost nuda - Achivement s 5000 bramborami jsem dƒõlal 4/6 nahran√Ωch hodin a jsem r√°d, ≈æe m≈Ø≈æu hru po tom nudn√©m a vyƒçerp√°vaj√≠c√≠m v√Ωkonu oddinstalovat Na des√≠tky minut zabav√≠, ale v√≠c nic. 4/10", "appid": "554310", "steamid": "profiles/76561198134125222", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1522670400.0} {"text": "Things that happened since 2013: - My mother's uncle died from Chronic Obtructive Pulmonary Disease. - My cousin's wife gave birth to NOT ONE BUT BUT TWO CHILDREN NOPE NOT AT A SINGLE BIRTH! - My other cousin got over her cocaine addiction. - Leonardo Da Vinci won the oscars. *cough* Caprio. - I graduated from highschool and I'm two years into university. - A military coup happened in my country, as well 5 different elections. Meh that's my country's unstability but whatever. - My brother got through 2 relationships. - Trump became the president of United States. - Brexit. - I spent 1200 hours playing this game with unbearable bugs and glitches. - Learned how to play the piano. - Malaysian aircraft accident. - We get to see J. Lawrance's nudes. - Bieber got arrested. - Ebola epidemic ended. - Same sex marriage became a thing in the USA. - Paris climate agreement. - New Star Wars film. - Autonomous cars became mainstream. - Giant pandas are no longer endangered. - Netflix added offline downloads BUT THIS GAME IS STILL NOT ON BETA. WHAT THE HELL. edit: Wow, so much hate coming in, the comment section is full with people telling me that I don't know how game development works. At Slumdog Millionaire movie, there's this scene where a rich guy gives a bottle of coke to some poor Indian kids living in poverty. These kids are so happy because they've never drunk coke before. You can make poor people happy with small things, because by default they are poor so their needs are obviously much less than a regular person. The regular DayZ player plays DayZ in poverty as well, a poverty of updates. This is how Bohemia keeps their players \"happy\", they give us small updates. Updates which take 6 months to finish and don't bring much new things to the game.. I was also one of these people. Bohemia sold 2.5million or maybe even more copies for this game. That's more than $60 million. They promised us Beta on 2015 Q4, we didn't get it. They said they wanted to change the game engine, it took their full year. They said the game will be on Play Station, but that's nowhere to be heard. They said they'll add basebuilding 2 years ago, it's not here. They said they'll add injury system, blood on hands when you skin an animal/human. Pooping, marijuana smoking, making the altar radio station fully fledged. Helicopters, bikes, motorbikes, car functioning and maintenance, full damage system for vehicles, stamina and endurance, realistic animal AI. They added wolves, but they can do 180 degree spins while you're running from them. They said they'll make all building floors enterable, they said they'll put vegetation all around the walls of the buildings. They said they will make the Tisy military base contaminated. They said they'll improve zombie AI. They said they'll add zombie hoardes, where are they? Where's the character soft skills? Where's the planes? Character lifespan? Visible scars? They promised us the player controller and new animation system to come around the summer of 2016 or the end 2017, but they still didn't implement it yet. Improved crafting system that allowed us to live off our lives in the wild WITHOUT visiting the cities etc. If I want to pitch a tent, I still need to run around the forest to find a place that both my character can fit in and put a tent. They promised a new tent placement system (link here: ) they said they'll add it in 3 months. They didn't. Here in the Trello you can see what they have in \"progress\" with the exact dates they've been added and have an overall idea what I'm talking about: The list goes on. You can see their old status reports here: please scroll all the way down to 2015 era and see what they promised to us. I'm an experienced DayZ player, I both played SA and topped lots of hours of play on the mod. Sure, this is a fun game. But I don't recommend it to any friend that asks me. If you're not patient as much as I am, this game is not for you. I still play this time to time, but let's be honest. An open alpha game, that made a revenue of 60million, a huge company like Bohemia, can't complete the alpha stage prior to its release, IN 3.5 YEARS? There's something wrong there. Maybe it was Dean Hall, maybe it's with the dev team. But you can clearly say something is wrong there. People are telling me that Beta is soon, you should take a look at the status reports that said beta was soon, around 189318 million times before. I remember them saying on twitter that they don't want to rush beta, so it will be on version 0.81 (current version is 0.62 and they said 0.63 will be beta) We've never been this close to beta before.They said it will be soon, by soon they probably mean 2036 or something. Considering we are not hit by an astreoid by then. lol. If they hit \"beta\" with the current speed they are developing, it is possible that they'll either release an incomplete game and continue developing after the full release, which is probably okay for most people. Or the game will take another 3 years to complete. edit 2: ohh btw, I just remembered. There's another excuse they say, \"alpha is for adding features you dumb ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•\" Very good point. Where are the features that they were supposed to add on Alpha? Will they add them all on Beta? Alpha means adding features, Beta is where these features are improved and the bugs are fixed. If they don't add the features they promised on Alpha then they'll continue adding these core features in the Beta phase which means then we'll be likely to see an Alpha-like Beta. Where they continue adding the features they promised years ago. Finally, I hope I'm wrong with all this and the DayZ dev team steps up their game. If they do, I'll surely delete this review.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198010837586", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "979", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1496318400.0} {"text": "Not worth the money. Buy PUBG instead", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198234519816", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1511438400.0} {"text": "Sadly the PC community is dead in this game. If you really want to enjoy this game go to PS4/Xbox. P2P which means MasterMinds (MM) abusing Lag Switch. Many MANY cheaters, as if infinite grenades, molotovs, energy to spam creatures. The balance is not that great and Matchmaking doesn't make it better. For example a lvl 2 Annete (first MasterMind) against full premade of 4 people that are 50+ lvls. There are 200-400 people playing daily a couple are newbies and most are abusing any explots. (Even RE 5 Mercenaries has more people playing) The devs won't add any anticheat or servers so this game will eventually die in the PC community. Was fun until it lasted. Maybe there will be a new peak when something new appear, it happened when Nic was added, but that peak lasted for a few hours.", "appid": "952070", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972766048", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594382400.0} {"text": "—ç—Ç–æ –∏–≥—Ä–∞ –Ω–µ –¥–ª—è –º–µ–Ω—è", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198080915448", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1458475200.0} {"text": "MMORPG with guns that means your gun is weak and fast reflexes are useless in this game", "appid": "1085660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198058230907", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1570708800.0} {"text": "–ì0BHO", "appid": "1046930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198201187469", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1561896000.0} {"text": "-The scariest thing about this game is the graphics. This game may look good if you watch the trailer but be warned it is nothing like that. You may only play 3 PvE matches a day unless you pay although after playing 3 you will be glad you don¬¥t have to play another; the graphics look like they are from 2007 and the voice acting is awful. You will be forced on to the repetitive team deathmatch games within 20 mins of gameplay. Another problem with this game is that it falls within the pay to win side of free games; most of the wepons are locked to premium money only. You will constantly find yourself getting your ass kicked by the people who have payed for better gear. Despite all the bad things about this game you can still get some fun out of mele matches which fall under the so bad its good catagory for me and the mutation matches which are satisfying as long as you are one of the mutants. As much as I hate this game at least it is free and for a free game it does have good production value; most of the free games I have played do not have a story line and as rubbishy as this ones is at least it tries. I would not recomend this game although I do respect the people who made it for at least trying to give it some sort of story instead of just having the generic multipayer fps. I would rate it at 4.5/10.", "appid": "223650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198079407131", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "60", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1418644800.0} {"text": "nosense", "appid": "204340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198277785200", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498219200.0} {"text": "Pior killer j√° lan√ßado, n√£o vale 1 real.", "appid": "971790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083542059", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": "16", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544788800.0} {"text": "ga zeeb", "appid": "335330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198130722771", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1498737600.0} {"text": "PUBG 2020 experience: cheater after killing me said to me in voice chat \"‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• you\"", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198145644913", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596715200.0} {"text": "R.i.P.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561197987672934", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544356800.0} {"text": "Rimworld's just better. The community around this game also seems... toxic, for lack of a better word. I made a single post on the community forums and seemed to be met with hostile responses. Not a good sign. It just seems to be a rip-off of rimworld, with worse graphics and even more lacking gameplay.", "appid": "457140", "steamid": "profiles/76561198087883181", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1552132800.0} {"text": "You know I was quite enjoying the game, despite the annoying \"open world\" wich itself was a puzzle to get to the next mission, poor voice acting and some other things. I do not recommend this game because I was about to finish the game but at one point I ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• up and I died, so I loaded at the latest checkpoint but then the mysterious bug appeared so I couldn't move at all and controls didn't work. I wasn't feeling like playing through the whole chapter again so I just quit. If you want you can still get it since it is very cheap and you will probably not come across this bug yourself. So I'm justl little salty that ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• happened to me. The Idea of thief is really cool and unique.", "appid": "239160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198340138163", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1546430400.0} {"text": "This is a tough game for me to recommmend, would love it there was a 'Neutral' button on Steam. It's beautiful and the music is amazing, but the game feels shallow. The ending is nice, but it comes after slowly walking for 90+ minutes. The last chapter feels most enjoyable, I'm not sure who would want to play through the first two though to get to that point honestly. Suggestions for improvement - Keep the user engaged more consistently through the narrartion. More talking, even if it's minor thoughts. - Interactions. Something to feel like you're actually engaged in the world - Make it more linear, if the point is pushing the story forward and the are no 'Easter Eggs' or 'rewards' for exploring make it so someone can't 'Get Lost' - Subtitles - Could be more interesting, could be used as typograhic art that scrolls or changes in size and font to fit the mood. They felt drab and did little for immersion, so I turned them off - Abilty to walk faster...jog even. Less of an issue if it was more linear, but going 'The wrong Way' then back tracking is tiresome here - Camera: Make more dynamic, small bobbing as the character walks", "appid": "203810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035396704", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1416744000.0} {"text": "This game have potential and great community, but the lag and fps problems are so annoying. a lot of bugs too and the world feels repeated same creatures on every island and no interesting stuff to explore after. Overall needs more work and more quality of life updates and weekly updates.", "appid": "834910", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075848428", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1572955200.0} {"text": "Disgusting how they split the game in half. It's a clear cash grab and exploition of their customer base.", "appid": "295110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198074785120", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1456056000.0} {"text": "--- --- +Good progress system +Peaceful ambiance +Beautiful scenery --- --- +Buggy +Unpolished +Bad tutorial --- --- Dark forester brings you into your own peaceful forest to build and defend against waves of baddies in a sort of tower defense/rogue-like/rpg mix of engaging gameplay, leaving the player to build, protect and farm their way to greatness. --- --- : Simple, most comparable to ARPG's. Right click to move, 1-5 to use magic, tab to attack. You can edit the inputs if needed. Very basic. : The mechanics are the most interesting part of this game. There is an open forest and the player can build wherever they would like, except on the very border of the map. While progressing, more buildings unlock and there are more units to place but it's limited by your level as well. In between waves of the PvE element of the game the player can choose to attack other players for resources which is almost a must because the waves of PvE monsters become increasingly difficult. That's basically it. Build, then defend or attack and keep building. : The game makes itself seem much more difficult than it is by including an overly lengthy tutorial in one huge mouthful rather than splitting it into spots when necessary. After you get a hang of what's going on, the game is very simple to the point of boring before increasing in difficulty again as waves increase. : Progression is just like your basic RPG game. You gain xp and resources, level up with xp and build with resources. It seems fairly balanced as long as you're attacking other players as well as defending your base. However, if the character dies or the main house is destroyed, progression is brought back a few levels or in some cases all the way back to the level 1, giving the game a very tense, rogue-like feel to it. --- --- : The environment is nice and is set in an autumn forest leaving the player in a lush world of orange and brown that really feels quite peaceful. : The player and monster models feel quite aged and plain, nothing to really talk about here and about what one expects from an indie game like this, if not just a tiny bit better than one would expect. : There's not much for animations while fighting but I found that the death animation was pretty cool, although they felt out of place, with explosions and lightning effects. : The user interface is pretty bad. Filled with unnecessary clutter.When you click on your monster it brings up a huge window that's mostly empty, the building ui doesn't disappear during the combat phase leaving a large black bar down the side of the screen. --- --- : Bugs are abundant in this game everywhere. From buildings randomly disappearing, to poor save states leading to game restarts, game crashes, hefty and unstable loading times and many more. The game is barely playable in its current state and only so if you're willing to run the risk of a complete restart on your progress. : The game runs well on max graphics for me, I don't experience any lag or stutter and it runs smooth. As mentioned under bugs however, the loading times can be long and even a couple of times the game just refused to load for me and resulted in a corrupt save state. --- --- : If the bugs were taken care of and the was less of a risk of a corrupt save, this game would have a great amount of replay value. It seems to stretch on quite far, but starts to feel like a grind fairly quickly, having to keep your resources up from attacking other players, many of whom are at base level with no defense. : I, personally, would not be happy with purchasing this game for 15$ in its current state. I see many people get it on sale or from when it was on early access for less than a dollar and I feel that's a fantastic value for what you're getting. However, even if the game was in a pristine state, polished and bug free, I don't feel like 15$ is a good value without the addition of much more content. I'd value the game in it's current state at under 5$. --- --- Overall, the game seems to be very interesting with loads of replay value and is a great concept, however all of that is overlooked by the bugs, horrible tutorial, and a poorly designed user UI. I understand the dev is still hard at work making improvements so definitely keep an eye out for improvements to the game in the future, if nothing else, I can surely say that this game is worth following and keeping on your indie radar. --- --- \t\tCPU \t\t\tIntel Core i5 @ 3.60GHz \t\t\tCoffee Lake 14nm Technology \t\tRAM \t\t\t16.0GB Dual-Channel Unknown @ 1066MHz (15-15-15-36) \t\tMotherboard \t\t\tMicro-Star International Co. Ltd. Z370-A PRO (MS-7B48) (U3E1)\t \t\tGraphics \t\t\tASUS VG236 (1920x1080@60Hz) \t\t\t4095MB NVIDIA GeForce GTX 970 (EVGA) \t\tStorage \t\t\t1397GB Western Digital WDC WD15EARS-00MVWB0 (SATA ) \t\t\t298GB Western Digital WDC WD3200AAKS-75L9A0 (SATA )