198129781465", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1542801600.0} {"text": "dont ruin your life with this game", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065166718", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584446400.0} {"text": "Have a lot of friends on Steam? This isn't the game for you. If you have a lot of friends your FPS gets cut down to roughly 43. If you go in Steam offline mode you get 100+ depending on your rig. Why is the game like this? Why should I have to play it in offline mode entirely? It's unoptimized and they don't care. My friendlist is over 400 people and I get: : 110-150 FPS in-game : 31-40 FPS even in menus Why should I play offline to play this game? Why should I clear my friendslist to have solid performance? It's been 3 years and something like this has never been fixed. It's a game problem. If I could rip out the Pawn system entirely with some mod I'd do that but no.", "appid": "367500", "steamid": "profiles/76561198012009261", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601899200.0} {"text": " Thought I'd give the Call of Duty franchise another try since my departure after the release of Ghosts. The nostalgic vibes got to me of my old days in highschool playing COD and pre-ordering DLCS and skins. After all that futuristic nonesense, I thought I'd give the good ol' boots-on-ground another chance, I hope you enjoyed my quick review of COD:WWII. I highly advise against this game as it is just another scheme to squeeze money out of your pockets by making another copy-pasta generic cod from last year. None of that stuff we asked for has changed apart from the boots-on-ground gameplay. None of the recent CODs have given the nostalgic and epic feeling we once had. It's safe to say, that unless the devs get their old team back; this franchise may just be dead to me.", "appid": "696