ing through the entire story over and over to where the game is more of a clicker game than a Visual Novel. However, I would like to take a moment to emphasise how much I LOVE the art, it's beautiful!! That's definitely one of the best qualities of this VN. I also quite enjoy the story and characters, but I must admit that the story is a bit... over the top... and feels very fast-forwarded during most scenes which makes it hard to appreciate fully. (Also, what is with the millions of convenient interruptions? I swear every time something exciting is about to happen, someone's damn phone rings haha) I really, really want to read this fully but right now I can't, it's too buggy. I would love to try it again in the future and will for sure change my review to a more positive one if the buggy bits are fixed because it has a lot of potential! I will admit I struggled to get into it for the first let's say, 20 minutes because it really felt like I was reading some teenage fanfic story but it did get more interesting later on. I only got the common bad ending so I obviously would like to read a beautiful ending with the adorable K-Pop idol wannabe Valen, but I guess I'll save that for when this game gets fixed or if I really feel like clicking my mouse awkwardly in silence a couple thousand times. Overall, it's an average story that has an interesting plot and some nice characters (Valen best boy, fight me) but really, really buggy at the moment. As of now, I will have to give a rating of 4/10. Hope to see updates and fixes!", "appid": "1294680", "steamid": "profiles/76561198368874986", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594209600.0} {"text": "DELETE RUSSIA PLS!", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066321074", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1435665600.0} {"text": "E mai buguit ca ori ce joc posibil", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles