y. One moment I'll be jumping down the stairs, the next I'll be being carried by the dad. Even with all this I still played with my friends, and it was fun for the first 20 minutes and then it really started to get repetitive. I do not recommend this game, and I am refunding it.", "appid": "427730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198322601842", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1484654400.0} {"text": "dont buy this game and save ur money: - 60-70 pers of the broken quests and unmarket on the map - some stars of the level up or wath ever call its buged and u cant rankup ur abiltys - make u do much fights against enemy ..monsters..or dragons with low abilty and sucks weapons at the bigging of the game (iam alweys using the glitcsh of the map to win the fight like go up on big rock and shot 100 arrow with bow) - and the much stuiped think is the dragon can be killed by frozen troll or 7 of 1m pigges tall or giant...he should be stronger then every createur in the game expecte the player or some other caracters - DO NOT BUY IT.. i have 84h recored in the game..belive me its 84h of boring and fixing bugs and much rage :D", "appid": "72850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198395258738", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597838400.0} {"text": "–ë–∞–ª–∞–Ω—Å –ø—Ä–æ—Å—Ç–æ –±–æ–º–±–∞,—É–º–∏—Ä–∞—Ç—å –∫–∞–∂–¥—ã–π —Ä–∞–∑ –æ—Ç —Ç–∞–Ω–∫–∞,–∫–æ–≥–¥–∞ —Ç—ã —Å –ø—É–∫–∞–ª–∫–æ–π –±–µ–≥–∞–µ—à—å.", "appid": "227940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198275029949", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544616000.0} {"text": "This is quite honestly one of the laggiest and glitchiest games I have ever played. My PC is perfectly fine. I have a gtx 980, so my computer isn't the problem. Playing this game is extremely painful. You teleport around, objects get stuck in the walls, and simple tasks like cleaning your mop take immense concentration to not cause the bucket to teleport you across the room and kill you. I've died countless times just by walking into wet floor signs and random clipboards and bullet casings strewn across the floor. I mostly bought this game for its multiplayer, and trust me, I could write for days about how awful that experience was. The underlying gameplay for Viscera Cleanup Deatail isn't nesesarily boring, just almost impossible due to the buggy and uncontrollable physics.", "appid": "246900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198053549889", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1546084800.0} {"text": "No asian server in this game? I think this game already have good engine but the server is dead now and bad for asian player, so if you r asian, just dont buy this game.", "appid": "219640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198396183576", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538654400.0} {"text": "This is a hard one to grade. Fall of Light has an awesome OST and great visuals, but misses the mark as a Souls-lite. Whereas in Dark Souls you're primarily fighting enemies repeatedly until you learn the best way to take them down, in Fall of Light you're fighting iffy hit detection and controls that sometimes don't respond. At just over four hours in, I'm on my 33rd overall \"rebirth\" and essentially trapped just past the first boss. Thanks to weird save spot / respawn location choices you must replay a decent chunk to escape the current area complete with a half dozen enemies. The real interesting bit is where said enemies continually zerg rush me once I free the little girl, yet when I was coming into this area initially they only attacked in pairs once I came into their line of sight. I've now been at it for more than 90 minutes in this spot and am seriously considering throwing in the towel, seeing a completed hit yet it not registering on an enemy multiple times before each death of my character is super disheartening. Worth a peek if you end up with it from a bundle, Fall of Light: Darkest Edition overstays its welcome with technical issues and an iffy save system. Not recommended.", "appid": "633950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198002069169", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602072000.0} {"text": "N√£o abre mais, simplesmente do nada para de abrir", "appid": "12110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198166071435", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533729600.0} {"text": "Disgraceful. Just started the game and the intro was so buggy the carts were jumping about until I eventually got projected into the air and started spinning at 100 miles per hour. In VR that kind of thing can cause extreme sickness to people. How does this stuff pass through quality control?? I would understand if this was a free community-made VR port, but not a ¬£40 release by the developer!!! EDIT: And Steam has rejected my refund because it was outside of the 2-week period, despite the fact the game dOESnT WoRK Fuming", "appid": "611670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198122369466", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597060800.0} {"text": "While I do think that the compaign mode could use a bit of work if they made another killingfloor VR title, the main beef I have with this game is the GOD AWFUL CONTROL! Okay so this game supports locomotion which is a good thing as I think teleporting is for VR ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• and granies who cant last a minute without throwing up, however the locomotion in this game somehow makes the game EVEN WORSE! Turn locomotion on and you're gunna be in a whole bunch of greef, first of all teleporting and locomotion modes lack a method of ingame turning around which means that you gotta watch that wire dangling behind you on that VR rig (the game says it has a way of turning around but I tried every combination of buttons to try and turn in game but it never worked) secondly the locomotion is SOOOOOO JIITTERY! itl make you cringe how bad it is... I was playing in a coop session with someone online so maybe it was a result of ping between me and the host (the other person) but even so ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•! The weapons are just... ass theres the sniper rifle which you get given at one point you have to defend a... thing whatever it is from the horde... the idea is to pick them off with the sniper which is so unnatural to use its much easier to just give the rifle the middle finger and just get out both pistols and pick them off with those... cause you're literally only 30 feet away from them all anyways! Overall couldve been a good game... but this is just a craptacular game... Good graphics though, Il give it that!", "appid": "690810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041405506", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533211200.0} {"text": "Ah man... This was my last try with the CoD franchise. Good thing Steam has a refunding option now! Can buy a lot of better games with the $100 that was refunded. Starting with DOOM, Shadow of Mordor and Shadow of War.", "appid": "476600", "steamid": "profiles/76561197961034809", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1510056000.0} {"text": "Îò•.Í≤ú Ïôú Ïù∏Í∏∞ ÎßéÏùÄÏßÄ Î™®Î•¥Í≤†ÎÑ§Ïöî", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198386350683", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593518400.0} {"text": "this game is full of non-sense ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•. for EX this game have a item which named 300rnd ammo box. but its cant store 300 rnd ammo. only 120 or less ammo. and dev said its make non-sense with this little box can store 300 rnd of bullets. ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• off dayz.", "appid": "221100", "steamid": "profiles/76