s annoying.", "appid": "361420", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073917939", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1484395200.0} {"text": "–° —Å–∞–º–æ–≥–æ –≤—ã—Ö–æ–¥–∞ –Ω–∏—á–µ–≥–æ –Ω–µ –º–µ–Ω—è–µ—Ç—Å—è,—Å–µ—Ä–≤–µ—Ä–∞ –∏ –æ–ø—Ç–∏–º–∏–∑–∞—Ü–∏—è –¥–æ —Å–∏—Ö-–ø–æ—Ä —É–±–æ–≥–∞—è", "appid": "489940", "steamid": "profiles/76561198425591030", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580040000.0} {"text": "Redrum: Dead Diary is basically just a linear sequence of small and easy object puzzles and a stripped down version of the original Big Fish Game. I am at a loss, why they decided to create a steam version which has even less content or quality than the initial release. If you are searching for a HOG like Grim Legends, Enigmatis etc. this is not what you are searching for. You don't move around, there are no animations and the \"story\" itself is badly written and told in static pictures in forms of a diary page, notes or an e-mail. There are four types of puzzles - shape based, word based, search the same item x times and match Image snippets. If you only after a small & very easy HOG game without any challenge/penalties or in search of a relatively fast 100% Achievement game appr. 1 hours (My time includes 2 crashes & looking it up on BigFish), then this might be for you. However, not for the full price! There are much better HOG you can get for the same amount of money.", "appid": "541720", "steamid": "profiles/76561197968312284", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1532001600.0} {"text": "I liked they previous games, they were all good but this one... clearly hasn't been tested by anyone...", "appid": "1185520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198326097650", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574337600.0} {"text": "–ì–ª–∞–≤–Ω–æ–µ –¥–µ—Ä—å–º–æ 2018 –≥–æ–¥–∞, –≥–ª–∞–≤–Ω–æ–µ –¥–µ—Ä—å–º–æ —Ç–≤–∏—á–∞, –∏–≥—Ä–∞ –ø–æ–ª–Ω–∞ –±–∞–≥–æ–≤ –∏ –≥–ª–∞–≤–Ω–æ–µ –õ–ê–ì–û–í. –°–µ—Ä–≤–µ—Ä–∞ –≤ —ç—Ç–æ–π –∏–≥—Ä–µ –≤–∏–¥–∏–º–æ –Ω–∞—Ö–æ–¥—è—Ç—Å—è –≤ –¥–µ—Ä–µ–≤–Ω–µ, –∏–±–æ –∫–∞–∫ –æ–±—å—è—Å–Ω–∏—Ç—å –ø–∏–Ω–≥ –Ω–∞ –ï–≤—Ä–æ–ø–µ –ø–æ–¥ 340. –û–±—ã—á–Ω–∞—è —Ä—ã–≥–æ—Ç–∞ –æ—Ç Hi-Rez Studios (–î–∞—É–Ω—ã –∫–æ—Ç–æ—Ä—ã–µ –Ω–µ –º–æ–≥—É—Ç –ø—Ä–∏–¥—É–º–∞—Ç—å —Å–≤–æ—é –∏–≥—Ä—É). –ö–∞—Ä–æ—á–µ –Ω–µ –Ω–∞–¥–æ —Ç—Ä–∞—Ç–∏—Ç—å –º–µ—Å—Ç–æ –Ω–∞ —Å–≤–æ—ë–º –¥–∏—Å–∫–µ –∏ —Å–≤–æ—ë –≤—Ä–µ–º—è –Ω–∞ —ç—Ç–æ—Ç –∫–∞–ª.", "appid": "813820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198204753148", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1529668800.0} {"text": "—è —ç—Ç—É —Ö—É–π–Ω—é –µ–±–∞–ª", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198838602667", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1527940800.0} {"text": "It's a nice game but it seems difficult to figure out what to do in mission and spend too much time exploring.", "appid": "211820", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972300511", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563105600.0} {"text": "fart", "appid": "945360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198076502834", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596369600.0} {"text": "–°–ª–æ–≤–∞–º–∏ —ç—Ç–æ ******* –Ω–µ –æ–ø–∏—Å–∞—Ç—å...", "appid": "834910", "steamid": "profiles/76561197990641038", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1545566400.0} {"text": "I bought it mainly for the Duke Nukem Tour because im a HUGE Duke Fan but ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô• this was not worth it! In every Cutscene Duke seems completly out of Place and gets somehow called Gray from the other Characters which is kind of ridiculous, also he get pushed around from other characters wtf??? Nobody pushes Duke Nukem around! In my Opinion a very lazy Feature and badly done! If you consider buying it for the Duke Tour do yourself a favor and dont buy it! not worth at all sadly", "appid": "501590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044770902", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "61", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1492603200.0} {"text": "–•—Ä–µ–Ω—å –∫–∞–∫–∞—è —Ç–æ", "appid": "550650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198851469475", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596196800.0} {"text": "I beat this game in less than two hours, and 20 minutes of that was on the first level. It's a slow, dull beat-em-up where you walk up to a group of thugs, beat them up, regenerate your health, clear an obstacle (door, electric wire) and then rinse and repeat. There seems to be less than half a dozen finisher moves and each one takes a good 15 seconds or so to execute, so you might as well strike the enemy a couple of extra times instead to save yourself some time. Combat is as follows: X, Y, X, Y, X, Y. Oncoming attack? Hit B to dodge. X, Y, X, Y, X, Y. If you want to vary things up, you can try different permutations of X and Y, but it doesn't do much. There are combos you can do by hitting three attacks one after another, which momentarily stuns the enemy, but there's very little difference between them and dodging an attack breaks your combo anyway. There's no variety in the combat at all. You're constantly fighting the same two kind of enemies, normal and big enemies. They do occasionally have weapons or a shield. You'll be fighting a big thug with a shield in one level, then in the next level a big police officer with a shield. Your moves remain the same throughout the whole game. How about letting me use that baseball bat I disarmed from an enemy? Isn't that beat'em up 101? Around the second level I got tired of beating up countless groups of enemies, so I tried just walking past them... it worked. In fact, you can walk past about 80% of the enemies in this game. Occasionally there will be a gate you can't climb over until you clear out a group of nearby enemies, but any other type of object (electric box, ladder) you can interact with while in combat. For some reason Kick-Ass has a Spanish accent. The voice acting is atrocious. Besides having little to no emotion, almost all of the voice actors mispronounce words (parkour = parker, goth = ghoth). Every other time you climb a ladder, for some reason Kick-Ass spouts \"Damn. Why the hell am I doing this?\". You'll be hearing the same taunts over and over throughout the game. Besides the issues with clipping, invisible walls galore, the camera obstructing your view in combat, and the lack of mouth movement when characters speak, I actually like the graphic style of the game. If they had put a bit of effort into making the combat fun and varied, maybe put some things to do in the levels besides beating up on groups of thugs every 30 seconds, they might have had a decent game. The game also screws up your system font every time you launch it. Many thanks to the German reviewer here for finding out what the game does: The game disables ClearType in Windows. To re-enable it, go to the Control Panel and search for \"Adjust ClearType text\". Check \"Turn on ClearType\" and hit next a few times to make your fonts normal again.", "appid": "304170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198017975643", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "33", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1423310400.0} {"text": "–ù–µ —É–¥–æ–≤–ª–µ—Ç–≤–æ—Ä–∏–ª–æ –∏ –Ω–µ–ø–æ–Ω—è—Ç–Ω–æ –ø–æ—á—Ç–∏ –Ω–∏—á–µ–≥–æ. –ò–Ω—Ç–µ—Ä–µ—Å–∞ –¥–∞–∂–µ –Ω–µ –≤—ã–∑–≤–∞–ª–æ.", "appid": "604330", "steamid": "profiles/76561198207491752", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602849600.0} {"text": "Too slow and clunky. :/", "appid": "355180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198086671694", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tsta