23200.0} {"text": "I HATE THIS GAME!!!!!!!!!! THIS GAME IS ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Honestly too rough to be any fun. Hunt more like C*** - no interactive tutorial at all, just a crummy manual. not even a sandbox or practise range mode to experiment in - Lack of sound when Alt Tabbed out, or even a notification in the Taskbar to say the game has started - Matchmaking is super ‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•‚ô•, you get rank 9s as a rank 4 or below so you die super fast. Or a rank 15 with superior weapons - doesn't tell you how many other hunters you could face in solo, or how many remaining - TTK is ultra low so you're gonna die really fast - game glitched on me. I found ONE clue for the Butcher and it says I have all 3. Butcher area was empty - keybinds are so horrible and unintuitive. Trying to set custom mappings for the tools and consumables is annoying. If you have x2 syringes and x1 firebomb does that mean you use the Tool 2 slot or the tool 3 slot? There were times it wouldn't even LET me select the item I wanted it was so terrible - speaking of tools and consummables...grenades and offensive tools are in consummables?!? This makes learning the game 1000000x harder than it needs to be and even makes keybind config annoying to do - no dedicated melee key just this crap annoying hold right mouse to aim them fire nonsense - dogs and some of the enemies were just straight up bullet sponges, and wish the right mouse to left mouse nonsense you'll die some stupid deaths ONLY things I liked about this are: - headshotting zombies with my guns or one shotting them with machete or axe is always fun to do - usual stuff like graphics and audio is great, I like the gritty realistic look they were going for - different Hunter rotations mean you try out new weapons each time - you start off with like $3000 so you don't go bankrupt so soon whilst you're learning the game Suggestions: - add an interactive tutorial so newer players can get used to the game's mechanics rather than trial by fire - add a COMPLETELY solo based mode. No other Hunters so us newer players can learn the game without getting shot in the back by other Hunters. Also means we can practise against the Spider and Butcher too Disabled comments so I don't face the cancerous \"get gud\" crowd but honestly this just pissed me off so much. I'd like my 3.3h back please!", "appid": "594650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198053356572", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1534161600.0} {"text": "–ü–æ—Ä–∞–¥–æ–≤–∞–ª–∏ —Ç–æ–ª—å–∫–æ —Ä—É—Å—Å–∫–∏–µ —Å–≤–∏–Ω—å–∏", "appid": "393420", "steamid": "profiles/76561198025347365", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1449316800.0} {"text": "O jogo em si √© bom... Por√©m a Usabilidade dele √© p√©ssima! Os tutoriais e modo carreira s√£o p√©ssimos para se evoluir no decorrer do jogo. Fica a√≠ a depend√™ncia de v√≠deos no youtube e haja paci√™ncia.", "appid": "107410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198000732920", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1485604800.0} {"text": "This game was a massive letdown for me. I went into it thinking it would be a game about (apparent) isolation in the wilderness, and what I got was a game that featured constant radio chatter, with no flow whatsoever. The game is broken up into days, and the days usually feature tasks you need to complete before moving onto the next day. The game is very stop-start which impacted on the enjoyment of the game for me. The game features a free roam mode which, although I haven't tried yet, I know I will enjoy much more than the story element of the game (You need to complete the story to unlock the free roam mode). The story is not very long at all, 3-4 hours maximum. At full price it is a hard 'no recommendation'. At ¬£3.74 (75% off), it is personal preference if you still 